obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line 2
  line `CHAPTER IV`
  line `A SSESSMENT`
  line `S ECTIONS`
  line `14. Return of wealth.`
  line `14A. Power of Board to dispense with furnishing documents, etc., with return of wealth.`
  line `14B. Filing of return in electronic form.`
  line `15. Return after due date and amendment of return.`
  line `15A. Return by whom to be signed.`
  line `15B. Self-assessment.`
  line `15C. [ Omitted. ].`
  line `16. Assessment.`
  line `16A. Reference to Valuation Officer.`
  line `17. Wealth escaping assessment.`
  line `17A. Time limit for completion of assessment and reassessment.`
  line `17B. Interest for defaults in furnishing return of net wealth.`
  line `18. Penalty for failure to furnish returns, to comply with notices and concealment of assets, etc.`
  line `18A. Penalty for failure to answer questions, sign statements, furnish information, allow inspection,`
  line etc.
  line `18B. Power to reduce or waive penalty in certain cases.`
  line `18BA. Power of Commissioner to grant immunity from penalty.`
  line `CHAPTER IVA`
  line `S PECIAL PROVISION FOR AVOIDING REPETITIVE APPEALS`
  line `18C. Procedure when assessee claims identical question of law is pending before High Court or`
  line `Supreme Court.`
  line `CHAPTER IVB`
  line `C HARGE OF ADDITIONAL WEALTH-TAX IN CERTAIN CASES`
  line `18D. [ Omitted. ].`
  line `CHAPTER V`
  line `L IABILITY TO ASSESSMENT IN SPECIAL CASES`
  line `19. Tax of deceased person payable by legal representative.`
  line `19A. Assessment in the case of executors.`
  line `20. Assessment after partition of a Hindu undivided family.`
  line `20A. Assessment after partial partition of a Hindu undivided family.`
  line `21. Assessment when assets are held by courts of wards, administrators-general, etc.`
  line `21A. Assessment in cases of diversion of property, or of income from property, held under trust for`
  line `public charitable or religious purposes.`
