  line `22. Assessment of persons residing outside India.`
  line `CHAPTER VA`
  line `S ETTLEMENT OF CASES`
  line `22A. Definitions.`
  line `22B. Wealth-tax Settlement Commission.`
  line `22BA. Jurisdiction and powers of Settlement Commission.`
  line `22BB. Vice-Chairman to act as Chairman or to discharge his functions in certain circumstances.`
  line `22BC. Power of Chairman to transfer cases from one Bench to another.`
  line `22BD. Decision to be by majority.`
  line `22C. Application for settlement of cases.`
  line `22D. Procedure on receipt of an application under section 22C.`
  line `22DD. Power of Settlement Commission to order provisional attachment to protect revenue.`
  line `22E. Power of Settlement Commission to reopen completed proceedings.`
  line `22F. Powers and procedure of Settlement Commission.`
  line `22G. Inspection, etc., of reports.`
  line `22H. Powers of Settlement Commission to grant immunity from prosecution.`
  line `22HA. Abatement of proceedings before Settlement Commission.`
  line `22HAA. Credit for tax paid in case of abatement of proceedings.`
  line `22-I. Order of settlement to be conclusive.`
  line `22J. Recovery of sums due under order of settlement.`
  line `22K. Bar on subsequent application for settlement.`
  line `22L. Proceedings before the Settlement Commission to be judicial proceedings.`
  line `22M. [ Omitted. ].`
  line `CHAPTER VI`
  line `A PPEALS, REVISIONS AND REFERENCES`
  line `23. Appeal to the Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) from orders of Assessing Officer.`
  line `23A. Appealable orders before Commissioner (Appeals).`
  line `24. Appeal to the Appellate Tribunal from orders of the Deputy Commissioner (Appeals).`
  line `25. Powers of Commissioner to revise orders of subordinate authorities.`
  line `26. Appeal to the Appellate Tribunal from orders of enhancement by Chief Commissioner or`
  line Commissioner.
  line `27A. Appeal to High Court.`
  line `28. Hearing by High Court.`
