obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line 7
  line `THE WEALTH-TAX ACT, 1957`
  line `A CT NO. 27 OF 1957 1`
  line `[12 th September, 1957.]`
  line `An Act to provide for the levy of wealth-tax.`
  line `B E it enacted by Parliament in the Eighth Year of the Republic of India as follows: —`
  line `CHAPTER I`
  line `P RELIMINARY`
  line `1. Short title, extent and commencement. — ( 1 ) This Act may be called the Wealth-tax Act, 1957.`
  line `( 2 ) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line `( 3 ) It shall be deemed to have come into force on the 1st day of April, 1957.`
  line `2. Definitions. — In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires, —`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `3 [( b ) “ Appellate Tribunal ” means the Appellate Tribunal constituted under section 252 of the`
  line `Income-tax Act;`
  line `( c ) “ assessee ” means a person by whom wealth-tax or any other sum of money is payable under`
  line `this Act, and includes —`
  line `( i ) every person in respect of whom any proceeding under this Act has been taken for the`
  line `determination of wealth-tax payable by him or by any other person or the amount of refund due to`
  line `him or such other person;`
  line `( ii ) every person who is deemed to be an assessee under this Act;`
  line `( iii ) every person who is deemed to be an assessee in default under this Act;`
  line `4 [( ca ) “ Assessing Officer ” means the Deputy Commissioner of Income-tax or the Assistant`
  line `Commissioner or the Income-tax Officer who is vested with the relevant jurisdiction by virtue of`
  line `directions or orders issued under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ) of section 120 or any other`
  line `provision of the Income-tax Act which apply for the purposes of wealth-tax under section 8 of this`
  line `Act and also the 5 [Additional Commissioner or] 6 [Additional Director or] Joint Commissioner who is`
  line `directed under clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 4 ) of the said section 120 to exercise or perform all or any of`
  line `the powers and functions conferred on or assigned to the Assessing Officer under that Act;]`
  line `7 [( cb )] “ assessment ” includes reassessment;`
  line `( d ) “ assessment year ” means a period of twelve months commencing on the 1st day of April,`
  line `every year;]`
  line ` Subject to verification and confirmation by the Department.`
  line `1. This Act has been extended with modifications to Dadra and Nagar Haveli, Goa, Daman and Diu, and Pondicherry by`
  line `Regulation 3 of 1963, s. 3( 1 ) and Schedule (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `2. Clause ( a ) omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 128 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988). Earlier clause ( a ) amended by Act 26 of 1988, s. 88`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1988)`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 46 of 1964, s. 2, for clauses ( b ), ( c ) and ( d ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 67, for clause ( ca ) (w.e.f. 1-10-1998). Earlier clause ( ca ) was inserted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 128`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1988) and amended by Act 26 of 1988, s. 88 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 83 (w.r.e.f. 1-6-1994).`
  line `6. Ins. by s. 83, ibid. (w.r.e.f. 1-10-1996).`
  line `7. Clause ( ca ) re-lettered as clause ( cb ) thereof by Act 4 of 1988, s. 128 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
