obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line 10
  line `( iii ) jewellery, bullion, furniture, utensils or any other article made wholly or partly of gold,`
  line `silver, platinum or any other precious metal or any alloy containing one or more of such precious`
  line `metals:`
  line `Provided that where any of the said assets is used by the assessee as stock-in-trade, such asset`
  line `shall be deemed as excluded from the assets specified in this sub-clause;`
  line `( iv ) yachts, boats and aircrafts (other than those used by the assessee for commercial`
  line `purposes);`
  line `( v ) urban land;`
  line `( vi ) cash in hand, in excess of fifty thousand rupees, of individuals and Hindu undivided`
  line `families and in the case of other persons any amount not recorded in the books of account.`
  line `Explanation 1 [ 1 ]. — For the purposes of this clause, —`
  line `( a ) “ jewellery ” includes —`
  line `( i ) ornaments made of gold, silver, platinum or any other precious metal or any alloy`
  line `containing one or more of such precious metals, whether or not containing any precious or semi-`
  line `precious stones, and whether or not worked or sewn into any wearing apparel;`
  line `( ii ) precious or semi-precious stones, whether or not set in any furniture, utensils or other`
  line `article or worked or sewn into any wearing apparel;`
  line `2 [( b ) “ urban land ” means land situate —`
  line `( i ) in any area which is comprised within the jurisdiction of a municipality (whether known`
  line `as a municipality, municipal corporation, notified area committee, town area committee, town`
  line `committee, or by any other name) or a cantonment board and which has a population of not less`
  line `than ten thousand; or`
  line `( ii ) in any area within the distance, measured aerially, —`
  line `( I ) not being more than two kilometres, from the local limits of any municipality or`
  line `cantonment board referred to in sub-clause ( i ) and which has a population of more than ten`
  line `thousand but not exceeding one lakh; or`
  line `( II ) not being more than six kilometres, from the local limits of any municipality or`
  line `cantonment board referred to in sub-clause ( i ) and which has a population of more than one`
  line `lakh but not exceeding ten lakh; or`
  line `( III ) not being more than eight kilometres, from the local limits of any municipality or`
  line `cantonment board referred to in sub-clause ( i ) and which has a population of more than ten`
  line lakh,
  line `but does not include land classified as agricultural land in the records of the Government and used for`
  line `agricultural purposes or land on which construction of a building is not permissible under any law for`
  line `the time being in force in the area in which such land is situated or the land occupied by any building`
  line `which has been constructed with the approval of the appropriate authority or any unused land held by`
  line `the assessee for industrial purposes for a period of two years from the date of its acquisition by him or`
  line `any land held by the assessee as stock-in-trade for a period of ten years from the date of its`
  line `acquisition by him.`
  line `1. Explanation renumbered as Explanation 1 thereof by Act 27 of 1999, s. 91 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 61, for clause ( b ) (w.e.f. 1-4-2014).`
