obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line 11
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of clause ( b ) of Explanation 1, “ population ” means the population`
  line `according to the last preceding census of which the relevant figures have been published before the date`
  line `of valuation.]]`
  line `1 [ Explanation 2. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that “ jewellery ” does not include`
  line `the Gold Deposit Bonds issued under the Gold Deposit Scheme, 1999 notified by the Central`
  line Government;]
  line `( f ) “ Board ” means the 2 [Central Board of Direct Taxes constituted under the Central Boards of`
  line `Revenue Act, 1963 (54 of 1963)];`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `4 [( h ) “ company ” shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause ( 17 ) of section 2 of the`
  line `Income-tax Act;]`
  line `5 [( ha ) “ co-operative society ” means a co-operative society registered under the Co-operative`
  line `Societies Act, 1912 (2 of 1912), or under any other law for the time being in force in any State for the`
  line `registration of co-operative societies;]`
  line `6 * * * * *`
  line `( i ) “ executor ” means an executor or administrator of the estate of a deceased person;`
  line `7 [( ia ) “ High Court ”, in relation to the Union territories of Dadra and Nagar Haveli and Goa,`
  line `Daman and Diu, means the High Court at Bombay;]`
  line `8 [( j ) “ Income-tax Act ” means the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961);]`
  line `9 * * * * *`
  line `10 [( ka ) “ India ” means the territory of India as referred to in article 1 of the Constitution, its`
  line `territorial waters, seabed and subsoil underlying such waters, continental shelf, exclusive economic`
  line `zone or any other maritime zone as referred to in the Territorial Waters, Continental Shelf, Exclusive`
  line `Economic Zone and other Maritime Zones Act, 1976 (80 of 1976), and the air space above its`
  line `territory and territorial waters;]`
  line `11 * * * * *`
  line `12 [( lb ) “ legal representative ” has the meaning assigned to it in clause ( 11 ) of section 2 of the Code`
  line `of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908);]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 91 (w.e.f. 1-4-2000).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 54 of 1963, s. 5, for “Central Board of Revenue constituted under the Central Board of Revenue`
  line `Act, 1924 (4 of 1924)” (w.e.f. 1 -1-1964).`
  line `3. Clauses ( g ) and ( gg ) omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 128 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 128, ibid., for clause ( h ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989)`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 16 of 1972, s. 44 (w.r.e.f. 1-4-1957).`
  line `6. Clause ( hb ) omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 128 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988). Earlier clause ( hb ) inserted by Act 46 of 1964, s. 2`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1965) and later amended by Act 16 of 1972, s. 44 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `7. Ins. by the Taxation Laws (Extension to Union Territories) Regulation, 1963 (3 of 1963) (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 46 of 1964, s. 2, for clause ( j ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `9. Clause ( k ) omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 128 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 83, for clause ( ka ) (w.r.e.f. 25-8-1976). Earlier clause ( ka ) inserted by the Taxation Laws`
  line `(Extension to Union Territories) Regulation, 1963 (3 of 1963) (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `11. Clauses ( l ) and ( la ) omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 128 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988). Earlier clause ( la ) inserted by Act 46 of 1964, s. 2`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `12. Ins. by Act 46 of 1964, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
