obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line 12
  line `1 [( lc ) “ maximum marginal rate ” means the rate of wealth-tax applicable in relation to the highest`
  line `slab of wealth in the case of an individual as specified in Part I of Schedule I;]`
  line `2 [( ld ) “ National Tax Tribunal ” means the National Tax Tribunal established under section 3 of the`
  line `National Tax Tribunal Act, 2005 (49 of 2005);]`
  line `( m ) “ net wealth ” means the amount by which the aggregate value computed in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of this Act of all the assets, wherever located, belonging to the assessee on the`
  line `valuation date, including assets required to be included in his net wealth as on that date under this`
  line `Act, is in excess of the aggregate value of all the debts owed by the assessee 3 [on the valuation date`
  line `which have been incurred in relation to the said assets;]`
  line `( n ) “ prescribed ” means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line `( o ) “ principal officer ”, used with reference to a company, means the secretary, manager,`
  line `managing agent or managing director of the company, and includes any person connected with the`
  line `management of the affairs of the company upon whom the 4 [Assessing Officer] has served a notice of`
  line `his intention of treating him as the principal officer thereof;`
  line `5 [( oa ) “ public servant ” has the same meaning as in section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of`
  line `1860);`
  line `6 [( oaa ) “ registered valuer ” means a person registered as a valuer under section 34AB;]`
  line `( ob ) “ regular assessment ” means the assessment made under 7 [sub-section ( 3 ) or sub-section ( 5 )`
  line `of section 16];]`
  line `( p ) “ Ruler ” means a Ruler as defined in clause ( 22 ) of article 366 of the Constitution;`
  line `( q ) “ valuation date ”, in relation to any year for which an assessment is to be made under this Act,`
  line `means the last day of the previous year as defined in 8 [section 3] of the Income-tax Act, if an`
  line `assessment were to be made under that Act for that year:`
  line `9 [Provided that —`
  line `10 * * * * *`
  line `( ii ) in the case of a person who is not an assessee within the meaning of the Income-tax Act,`
  line `the valuation date for the purposes of this Act shall be the 31st day of March immediately`
  line `preceding the assessment year;`
  line `( iii ) where an assessment is made in pursuance of section 19A, the valuation date shall be the`
  line `same valuation date as would have been adopted in respect of the net wealth of the deceased if he`
  line `were alive;]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 128 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Shall stand inserted (date to be notified) by Act 49 of 2005, s. 30 and the Schedule. This amendment has been struck down by`
  line `the Supreme Court’s Order dated 25th September, 2014 in the Madras Bar Association Vs. Union of India.`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 89, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Wealth -tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 46 of 1964, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 45 of 1972, s. 7 (w.e.f. 15-11-1972).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 51, for “section 16” (w.r.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 46 of 1964, s. 2, for “clause ( 11 ) of section 2” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1965).`
  line `9. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for the proviso (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `10. Clause ( i ) omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 128 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
