  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  sourcePage 13
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line 13
  line `1 [( r ) “Valuation Officer” means a person appointed as a Valuation Officer under section 12A, and`
  line `includes a Regional Valuation Officer, a District Valuation Officer and an Assistant Valuation`
  line Officer;]
  line `2 [( s ) the expressions “Chief Commissioner, Director -General, Commissioner, Commissioner`
  line `(Appeals), Director, Additional Director of Income-tax, Additional Commissioner of Income-tax,`
  line `Joint Director, Joint Commissioner of Income-tax, Deputy Director, Deputy Commissioner, Assistant`
  line `Commissioner, Assistant Director, Income-tax Officer, Inspector of Income-tax and Tax Recovery`
  line `Officer ” shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them under section 2 of the Income-tax`
  line Act.]
  line `CHAPTER II`
  line `C HARGE OF WEALTH-TAX AND ASSETS SUBJECT TO SUCH CHARGE`
  line `3. Charge of wealth-tax. — 3 [( 1 )] 4 [Subject to the other provisions contained in this Act], there shall`
  line `be charged for every 5 [assessment year] commencing on and from the first day of April, 1957 6 [but before`
  line `the first day of April, 1993], a tax (hereinafter referred to as wealth-tax) in respect of the net wealth on the`
  line `corresponding valuation date of every individual, Hindu undivided family and company 7 [at the rate or`
  line `rates specified in Schedule I].`
  line `6 [( 2 ) Subject to the other provisions contained in this Act, there shall be charged for every assessment`
  line `year commencing on and from the 1st day of April, 1993, 8 [but before the 1st day of April, 2016], wealth-`
  line `tax in respect of the net wealth on the corresponding valuation date of every individual, Hindu undivided`
  line `family and company, at the rate of one per cent. of the amount by which the net wealth exceeds fifteen`
  line `lakh rupees:]`
  line `9 [Provided that in the case of every assessment year commencing on and from the 1st day of April,`
  line `2010, the provisions of this section shall have effect as if for the words “ fifteen lakh rupees ”, the words`
  line `“ thirty lakh rupees ” had been substituted.]`
  line `4. Net wealth to include certain assets. — ( 1 ) 10 [In computing the net wealth —`
  line `( a ) of an individual, there shall be included, as belonging to that individual, the value of assets`
  line `which on the valuation date are held — ]`
  line `11 [( i ) by the spouse of such individual to whom such assets have been transferred by the`
  line `individual, directly or indirectly, otherwise than for adequate consideration or in connection with`
  line `an agreement to live apart, or`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 45 of 1972, s. 7, for clause ( r ) (w.e.f. 15-11-1972).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 67, for clause ( s ) (w.e.f. 1-10-1998).`
  line `3. Section 3 renumbered as sub-section ( 1 ) thereof by Act 18 of 1992, s. 90 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `4. Amendment introduced by the Direct Tax Laws (Amendment) Act, 1987 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989), has become redundant in view of`
  line `omission of provision relating to additional wealth-tax.`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 46 of 1964, s. 3, for “financial year” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1965).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 90 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 66 of 1976, s. 27, for “at the rate or rates specified in the Schedule” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1977).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 81 (w.e.f. 1-4-2016).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 83 (w.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 59, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Earlier it was amended by Act 46 of 1964, s. 4`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `11. Subs. by Act 46 of 1964, s. 4, for sub-clauses ( i ), ( ii ) and ( iii ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
