obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line 14
  line `( ii ) by a minor child, not being 1 [a minor child suffering from any disability of the nature`
  line `specified in section 80U of the Income-tax Act or] a married daughter, of such individual, 2 *** or`
  line `( iii ) by a person or association of persons to whom such assets have been transferred by the`
  line `individual 3 [, directly or indirectly] otherwise than for adequate consideration for the immediate`
  line `or deferred benefit of the individual, his or her spouse 4 ***, or]`
  line `( iv ) by a person or association of persons to whom such assets have been transferred by the`
  line `individual otherwise than under an irrevocable transfer, 3 [or]`
  line `3 [( v ) by the son ’ s wife, 5 *** of such individual, to whom such assets have been transferred by`
  line `the individual, directly or indirectly, on or after the 1st day of June, 1973, otherwise than for`
  line `adequate consideration,] 6 [or]`
  line `6 [( vi ) by a person or association of persons to whom such assets have been transferred by the`
  line `individual, directly or indirectly, on or after the 1st day of June, 1973, otherwise than for`
  line `adequate consideration for the immediate or deferred benefit of the son ’ s wife, 5 *** of such`
  line `individual or both,]`
  line `whether the assets referred to in any of the sub-clauses aforesaid are held in the form in which they were`
  line `transferred or otherwise:`
  line `7 [Provided that where the transfer of such assets or any part thereof is either chargeable to gift-tax`
  line `under the Gift-tax Act, 1958 (18 of 1958), or is not chargeable under section 5 of that Act, for any`
  line `assessment year commencing 8 [after the 31st day of March, 1964, but before the 1st day of April, 1972,]`
  line `the value of such assets or part thereof, as the case may be, shall not be included in computing the net`
  line `wealth of the individual:]`
  line `9 [Provided further that nothing contained in sub-clause ( ii ) shall apply in respect of such assets as`
  line `have been acquired by the minor child out of his income referred to in the proviso to sub-section ( 1A ) of`
  line `section 64 of the Income-tax Act and which are held by him on the valuation date:`
  line `Provided also that where the assets held by a minor child are to be included in computing the net`
  line `wealth of an individual, such assets shall be included, —`
  line `( a ) where the marriage of his parents subsists, in the net wealth of that parent whose net wealth`
  line `(excluding the assets of the minor child so includible under this sub-section) is greater; or`
  line `( b ) where the marriage of his parents does not subsist, in the net wealth of that parent who`
  line `maintains the minor child in the previous year as defined in section 3 of the Income-tax Act,`
  line `and where any such assets are once included in the net wealth of either parent, any such assets shall not be`
  line `included in the net wealth of the other parent in any succeeding year unless the Assessing Officer is`
  line `satisfied, after giving that parent an opportunity of being heard, that it is necessary so to do;]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 51 (w.e.f. 1-4-1995).`
  line `2. The words “to whom such assets have been transferred by t he individual, directly or indirectly, otherwise than for adequate`
  line `consideration,” omitted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 91 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1993).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 82 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `4. The words “or minor child (not being a married daughter) or both” omitted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 91 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `5. The words “or the son’s minor child,” omitted by s. 91, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 54 (w.e.f. 1-4-1985).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 46 of 1964, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 32 of 1971, s. 31, for “after the 31st day of March, 1964” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1972).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 91 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
