  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  sourcePage 15
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line 15
  line `1 [( b ) of an assessee who is a partner in a firm or a member of an association of persons (not being`
  line `a co-operative housing society), there shall be included, as belonging to that assessee, the value of`
  line `his 2 [interest in the assets of the firm] or association determined in the manner laid down in`
  line `Schedule III:`
  line `3 [Provided that where a minor is admitted to the benefits of partnership in a firm, the value of the`
  line `interest of such minor in the firm, determined in the manner specified above, shall be included in the`
  line `net wealth of the parent of the minor, so far as may be, in accordance with the provisions of the third`
  line `proviso to clause ( a ).]]`
  line `4 [( 1A ) Where, in the case of an individual being a member of a Hindu undivided family, any property`
  line `having been the separate property of the individual has, at any time after the 31st day of December, 1969,`
  line `been converted by the individual into property belonging to the family through the act of impressing such`
  line `separate property with the character of property belonging to the family or throwing it 5 [into the common`
  line `stock of the family or been transferred by the individual, directly or indirectly, to the family otherwise`
  line `than for adequate consideration (the property so converted or transferred being hereinafter referred to as`
  line `the converted property)], then, notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act or in`
  line `any other law for the time being in force, for the purpose of computing the net wealth of the individual`
  line `under this Act for any assessment year commencing on or after the 1st day of April, 1972, —`
  line `( a ) the individual shall be deemed to have transferred the converted property, through the family,`
  line `to the members of the family for being held by them jointly;`
  line `( b ) the converted property or any part thereof 6 *** shall be deemed to be assets belonging to the`
  line `individual and not to the family;`
  line `7 [( c ) where the converted property has been the subject-matter of a partition (whether partial or`
  line `total) amongst the members of the family, the converted property or any part thereof which is`
  line `received by the spouse 8 *** of the individual on such partition shall be deemed to be assets`
  line `transferred indirectly by the individual to the spouse 8 *** and the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ) shall,`
  line `so far as may be, apply accordingly:]`
  line `Provided that the property referred to in clause ( b ) or clause ( c ) shall, on being included in the net`
  line `wealth of the individual, be excluded from the net wealth of the family or, as the case may be, the`
  line `spouse 8 *** of the individual.]`
  line `9 * * * * *`
  line `10 * * * * *`
  line `( 4 ) Nothing contained in clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 1 ) shall apply to any such transfer as is referred to`
  line `therein made by an individual before the 1st day of April, 1956, and the value of any assets so transferred`
  line `shall not be included in the computation of his net wealth.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 59, for clause ( b ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Earlier it was amended by Act 32 of 1971, s. 31`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1972).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 91, for “interest in the firm” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1993).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 91, ibid., for the proviso (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 32 of 1971, s. 31 (w.e.f. 1-4-1972).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 21 of 1979, s. 23, for “into the common stock of the family (such property being hereinafter referred to as the`
  line `converted property)” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1980).`
  line `6. The words “, in so far as it is attributable to the interest of the individual in the property of the family,” omitted by`
  line `Act 41 of 1975, s. 82 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 82, ibid., for clause ( c ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `8. The words “or minor child” omitted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 91 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1993).`
  line `9. Sub-section ( 2 ) omitted by Act 3 of 1989, s. 59 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `10. Sub-section ( 3 ) omitted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 91 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993). Earlier it was amended by Act 21 of 1979, s. 23`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1980) and Act 25 of 1975, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-4-1975),`
