  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  sourcePage 16
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line 16
  line `1 [( 4A ) Notwithstanding anything in sub-section (4), nothing contained in clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `shall apply to any such transfer as is referred to therein made before the 1st day of April, 1963, by an`
  line `individual who but for the extension of this Act to the Union territories of Dadra and Nagar Haveli, Goa,`
  line `Daman and Diu, and Pondicherry, would not have been an assessee, and the value of any assets so`
  line `transferred shall not be included in the computation of his net wealth.]`
  line `( 5 ) The value of any assets transferred under an irrevocable transfer shall be liable to be included in`
  line `computing the net wealth of the transferor as and when the power to revoke arises to him.`
  line `2 [( 5A ) Where a gift of money from one person to another is made by means of entries in the books of`
  line `account maintained by the person making the gift or by an individual or a Hindu undivided family or a`
  line `firm or an association of persons or body of individuals with whom or which he has business or other`
  line `relationship, the value of such gift shall be liable to be included in computing the net wealth of the person`
  line `making the gift unless he proves to the satisfaction of the 3 [Assessing Officer] that the money has actually`
  line `been delivered to the other person at the time the entries were made.]`
  line `4 [( 6 ) For the purposes of this Act, the holder of an impartible estate shall be deemed to be the`
  line `individual owner of all the properties comprised in the estate.`
  line `5 [( 7 ) Where the assessee is a member of a co-operative society, company or other association of`
  line `persons and a building or part thereof is allotted or leased to him under a house building scheme of the`
  line `society, company or association, as the case may be, the assessee shall, notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in this Act or any other law for the time being in force, be deemed to be the owner of such`
  line `building or part and the value of such building or part, shall be included in computing the net wealth of`
  line `the assessee; and, in determining the value of such building or part, the value of any outstanding`
  line `instalments of the amount payable under such scheme by the assessee to the society, company or`
  line `association towards the cost of such building or part and the land appurtenant thereto shall, whether the`
  line `amount so payable is described as such or in any other manner in such scheme, be deducted as a debt`
  line `owed by him in relation to such building or part.`
  line `( 8 ) A person —`
  line `( a ) who is allowed to take or retain possession of any building or part thereof in part performance`
  line `of a contract of the nature referred to in section 53A of the Transfer of Property Act, 1882 (4 of`
  line `1882);`
  line `( b ) who acquires any rights (excluding any rights by way of a lease from month to month or for a`
  line `period not exceeding one year) in or with respect to any building or part thereof by virtue of any such`
  line `transaction as is referred to in clause ( f ) of section 269UA of the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961),`
  line `shall be deemed to be the owner of that building or part thereof and the value of such building or part`
  line `shall be included in computing the net wealth of such person.]`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) the expression “ transfer ” includes any disposition, settlement, trust, covenant, agreement or`
  line `arrangement; 6 ***`
  line `2 [( aa ) the expression “ child ” includes a step-child and an adopted child;]`
  line `1. Ins. by The Taxation Laws (Extension to Union Territories) Regulation, 1963 (3 of 1963), s. 3 and the Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 82 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w. e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 46 of 1964, s. 4, for the Explanation (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 33 of 1996, s. 57, for sub-section ( 7 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1997). Earlier sub-section ( 7 ) was inserted by Act 32 of 1971,`
  line `s. 31 (w.e.f. 1-4-1972).`
  line `6. The word “and” omitted by Act 32 of 1971, s. 31 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1972).`
