obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line 17
  line `( b ) the expression “ irrevocable transfer ” includes a transfer of assets which, by the terms of the`
  line `instrument effecting it, is not revocable for a period exceeding six years or during the lifetime of the`
  line `transferee, and under which the transferor derives no direct or indirect benefit, but does not include a`
  line `transfer of assets if such instrument —`
  line `( i ) contains any provision for the retransfer, directly or indirectly, of the whole or any part of`
  line `the assets or income therefrom to the transferor, or`
  line `( ii ) in any way gives the transferor a right to reassume power, directly or indirectly, over the`
  line `whole or any part of the assets or income therefrom;] 1 [and]`
  line `2 [( c ) the expression “ property ” includes any interest in any property, movable or immovable, the`
  line `proceeds of sale thereof and any money or investment for the time being representing the proceeds of`
  line `sale thereof and where the property is converted into any other property by any method, such other`
  line `property 3 ***.`
  line `4 * * * * *]`
  line `5. Exemptions in respect of certain assets. — 5 [ 6 *** Wealth-tax shall not be payable by an assessee`
  line `in respect of the following assets], and such assets shall not be included in the net wealth of the`
  line `assessee —`
  line `( i ) any property held by him under trust or other legal obligation for any public purpose of a`
  line `charitable or religious nature in India:`
  line `7 [Provided that nothing contained in this clause shall apply to any property forming part of any`
  line `business, not being a business referred to in clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) of sub-section (4A) of section 11`
  line `of the Income-tax Act in respect of which separate books of account are maintained or a business`
  line `carried on by an institution, fund or trust referred to in 8 *** clause ( 23B ) or clause ( 23C ) of section 10`
  line `of that Act;]`
  line `( ii ) the interest of the assessee in the coparcenary property of any Hindu undivided family of`
  line `which he is a member;`
  line `( iii ) 9 [any one building in the occupation of a Ruler, being a building which immediately before`
  line `the commencement of the Constitution (Twenty-sixth Amendment) Act, 1971, was his official`
  line `residence by virtue of a declaration by the Central Government] under paragraph 13 of the Merged`
  line `States (Taxation Concessions) Order, 1949, or paragraph 15 of the Part B States (Taxation`
  line `Concessions) Order, 1950;`
  line `10 * * * * *`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 82 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 32 of 1971, s. 31 (w.e.f. 1-4-1972).`
  line `3. The word “and” omitted by Act 41 of 1975, s. 82 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1976).`
  line `4. Clause ( d ) omitted by s. 82, ibid., (w.e.f. 1-4-1976). Earlier clause ( d ) inserted by Act 32 of 1971, s. 31 (w.e.f. 1-4-1972).`
  line `5. The brackets, figures, words and letters, “( 1 ) Subject to the provisions of sub-section ( 1A ),” omitted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 92`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 19 of 1970, s. 26, for “Wealth - tax shall not be payable by an assessee in respect of the following assets”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1971).`
  line `7. Restored by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Earlier the proviso was added by Act 32 of 1985, s. 37 (w.e.f. 1-4-1986)`
  line `which was later substituted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 60 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `8. The words brackets, figures and letters “clause ( 22 ) or clause ( 22A ) or” omitted by Act 21 of 1998, s. 68 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1999).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 54 of 1972, s. 5, for “any one building in the occupation of a Ruler declared by the Central Government as his`
  line `official residence” (w.e.f. 28 -12-1971).`
  line `10. Clauses ( iv ) to ( viii ) omitted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 92 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
