obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line 18
  line `1 [( iv )] jewellery in the possession of any Ruler, not being his personal property, which has been`
  line `recognised before the commencement of this Act, by the Central Government as his heirloom or,`
  line `where no such recognition exists, which the Board may, subject to any rules that may be made by the`
  line `Central Government in this behalf, recognise as his heirloom at the time of his first assessment to`
  line `wealth-tax under this Act:`
  line `2 [Provided that in the case of jewellery recognised by the Central Government as aforesaid, such`
  line `recognition shall be subject to the following conditions, namely: —`
  line `( i ) that the jewellery shall be permanently kept in India and shall not be removed outside`
  line `India except for a purpose and period approved by the Board;`
  line `( ii ) that reasonable steps shall be taken for keeping the jewellery substantially in its original`
  line shape;
  line `( iii ) that reasonable facilities shall be allowed to any officer of Government authorised by the`
  line `Board in this behalf to examine the jewellery as and when necessary; and`
  line `( iv ) that if any of the conditions hereinbefore specified is not being duly fulfilled, the Board`
  line `may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, withdraw the recognition retrospectively with effect`
  line `from the date of commencement of clause ( b ) of section 5 of the Rulers of Indian States`
  line `(Abolition of Privileges) Act, 1972 (54 of 1972), and in such a case, wealth-tax shall become`
  line `payable by the Ruler for all the assessment years after such commencement for which the`
  line `jewellery was exempted on account of the recognition.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of clause ( iv ) of the foregoing proviso, the fair market value of any`
  line `jewellery on the date of the withdrawal of the recognition in respect thereof shall be deemed to be the fair`
  line `market value of such jewellery on each successive valuation date relevant for the assessment years`
  line `referred to in the said proviso:`
  line `Provided further that the aggregate amount of wealth-tax payable in respect of any jewellery under`
  line `clause ( iv ) of the foregoing proviso for all the assessment years referred to therein shall not in any case`
  line `exceed fifty per cent. of its fair market value on the valuation date relevant for the assessment year in`
  line `which recognition was withdrawn;]`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `4 [ 5 [( v )] in the case of an assessee, being a person of Indian origin 6 [or a citizen of India (hereafter`
  line `in this clause referred to as such person)] who was ordinarily residing in a foreign country and who,`
  line `on leaving such country, has returned to India with the intention of permanently residing therein,`
  line `moneys and the value of assets brought by him into India and the value of the assets acquired by him`
  line `out of such moneys 7 [within one year immediately preceding the date of his return and at any time`
  line `thereafter]:`
  line `Provided that this exemption shall apply only for a period of seven successive assessment years`
  line `commencing with the assessment year next following the date on which such person returned to India.`
  line `1. Clause ( xiv ) renumbered as clause ( iv ) thereof by Act 18 of 1992, s. 92 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `2. Added by Act 54 of 1972, s. 5 (w.e.f. 9-9-1972).`
  line `3. Clauses ( xv ) to ( xxxii ) omitted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 92 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `4. Clause ( xxxiii ) renumbered as clause ( v ) thereof by s. 92, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 66 of 1976, s. 27 (w.e.f. 1-4-1977).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 54 (w.r.e.f. 1-4-1977).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 23 of 1986, s. 40 (w.e.f. 1-4-1987).`
