  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  sourcePage 19
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line 19
  line `Explanation 1 [1]. — A person shall be deemed to be of Indian origin if he, or either of his parents or`
  line `any of his grand-parents, was born in undivided India.]`
  line `2 [ Explanation 2. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that moneys standing to the credit`
  line `of such person in a Non-resident (External) Account in any bank in India in accordance with the Foreign`
  line `Exchange Regulation Act, 1973 (46 of 1973), and any rules made thereunder, on the date of his return to`
  line `India, shall be deemed to be moneys brought by him into India on that date;]`
  line `3 [( vi ) one house or part of a house or a plot of land belonging to an individual or a Hindu`
  line `undivided family:`
  line `Provided that wealth-tax shall not be payable by an assessee in respect of an asset being a plot of`
  line `land comprising an area of five hundred square metres or less.]`
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `5 * * * * *`
  line `6. Exclusion of assets and debts outside India. — 6 [In computing the net wealth of an individual who`
  line `is not a citizen of India or of an individual] or a Hindu undivided family not resident in India or resident`
  line `but not ordinarily resident in India, or of a company not resident in India during the year ending on the`
  line `valuation date —`
  line `( i ) the value of the assets and debts located outside India; and`
  line `( ii ) the value of the assets in India represented by any loans or debts owing to the assessee in any`
  line `case where the interest, if any, payable on such loans or debts is not to be included in the total income`
  line `of the assessee under 7 [section 10] of the Income-tax Act;`
  line `shall not be taken into account.`
  line `Explanation 1. — An individual or a Hindu undivided family shall be deemed to be not resident in`
  line `India or resident but not ordinarily resident in India during the year ending on the valuation date if in`
  line `respect of that year the individual or the Hindu undivided family, as the case may be, is not resident in`
  line `India or resident but not ordinarily resident in India within the meaning of the Income-tax Act.`
  line `8 [ Explanation 1A. — Where in the case of an individual the value of an asset in India is represented by`
  line `any debt owing to him, being any moneys to his credit in a Non-resident (External) Account, the interest`
  line `payable on which is not to be included in his total income under 9 [sub-clause ( ii ) of clause ( 4 )] of section`
  line `10 of the Income-tax Act, the provisions of this section shall, in relation to such asset, apply subject to the`
  line `modification that the reference in this section to an individual not resident in India shall be construed as a`
  line `reference to a person resident outside India as defined in clause ( q ) of section 2 of the Foreign Exchange`
  line `Regulation Act, 1973 (46 of 1973).]`
  line `1. The Explanation renumbered as Explanation 1 thereof by Act 23 of 1986, s. 40 (w.r.e.f. 1-4-1977).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 40, ibid. (w.r.e.f. 1-4-1977).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 68, for clause ( vi ) (w.e.f.. 1-4-1998).`
  line `4. Clauses ( xxxiv ) omitted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 92 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993). Earlier it was inserted by Act 66 of 1976, s. 27`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `5. Sub-sections ( 1A ) to ( 4 ) omitted by s. 92, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 11 of 1958, s. 14, for “In computing the net wealth of an individual” (w.r.e.f. 1 -4-1957).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 46 o f 1964, s. 6, for “sub -section ( 3 ) of section 4” (w.e.f.1 -4-1965).`
  line `8. The Explanation inserted by Act 14 of 1982, s. 35 (w.e.f. 1-4-1982).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 61, for “clause ( 4A )” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
