obj_root_law_sections_20:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-20
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Page 20`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  sourcePage 20
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line 20
  line `Explanation 2. — A company shall be deemed to be resident in India during the year ending on the`
  line `valuation date, if —`
  line `( a ) it is a company formed and registered under the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), or is an`
  line `existing company within the meaning of that Act; or`
  line `( b ) during that year the control and management of its affairs is situated wholly in India.`
  line `1 [7. Value of assets, how to be determined. — ( 1 ) Subject to the provisions of sub-section ( 2 ), the`
  line `value of any asset, other than cash, for the purposes of this Act shall be its value as on the valuation date`
  line `determined in the manner laid down in Schedule III.`
  line `( 2 ) The value of a house belonging to the assessee and exclusively used by him for residential`
  line `purposes throughout the period of twelve months immediately preceding the valuation date, may, at the`
  line `option of the assessee, be taken to be the value determined in the manner laid down in Schedule III as on`
  line `the valuation date next following the date on which he became the owner of the house or the valuation`
  line `date relevant to the assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1971, whichever valuation date`
  line `is later.`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section, —`
  line `( i ) where the house has been constructed by the assessee, he shall be deemed to have become the`
  line `owner thereof on the date on which the construction of such house was completed;`
  line `( ii ) “house” includes a part of a house being an independent residential unit.]`
  line `CHAPTER III`
  line `W EALTH-TAX AUTHORITIES`
  line `3 [ 8. Wealth-tax authorities and their jurisdiction. — The income-tax authorities specified in`
  line `section 116 of the Income-tax Act shall be the wealth-tax authorities for the purposes of this Act and`
  line `every such authority shall exercise the powers and perform the functions of a wealth-tax authority under`
  line `this Act in respect of any individual, Hindu undivided family or company, and for this purpose his`
  line `jurisdiction under this Act shall be the same as he has under the Income-tax Act by virtue of orders or`
  line `directions issued under section 120 of that Act (including orders or directions assigning concurrent`
  line `jurisdiction) or under any other provision of that Act.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, the wealth-tax authority having jurisdiction in relation`
  line `to a person who is not an assessee within the meaning of the Income-tax Act shall be the wealth-tax`
  line `authority having jurisdiction in respect of the area in which that person resides.`
  line `8A. [ Power of Commissioner respecting specified areas, cases, persons, etc.] — Omitted by the Direct`
  line `Tax Laws ( Amendment ) Act, 1987 (4 of 1988), s. 132 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988). Earlier it was inserted by Act 46`
  line `of 1964, s. 9 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 62, for section 7 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Earlier section 7 was amended by Act 46 of 1964, s. 6`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1965), Act 45 of 1972, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-4-1973), Act 66 of 1976, s. 27 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976) and Act 44 of 1980, s. 38`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1980).`
  line `2. The proviso omitted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 93 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 131, for sections 8, 9, 10 and 11 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988). Earlier these sections was amended by Act 46 of`
  line `1964, s. 8 and 10 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965), Act 20 of 1967, s. 34 (w.e.f. 1-4-1967) and Act 41 of 1975, s. 84 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-21
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Page 21`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  sourcePage 21
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line 21
  line `8AA. [ Concurrent jurisdiction of Inspecting Assistant Commissioner and Wealth-tax`
  line `Officer.] — Omitted by the Direct Tax Laws ( Amendment ) Act, 1987 (4 of 1988), s. 132 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `Earlier it was inserted by Act 41 of 1975, s. 85 ( w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `8B. [ Power to transfer cases. ] — Omitted by s. 132, ibid. ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `9. Control of wealth-tax authorities. — Section 118 of the Income-tax Act and any notification`
  line `issued thereunder shall apply in relation to the control of wealth-tax authorities as they apply in relation to`
  line `the control of the corresponding income-tax authorities, except to the extent to which the Board may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, otherwise direct in respect of any wealth-tax authority.`
  line `9A. [ Commissioners of Wealth-tax ( Appeals ).] — Omitted by the Direct Tax Laws ( Amendment ) Act,`
  line `1987 (4 of 1988), s. 132 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `10. Instructions to subordinate authorities. — ( 1 ) The Board may, from time to time, issue such`
  line `orders, instructions and directions to other wealth-tax authorities as it may deem fit for the proper`
  line `administration of this Act, and such authorities and all other persons employed in the execution of this`
  line `Act shall observe and follow such orders, instructions and directions of the Board:`
  line `Provided that no such orders, instructions or directions shall be issued —`
  line `( a ) so as to require any wealth-tax authority to make a particular assessment or to dispose of a`
  line `particular case in a particular manner; or`
  line `( b ) so as to interfere with the discretion of the Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) or Commissioner`
  line `(Appeals) in the exercise of his appellate functions.`
  line `( 2 ) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, —`
  line `( a ) the Board may, if it considers it necessary or expedient so to do, for the purpose of proper and`
  line `efficient management of the work of assessment and collection of revenue, issue, from time to time,`
  line `(whether by way of relaxation of any of the provisions of sections 1 [14, 15, 16, 17, 17B,] 18 and 35 or`
  line `otherwise), general or special orders in respect of any class of cases, setting forth directions or`
  line `instructions (not being prejudicial to assessees) as to the guidelines, principles or procedures to be`
  line `followed by other wealth-tax authorities in the work relating to assessment or collection of revenue or`
  line `the initiation of proceedings for the imposition of penalties and any such order may, if the Board is of`
  line `opinion that it is necessary in the public interest so to do, be published and circulated in the`
  line `prescribed manner for general information;`
  line `( b ) the Board may, if it considers it desirable or expedient so to do for avoiding genuine hardship`
  line `in any case or class of cases, by general or special order, authorise any wealth-tax authority, not being`
  line `a Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) or Commissioner (Appeals), to admit an application or claim for`
  line `any exemption, deduction, refund or any other relief under this Act after the expiry of the period`
  line `specified by or under this Act for making such application or claim and deal with the same on merits`
  line `in accordance with law.]`
  line `10A. [ Directors of Inspection.] — Omitted by the Direct Tax Laws ( Amendment ) Act, 1987 (4 of`
  line `1988), ( w.e.f. 1-4-1988). Earlier section 10 A was inserted by Act 46 of 1964, s. 10 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 53, for “16, 17” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1990).`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-22
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Page 22`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  sourcePage 22
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line 22
  line `11. Jurisdiction of Assessing Officers and power to transfer cases. — ( 1 ) The provisions of sections`
  line `124 and 127 of the Income-tax Act shall, so far as may be, apply for the purposes of this Act as they`
  line `apply for the purposes of the Income-tax Act, subject to the modifications specified in sub-section ( 2 ).`
  line `( 2 ) The modifications referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be the following, namely: —`
  line `( a ) in section 124 of the Income-tax Act, —`
  line `( i ) in sub-section ( 3 ), references to the provisions of the Income-tax Act shall be construed as`
  line `references to the corresponding provisions of the Wealth-tax Act;`
  line `( ii ) sub-section ( 5 ) shall be omitted;`
  line `( b ) in section 127 of the Income-tax Act, in the Explanation below sub-section 1 [( 4 )], references`
  line `to proceedings under the Income-tax Act shall be construed as including references to proceedings`
  line `under the Wealth-tax Act.]`
  line `11A. [ Inspector of Wealth-tax. ] — Omitted by the Direct Tax Laws ( Amendment ) Act, 1987 (4 of`
  line `1988), s. 132 ( w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1988). Earlier inserted by Act 46 of 1964, s. 11 ( w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1965) and later`
  line `substituted by Act 20 of 1967, s. 34 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1967).`
  line `11AA. [ Commissioner competent to perform any function or functions.] — Omitted by s. 132, ibid.`
  line `w.e.f. 1-4-1988. Earlier section 11 AA was inserted by Act 19 of 1970, s. 26 ( w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1970).`
  line `11B. [ Wealth-tax Officer competent to perform any function or functions.] — Omitted by s. 132, ibid.`
  line `( w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1988). Earlier section 11 B was inserted by Act 20 of 1967, s. 34 ( w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1967) and later`
  line `amended by Act 41 of 1975, s. 87 ( w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `12. [ Control of wealth-tax authorities.] — Omitted by s. 132, ibid. ( w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1988). Earlier`
  line `substituted by Act 46 of 1964, s. 11 ( w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1965).`
  line `2 [12A. Appointment of Valuation Officers. — ( 1 ) The Central Government may appoint as many`
  line `Valuation Officers as it thinks fit.`
  line `( 2 ) Subject to the rules and orders of the Central Government regulating the conditions of service of`
  line `persons in public services and posts, a wealth-tax authority may appoint as many overseers, surveyors and`
  line `assessors as may be necessary to assist the Valuation Officers in the performance of their functions.]`
  line `13. [ Wealth-tax authorities to follow orders, etc., of the Board.] — Omitted by the Direct Tax Laws`
  line `( Amendment ) Act, 1987 (4 of 1988), s. 132 ( w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1988).`
  line `3 [13A. Powers of 4 [Director-General or Director], 5 [Chief Commissioner or Commissioner]`
  line `and 6 [ Joint Commissioner] to make enquiries. — The 4 [Director-General or Director], the 5 [Chief`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner] and the 6 [Joint Commissioner] shall be competent to make any enquiry`
  line `under this Act, and for this purpose shall have all the powers that an 7 [Assessing Officer] has under this`
  line `Act in relation to the making of enquiries.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 63, for “( 5 )” (w.r.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 45 of 1972, s. 9 (w.e.f. 15-11-1972).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 46 of 1964, s. 13 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Director of Inspection” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 127, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 3, for “Deputy Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988). Earlier the quoted words were substituted by Act`
  line `4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Inspecting Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-23
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Page 23`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  sourcePage 23
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line 23
  line `CHAPTER IV`
  line `A SSESSMENT`
  line `14. Return of wealth. — 1 [( 1 ) Every person, if his net wealth or the net wealth of any other person in`
  line `respect of which he is assessable under this Act on the valuation date exceeded the maximum amount`
  line `which is not chargeable to wealth-tax, shall, on or before the due date, furnish a return of his net wealth or`
  line `the net wealth of such other person as on that valuation date in the prescribed form and verified in the`
  line `prescribed manner setting forth particulars of such net wealth and such other particulars as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line `Explanation. — In this sub-section, “ due date ” in relation to an assessee under this Act shall be the`
  line `same date as that applicable to an assessee under the Income-tax Act under the Explanation to sub-section`
  line `( 1 ) of section 139 of the Income-tax Act.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act, a return of net wealth`
  line `which shows the net wealth below the maximum amount which is not chargeable to tax shall be deemed`
  line `never to have been furnished:`
  line `Provided that this sub-section shall not apply to a return furnished in response to a notice under`
  line `section 17.]`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `3 [ 14A. Power of Board to dispense with furnishing documents, etc., with return of wealth. — The`
  line `Board may make rules providing for a class or classes of persons who may not be required to furnish`
  line `documents, statements, receipts, certificates, audit reports, reports of registered valuer or any other`
  line `documents, which are otherwise under any other provisions of this Act, except section 14B, required to be`
  line `furnished, along with the return but on demand to be produced before the Assessing Officer.`
  line `14B. Filing of return in electronic form. — The Board may make rules providing for —`
  line `( a ) the class or classes of persons who shall be required to furnish the return in electronic form;`
  line `( b ) the form and the manner in which the return in electronic form may be furnished;`
  line `( c ) the documents, statements, receipts, certificates, audit reports, reports of registered valuer or`
  line `any other documents which may not be furnished along with the return in electronic form but shall be`
  line `produced before the Assessing Officer on demand;`
  line `( d ) the computer resource or the electronic record to which the return in electronic form may be`
  line transmitted.]
  line `4 [ 15. Return after due date and amendment of return. — If any person has not furnished a return`
  line `within the time allowed under sub- section (1) of section 14 or under a notice issued under clause ( i ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 4 ) of section 16, or having furnished a return discovers any omission or wrong statement`
  line `therein, he may furnish a return or a revised return, as the case may be, at any time before the expiry of`
  line `one year from the end of the relevant assessment year or before the completion of the assessment,`
  line `whichever is earlier:`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 133, for sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Earlier these sub-sections amended by`
  line `Act 58 of 1960, s. 3 and the Second Schedule (w.e.f. 26-12-1960), Act 46 of 1964, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-4-1964), Act 19 of 1970,`
  line `s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-4-1970).`
  line `2. Sub-section ( 3 ) omitted by s. 133, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 62 (w.e.f. 1-6-2013).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 134, for section 15 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-24
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Page 24`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  sourcePage 24
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line 24
  line `Provided that —`
  line `( a ) where such return or revised return relates to the assessment year commencing on the 1st day`
  line `of April, 1987, or any earlier assessment year, it may be furnished at any time up to and inclusive of`
  line `the 31st day of March, 1990 or before the completion of the assessment, whichever is earlier;`
  line `( b ) where such return or revised return relates to the assessment year commencing on the 1st day`
  line `of April, 1988, it may be furnished at any time up to and inclusive of the 31st day of March, 1991 or`
  line `before the completion of the assessment, whichever is earlier.]`
  line `1 [ 15A. Return by whom to be signed. — The return made under section 14 or section 15 shall be`
  line `signed and verified —`
  line `2 [( a ) in the case of an individual, —`
  line `( i ) by the individual himself;`
  line `( ii ) where he is absent from India, by the individual himself or by some person duly`
  line `authorised by him in this behalf;`
  line `( iii ) where he is mentally incapacitated from attending to his affairs, by his guardian or any`
  line `other person competent to act on his behalf; and`
  line `( iv ) where, for any other reason, it is not possible for the individual to sign the return, by any`
  line `person duly authorised by him in this behalf:`
  line `Provided that in a case referred to in sub-clause ( ii ) or sub-clause ( iv ), the person signing the`
  line `return holds a valid power of attorney from the individual to do so, which shall be attached to the`
  line return;]
  line `( b ) in the case of a Hindu undivided family, by the karta, and, where the karta is absent from`
  line `India or is mentally incapacitated from attending to his affairs, by any other adult member of such`
  line `family; and`
  line `3 [( c ) in the case of a company, by the managing director thereof, or where for any unavoidable`
  line `reason such managing director is not able to sign and verify the return or where there is no managing`
  line `director, by any director thereof:]`
  line `4 [Provided that where the company is not resident in India, the return may be signed and verified`
  line `by a person who holds a valid power of attorney from such company to do so, which shall be attached`
  line `to the return:`
  line `Provided further that, —`
  line `( a ) where the company is being wound up, whether under the orders of the court or`
  line `otherwise, or where any person has been appointed as the receiver of any assets of the company,`
  line `the return shall be signed and verified by the liquidator referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) of section`
  line `178 of the Income-tax Act;`
  line `( b ) where the management of the company has been taken over by the Central Government or`
  line `any State Government under any law, the return of the company shall be signed and verified by`
  line `the principal officer thereof.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 46 of 1964, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 135, for clause ( a ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 88, for clause ( c ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `4. Added by Act 4 of 1988, s. 135 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-25
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Page 25`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  sourcePage 25
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line 25
  line `1 [ 15B. Self-assessment. — ( 1 ) Where any tax is payable on the basis of any return furnished under`
  line `section 14 or section 15 or in response to a notice under clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 4 ) of section 16 or`
  line `under section 17, after taking into account the amount of tax, if any, already paid under any provision of`
  line `this Act, the assessee shall be liable to pay such tax, together with interest payable under any provision of`
  line `this Act, for any delay in furnishing the return, before furnishing the return and the return shall be`
  line `accompanied by proof of payment of such tax and interest.`
  line `Explanation. — Where the amount paid by the assessee under this sub-section falls short of the`
  line `aggregate of the tax and interest as aforesaid, the amount so paid shall first be adjusted towards the`
  line `interest payable as aforesaid and the balance, if any, shall be adjusted towards the tax payable.`
  line `( 2 ) After the regular assessment under section 16 has been made, any amount paid under sub-section`
  line `( 1 ) shall be deemed to have been paid towards such regular assessment.`
  line `( 3 ) If any assessee fails to pay the whole or any part of such tax or interest or both in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ), he shall, without prejudice to any other consequences which he may`
  line `incur, be deemed to be an assessee in default in respect of the tax or interest or both remaining unpaid and`
  line `all the provisions of this Act shall apply accordingly.]`
  line `2 [( 4 ) The provisions of this section as they stood immediately before their amendment by the Direct`
  line `Tax Laws (Amendment) Act, 1987 (4 of 1988), shall apply to and in relation to any assessment for the`
  line `assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1988, or any earlier assessment year and references`
  line `in this section to the other provisions of this Act shall be construed as references to those provisions as for`
  line `the time being in force and applicable to the relevant assessment year.]`
  line `15C. [ Provisional assessment.] — Omitted by the Direct Tax Laws ( Amendment ) Act, 1987, s. 137`
  line `( w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1989). Earlier it was inserted by the Wealth-tax ( Amendment ) Act, 1964, s. 15`
  line `( w.e.f. 1 - 4 - 1965).`
  line `3 [ 16. Assessment. — 4 [ ( 1 ) Where a return has been made under section 14 or section 15 or in response`
  line `to a notice under clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 4 ), —`
  line `( i ) if any tax or interest is found due on the basis of such return, after adjustment of any amount`
  line `paid by way of tax or interest, then, without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section ( 2 ), an`
  line `intimation shall be sent to the assessee specifying the sum so payable, and such intimation shall be`
  line `deemed to be a notice of demand issued under section 30 and all the provisions of this Act shall apply`
  line `accordingly; and`
  line `( ii ) if any refund is due on the basis of such return, it shall be granted to the assessee and an`
  line `intimation to this effect shall be sent to the assessee:`
  line `Provided that except as otherwise provided in this sub-section, the acknowledgement of the return`
  line `shall be deemed to be an intimation under this sub-section where either no sum is payable by the`
  line `assessee or no refund is due to him:`
  line `Provided further that no intimation under this sub-section shall be sent after the expiry of two`
  line `years from the end of the assessment year in which the net wealth was first assessable.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 136, for section 15B (w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Earlier it was inserted by Act 46 of 1964, s. 15`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1965) which was later amended by Act 42 of 1970, s. 60 (w.e.f. 1-4-1971) and Act 41 of 1975, s. 89`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 36 of 1989, s. 27 (w.r.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 138, for section 16 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Earlier section 16 was amended by Act 46 of 1964, s. 16`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 92, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-6-1999). Earlier it was amended by Act 3 of 1989, s. 64`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1989) and Act 36 of 1989, s. 28 (w.r.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-26
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Page 26`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  sourcePage 26
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line 26
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `( 2 ) 2 [Where a return has been made under section 14 or section 15, or in response to a notice under`
  line `clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 4 ) of this section, the Assessing Officer shall, if he] considers it necessary or`
  line `expedient to ensure that the assessee has not understated the net wealth or has not underpaid the tax in any`
  line `manner, 3 [serve on the assessee] a notice requiring him, on a date to be specified therein, either to attend`
  line `at the office of the Assessing Officer or to produce, or cause to be produced there, any evidence on which`
  line `the assessee may rely in support of the return:`
  line `4 [Provided that no notice under this sub-section shall be served on the assessee after the expiry of`
  line `twelve months from the end of the month in which the return is furnished.]`
  line `( 3 ) On the day specified in the notice issued under sub-section ( 2 ) or as soon afterwards as may be,`
  line `after hearing such evidence as the assessee may produce and such other evidence as the Assessing Officer`
  line `may require on specified points, and after taking into account all relevant material which he has gathered,`
  line `the Assessing Officer shall, by order in writing, assess the net wealth of the assessee and determine the`
  line `sum payable by him on the basis of such assessment.`
  line `( 4 ) For the purposes of making an assessment under this Act, the Assessing Officer may serve, on any`
  line `person who has made a return under section 14 or section 15 or in whose case the time allowed under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 14 for furnishing the return has expired, a notice requiring him, on a date to be`
  line `specified therein, —`
  line `( i ) where such person has not made a return 5 [within the time allowed under sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 14] to furnish a return of his net wealth or the net wealth of any other person in respect of`
  line `which he is assessable under this Act on the valuation date, in the prescribed form and verified in the`
  line `prescribed manner, setting forth the particulars of such net wealth and such other particulars as may`
  line `be prescribed, or`
  line `( ii ) to produce or cause to be produced such accounts, records or other documents as the`
  line `Assessing Officer may require.`
  line `( 5 ) If any person, —`
  line `( a ) fails to make the return required under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 14 and has not made a return`
  line `or a revised return under section 15, or`
  line `( b ) fails to comply with all the terms of a notice issued under sub-section ( 2 ) or sub-section ( 4 ),`
  line `the Assessing Officer, after taking into account, all relevant material which he has gathered, shall, after`
  line `giving such person an opportunity of being heard, estimate the net wealth to the best of his judgment and`
  line `determine the sum payable by the person on the basis of such assessment:`
  line `Provided that such opportunity shall be given by the Assessing Officer by serving a notice calling`
  line `upon the person to show cause, on a date and time to be specified in the notice, why the assessment`
  line `should not be completed to the best of his judgment:`
  line `Provided further that it shall not be necessary to give such opportunity in a case where a notice under`
  line `sub-section ( 4 ) has been issued prior to the making of the assessment under this sub-section.]`
  line `1. Sub-section ( 1A ) and ( 1B ) omitted by Act 27 of 1999, s. 92 (w.e.f. 1-6-1999). Earlier sub-section ( 1A ) inserted by Act 3 of`
  line `1989, s. 64 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989) and later amended by Act 36 of 1989, s. 28 (w.r.e.f. 1-4-1989). Sub-section ( 1B ) inserted by Act`
  line `12 of 1990, s. 54 (w.r.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 36 of 1989, s. 28, for “In a case referred to in sub - section (1), if the Assessing Officer” (w. r.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 28, ibid., for “he shall server or the Assessee” (w.r.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 74, for the proviso (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 54, for “before the end of the relevant assessment year” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1990).`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-27
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Page 27`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  sourcePage 27
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line 27
  line `1 [( 6 ) Where a regular assessment under sub-section ( 3 ) or sub-section ( 5 ) is made, —`
  line `( a ) any tax or interest paid by the assessee under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be deemed to have been`
  line `paid towards such regular assessment;`
  line `( b ) if no refund is due on regular assessment or the amount refunded under sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `exceeds the amount refundable on regular assessment, the whole or the excess amount so refunded`
  line `shall be deemed to be tax payable by the assessee and the provisions of this Act shall apply`
  line accordingly.
  line `2 * * * * *]`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `4 [ 16A. Reference to Valuation Officer. — ( 1 ) For the purpose of making an assessment (including an`
  line `assessment in respect of any assessment year commencing before the date of coming into force of this`
  line `section) under this Act, 5 [where under the provisions of section 7 read with the rules made under this Act,`
  line `or, as the case may be, the rules in Schedule III, the market value of any asset is to be taken into account`
  line `in such assessment,] the 6 [Assessing Officer] may refer the valuation of any asset to a Valuation`
  line `Officer —`
  line `( a ) in a case where the value of the asset as returned is in accordance with the estimate made by a`
  line `registered valuer, if the 6 [Assessing Officer] is of opinion that the value so returned is less than its fair`
  line `market value;`
  line `( b ) in any other case, if the 6 [Assessing Officer] is of opinion —`
  line `( i ) that the fair market value of the asset exceeds the value of the asset as returned by more`
  line `than such percentage of the value of the asset as returned or by more than such amount as may be`
  line `prescribed in this behalf; or`
  line `( ii ) that having regard to the nature of the asset and other relevant circumstances, it is`
  line `necessary so to do.`
  line `( 2 ) For the purpose of estimating the value of any asset in pursuance of a reference under sub-section`
  line `( 1 ), the Valuation Officer may serve on the assessee a notice requiring him to produce or cause to be`
  line `produced on a date specified in the notice such accounts, records or other documents as the Valuation`
  line `Officer may require.`
  line `( 3 ) Where the Valuation Officer is of opinion that the value of the asset has been correctly declared in`
  line `the return made by the assessee under section 14 or section 15, he shall pass an order in writing to that`
  line `effect and send a copy of his order to the 6 [Assessing Officer] and to the assessee.`
  line `( 4 ) Where the Valuation Officer is of opinion that the value of the asset is higher than the value`
  line `declared in the return made by the assessee under section 14 or, section 15, or where the asset is not`
  line `disclosed or the value of the asset is not declared in such return or where no such return has been made,`
  line `the Valuation Officer shall serve a notice on the assessee intimating the value which he proposes to`
  line `estimate and giving the assessee an opportunity to state, on a date to be specified in the notice, his`
  line `objections either in person or in writing before the Valuation Officer and to produce or cause to be`
  line `produced on that date such evidence as the assessee may rely in support of his objections.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 36 of 1989, s. 28 (w.r.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Sub-section ( 7 ) omitted by Act 27 of 1999, s. 92 (w.e.f. 1-6-1999). Earlier it was inserted by Act 36 of 1989, s. 28`
  line `(w.r.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. The Explanation omitted by s. 92, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-1999). Earlier it was inserted by Act 49 of 1991, s. 74 (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 45 of 1972, s. 10 (w.e.f. 1-1-1973).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 65 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
