  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  sourcePage 28
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line 28
  line `( 5 ) On the date specified in the notice under sub-section ( 4 ), or as soon thereafter as may be, after`
  line `hearing such evidence as the assessee may produce and after considering such evidence as the Valuation`
  line `Officer may require on any specified points and after taking into account all relevant material which he`
  line `has gathered, the Valuation Officer shall, by order in writing, estimate the value of the asset and send a`
  line `copy of his order to the 1 [Assessing Officer] and to the assessee.`
  line `( 6 ) On receipt of the order under sub-section ( 3 ) or sub-section ( 5 ) from the Valuation Officer,`
  line `the 1 [Assessing Officer] shall, so far as the valuation of the asset in question is concerned, proceed to`
  line `complete the assessment in conformity with the estimate of the Valuation Officer.]`
  line `17. Wealth escaping assessment. — 2 [( 1 ) If the Assessing Officer 3 [has reason to believe] that the net`
  line `wealth chargeable to tax in respect of which any person is assessable under this Act has escaped`
  line `assessment for any assessment year (whether by reason of under- assessment or assessment at too low a`
  line `rate or otherwise), he may, subject to the other provisions of this section and section 17A, serve on such`
  line `person a notice requiring him to furnish within such period, 4 *** as may be specified in the notice, a`
  line `return in the prescribed form and verified in the prescribed manner setting forth the net wealth in respect`
  line `of which such person is assessable as on the valuation date mentioned in the notice, along with such other`
  line `particulars as may be required by the notice, and may proceed to assess or reassess such net wealth and`
  line `also any other net wealth chargeable to tax in respect of which such person is assessable, which has`
  line `escaped assessment and which comes to his notice subsequently in the course of the proceedings under`
  line `this section for the assessment year concerned (hereafter in this section referred to as the relevant`
  line `assessment year), and the provisions of this Act shall, so far as may be, apply as if the return were a return`
  line `required to be furnished under section 14:`
  line `Provided that where an assessment under sub-section ( 3 ) of section 16 or this section has been made`
  line `for the relevant assessment year, no action shall be taken under this section after the expiry of four years`
  line `from the end of the relevant assessment year, unless any net wealth chargeable to tax has escaped`
  line `assessment for such assessment year by reason of the failure on the part of the assessee to make a return`
  line `under section 14 or section 15 or in response to a notice issued under sub-section ( 4 ) of section 16 or this`
  line `section or to disclose fully and truly all material facts necessary for his assessment for that assessment`
  line `year:`
  line `5 [Provided further that the Assessing Officer shall, before issuing any notice under this sub-section,`
  line `record his reasons for doing so:]`
  line `6 [Provided also that nothing contained in the first proviso shall apply in a case where any net wealth`
  line `in relation to any asset (including financial interest in any entity) located outside India chargeable to tax,`
  line `has escaped assessment for any assessment year:]`
  line `7 [Provided also that the Assessing Officer may assess or reassess such net wealth, other than the net`
  line `wealth which is the subject matter of any appeal, reference or revision, which is chargeable to tax and has`
  line `escaped assessment.]`
  line `Explanation. — Production before the Assessing Officer of account books or other evidence from`
  line `which material evidence could with due diligence have been discovered by the Assessing Officer will not`
  line `necessarily amount to disclosure within the meaning of the foregoing proviso.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 139, ibid., for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Earlier it was amended by Act 46 of 1964, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 66, for “, for reasons to be recorded by him in writing, is of the opinion” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `4. The words “not being less than thirty days,” omitted by Act 32 of 2003, s. 100 (w.r.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 66 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 116 (w.r.e.f. 1-7-2012).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 60 (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
