obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line 30
  line `1 [( 2 ) Nothing contained in this section limiting the time within which any proceeding for assessment`
  line `or reassessment may be commenced, shall apply to an assessment or reassessment to be made on such`
  line `person in consequence of or to give effect to any finding or direction contained in an order under`
  line `section 23, 24, 25, 27 or 29 2 [or by a Court in any proceedings under any other law]:`
  line `Provided that the provisions of this sub-section shall not apply in any case where any such assessment`
  line `or reassessment relates to an assessment year in respect of which an assessment or reassessment could not`
  line `have been made at the time the order which was the subject-matter of the appeal, reference or revision, as`
  line `the case may be, was made by reason of any provision limiting the time within which any action for`
  line `assessment or reassessment may be taken.]`
  line `3 [ 17A. Time limit for completion of assessment and reassessment. — 4 [( 1 ) No order of assessment`
  line `shall be made under section 16 at any time after the expiry of two years from the end of the assessment`
  line `year in which the net wealth was first assessable:`
  line `5 [Provided that, —`
  line `( a ) where the net wealth was first assessable in the assessment year commencing on the 1st day of`
  line `April, 1987, or any earlier assessment year, such assessment may be made on or before the 31st day`
  line `of March, 1991;`
  line `( b ) where the net wealth was first assessable in the assessment year commencing on the 1st day of`
  line `April, 1988, such assessment may be made on or before the 31st day of March, 1992:]`
  line `6 [Provided further that in case the assessment year in which the net wealth was first assessable is`
  line `the assessment year 7 [commencing on or after the 1st day of April, 2004 but before the 1st day of`
  line `April, 2010], the provisions of this sub-section shall have effect as if for the words “ two years ”, the`
  line `words “ twenty-one months ” had been substituted.]`
  line `( 2 ) No order of assessment or reassessment shall be made under section 17 after the expiry of 8 [one`
  line `year] from the end of the financial year in which the notice under sub-section ( 1 ) of that section was`
  line `served]:`
  line `9 [Provided that where the notice under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 17 was served on or after the 1st day`
  line `of April, 1999 but before the 1st day of April, 2000, such assessment or reassessment may be made at any`
  line `time up to the 31st day of March, 2002:]`
  line `6 [Provided further that where the notice under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 17 was served on or 10 [after`
  line `the 1st day of April, 2005 but before the 1st day of April, 2011], the provisions of this sub-section shall`
  line `have effect as if for the words "one year", the words "nine months" had been substituted.]`
  line `11 * * * * *]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 46 of 1964, s. 17 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `2. Added by Act 4 of 1988, s. 139 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 90 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 140, for sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 13 of 1989, s. 28, for the proviso (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 57 (w.e.f. 1-6-2006).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 117, for “commencing on the 1st day of April, 2004 or any subsequent year” (w.e.f. 1 -7-2012)`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 97, for “two years” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2001).`
  line `9. Subs. by s. 97, ibid., for the proviso (w.e.f. 1-6-2001).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 117, for “after the 1st day of April, 2005” (w.e.f. 1 -7-2012).`
  line `11. The Explanation omitted by Act 14 of 2001, s. 97 (w.e.f. 1-6-2001).`
