obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line 31
  line `( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ), an order of fresh assessment in`
  line `pursuance of an order passed on or after the 1st day of April, 1975, under section 1 [23A], section 24 or`
  line `section 25, setting aside or cancelling an assessment, may be made at any time before the expiry of 2 [one`
  line `year] from the end of the financial year in which the order under section 1 [23A] or section 24 is received`
  line `by the 3 [Chief Commissioner or Commissioner] or, as the case may be, the order under section 25 is`
  line `passed by the Commissioner:`
  line `4 [Provided that where the order under section 23A or section 24 is received by the Chief`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner or, as the case may be, the order under section 25 is passed by the`
  line `Commissioner, on or after the 1st day of April, 1999 but before the 1st day of April, 2000, such an order`
  line `of fresh assessment may be made at any time up to the 31st day of March, 2002:]`
  line `5 [Provided further that where the order under section 23A or section 24 is received by the Chief`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner or, as the case may be, the order under section 25 is passed by the`
  line `Commissioner, on or 6 [after the 1st day of April, 2005 but before the 1st day of April, 2011], the`
  line `provisions of this sub-section shall have effect as if for the words "one year", the words "nine months"`
  line `had been substituted.]`
  line `( 4 ) The provisions of sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ) shall not apply to the assessment or reassessment made`
  line `on the assessee or any other person in consequence of, or to give effect to, any finding or direction`
  line `contained in an order under section 23, section 24, section 25, section 27 or section 29 or in an order of`
  line `any court in a proceeding otherwise than by way of appeal or reference under this Act, and such`
  line `assessment or reassessment may, subject to the provisions of sub-section ( 3 ), be completed at any time.`
  line `Explanation 1. — In computing the period of limitation for the purposes of this section —`
  line `( i ) the time taken in reopening the whole or any part of the proceeding or in giving an opportunity`
  line `to the assessee to be reheard under the proviso to section 39, or`
  line `( ii ) the period during which the assessment proceeding is stayed by an order or injunction of any`
  line `court, or`
  line `7 [( iia ) the period (not exceeding sixty days) commencing from the date on which the 8 [Assessing`
  line `Officer] received the declaration under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 18C and ending with the date on`
  line `which the order under sub-section ( 3 ) of that section is made by him, or]`
  line `( iii ) in a case where an application made before the Wealth-tax Settlement Commission under`
  line `section 22C is rejected by it or is not allowed to be proceeded with by it, the period commencing from`
  line `the date on which such application is made and ending with the date on which the order under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 22D is received by the Commissioner under sub-section ( 2 ) of that section,`
  line `shall be excluded:`
  line `9 [Provided that where immediately after the exclusion of the aforesaid time or period, the period of`
  line `limitation referred to in sub-sections ( 1 ), ( 2 ) and ( 3 ) available to the Assessing Officer for making an`
  line `order of assessment or reassessment, as the case may be, is less than sixty days, such remaining period`
  line `shall be extended to sixty days and the aforesaid period of limitation shall be deemed to be extended`
  line `accordingly:]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 14 of 20 01, s. 97, for “23” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2001).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 97, ibid., for “two years” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2001). Earlier the quoted words were substituted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 140, for`
  line `“four years” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 14 of 2001, s. 97, for the proviso (w.e.f. 1-6-2001). Earlier the proviso was inserted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 140`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 21 of 2006, s. 57 (w.e.f. 1-6-2006).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 117, f or “after the 1st day of April, 2005” (w.e.f. 1 -7-2012).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 56 (w.e.f. 1-10-1984).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 75 (w.e.f. 27-9-1991).`
