  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  sourcePage 32
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line 32
  line `1 [Provided further that where a proceeding before the Settlement Commission abates under`
  line `section 22HA, the period of limitation referred to in this section available to the Assessing Officer for`
  line `making an order of assessment or reassessment, as the case may be, shall, after the exclusion of the period`
  line `under sub-section ( 4 ) of section 22HA, be not less than one year; and where such period of limitation is`
  line `less than one year, it shall be deemed to have been extended to one year.]`
  line `Explanation 2. — Where, by an order referred to in sub-section ( 4 ), any asset is excluded from the net`
  line `wealth of one person and held to be the asset of another person, then, an assessment in respect of such`
  line `asset on such other person shall, for the purposes of sub-section ( 2 ) of section 17 and this section, be`
  line `deemed to be one made in consequence of, or to give effect to, any finding or direction contained in the`
  line `said order, provided such other person was given an opportunity of being heard before the said order was`
  line passed.]
  line `2 [ 17B. Interest for defaults in furnishing return of net wealth. — ( 1 ) Where the return of net`
  line `wealth for any assessment year under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 14 or section 15, or in response to a`
  line `notice under clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 4 ) of section 16, is furnished after the due date, or is not furnished,`
  line `the assessee shall be liable to pay simple interest at the rate of 3 [one per cent.] for every month or part of a`
  line `month comprised in the period commencing on the date immediately following the due date, and, —`
  line `( a ) where the return is furnished after the due date, ending on the date of furnishing of the return,`
  line or
  line `( b ) where no return has been furnished, ending on the date of completion of the assessment under`
  line `sub-section ( 5 ) of section 16,`
  line `on the amount of tax payable on the net wealth as determined 4 [under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 16 or] on`
  line `regular assessment.`
  line `Explanation 1. — In this section, “ due date ” means the date specified in sub-section ( 1 ) of section 14`
  line `as applicable in the case of the assessee.`
  line `5 [ Explanation 2. — In this sub-section, “ tax payable on the net wealth as determined under sub-section`
  line `( 1 ) of section 16 ” shall not include the additional wealth-tax, if any, payable under section 16.]`
  line `Explanation 3. — Where, in relation to an assessment year, an assessment is made for the first time`
  line `under section 17, the assessment so made shall be regarded as a regular assessment for the purposes of`
  line `this section.`
  line `4 [ Explanation 4. — In this sub-section, “ tax payable on the net wealth as determined under sub-section`
  line `( 1 ) of section 16 or on regular assessment ” shall, for the purposes of computing the interest payable under`
  line `section 15B, be deemed to be tax payable on the net wealth as declared in the return.]`
  line `( 2 ) The interest payable under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be reduced by the interest, if any, paid under`
  line `section 15B towards the interest chargeable under this section.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 61 (w.r.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 141 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 54 of 2003, s. 19, for “one and one - fourth per cent.” (w.e.f. 8 -9-2003). Earlier the quoted words were substituted`
  line `by Act 14 of 2001, s. 98, for “two per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2001).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 67 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 67, ibid., for the Explanation (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-33
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Page 33`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  sourcePage 33
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line 33
  line `( 3 ) Where the return of net wealth for any assessment year, required by a notice under sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `of section 17, issued 1 [after the determination of net wealth under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 16 or] after`
  line `the completion of an assessment under sub-section ( 3 ) or sub-section ( 5 ) of section 16 or section 17, is`
  line `furnished after the expiry of the time allowed under such notice, or is not furnished, the assessee shall be`
  line `liable to pay simple interest at the rate of 2 [one per cent.] for every month or part of a month comprised in`
  line `the period commencing on the day immediately following the expiry of the time allowed as aforesaid,`
  line `and, —`
  line `( a ) where the return is furnished after the expiry of the time aforesaid, ending on the date of`
  line `furnishing the return; or`
  line `( b ) where no return has been furnished, ending on the date of completion of the reassessment`
  line `under section 17,`
  line `on the amount by which the tax on the net wealth determined on the basis of such reassessment exceeds`
  line `the tax on the net wealth as determined 1 [under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 16 or] on the basis of the earlier`
  line `assessment aforesaid.`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `( 4 ) Where, as a result of an order under section 23 or section 24 or section 25 or section 27 or`
  line `section 29 or section 35 or any order of the Wealth-tax Settlement Commission under sub-section ( 4 ) of`
  line `section 22D, the amount of tax on which interest was payable under this section has been increased or`
  line `reduced, as the case may be, the interest shall be increased or reduced accordingly, and, —`
  line `( i ) in a case where the interest is increased, the Assessing Officer shall serve on the assessee a`
  line `notice of demand in the prescribed form specifying the sum payable, and such notice of demand shall`
  line `be deemed to be a notice under section 30 and the provisions of this Act shall apply accordingly, and`
  line `( ii ) in a case where the interest is reduced, the excess interest paid, if any, shall be refunded.`
  line `( 5 ) The provisions of this section shall apply in respect of assessments, for the assessment year`
  line `commencing on the 1st day of April, 1989 and subsequent assessment years.]`
  line `4 [ 18. Penalty for failure to furnish returns, to comply with notices and concealment of`
  line `assets, etc. — ( 1 ) If the 5 [Assessing Officer], 6 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)], 7 [Commissioner`
  line `(Appeals),] 8 [Chief Commissioner or Commissioner] or Appellate Tribunal in the course of any`
  line `proceedings under this Act is satisfied that any person —`
  line `9 * * * * *`
  line `( b ) has 10 *** failed to comply with a notice under sub-section ( 2 ) or sub-section ( 4 ) of`
  line `section 16; or`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 67 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 54 of 2003, s. 19, for “one and one -fourt h per cent.” (w.e.f. 8 -9-2003). Earlier the quoted words were substituted`
  line `by Act 14 of 2001, s. 98, for “two per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2001).`
  line `3. The Explanation omitted by Act 3 of 1989, s. 67 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `4. Restored by s. 95, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Earlier subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 142 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989) and also substituted by Act`
  line `46 of 1964, s. 18 (w.e.f. -1-4-1965).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 127, ibid., for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `9. Clause ( a ) omitted by Act 3 of 1989, s. 68 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Earlier it was amended by Act 46 of 1986, s. 33`
  line `(w.e.f. 10-9-1986).`
  line `10. The words “without reasonable cause” omitted by Act 46 of 1986, s. 33 (w.e.f. 10 -9-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
