  title `Page 34`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  sourcePage 34
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line 34
  line `( c ) has concealed the particulars of any assets or furnished inaccurate particulars of any assets or`
  line debts,
  line `he or it may, by order in writing, direct that such person shall pay by way of penalty —`
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `2 [( ii ) in the cases referred to in clause ( b ), in addition to the amount of wealth-tax payable by him, a`
  line `sum which shall not be less than one thousand rupees but which may extend to twenty-five thousand`
  line `rupees for each such failure;]`
  line `3 [( iii ) in the cases referred to in clause ( c ), in addition to any wealth-tax payable by him, a sum which`
  line `shall not be less than, but which shall not exceed five times, the amount of tax sought to be evaded by`
  line `reason of the concealment of particulars of any assets or the furnishing of inaccurate particulars in respect`
  line `of any assets or debts:`
  line `4 [Provided that in the cases referred to in clause ( b ), no penalty shall be imposable if the person`
  line `proves that there was a reasonable cause for the failure referred to in that clause.]`
  line `Explanation 1. — For the purposes of clause ( iii ) of this sub-section, the expression “ the amount of tax`
  line `sought to be evaded ”—`
  line `( a ) in a case to which Explanation 3 applies, means the tax on the net wealth assessed;`
  line `( b ) in any other case, means the difference between the tax on the net wealth assessed and the tax`
  line `that would have been chargeable had the net wealth assessed been reduced by the amount which`
  line `represents the value of any assets in respect of which particulars have been concealed or inaccurate`
  line `particulars have been furnished and of any debts in respect of which inaccurate particulars have been`
  line furnished.
  line `Explanation 2. — Where in respect of any facts material to the computation of the net wealth of any`
  line `person under this Act, —`
  line `( A ) such person fails to offer an explanation or offers an explanation which is found by`
  line `the 5 [Assessing Officer] or the 6 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] 7 [or the Commissioner`
  line `(Appeals)] 8 [or the Commissioner] to be false, or`
  line `( B ) such person offers an explanation which he is 9 [not able to substantiate and fails to prove that`
  line `such explanation is bona fide and that all the facts relating to the same and material to the`
  line `computation of his net wealth have been disclosed by him,]`
  line `then, the amount added or disallowed in computing the net wealth of such person as a result thereof shall,`
  line `for the purposes of clause ( c ) of this sub-section, be deemed to represent the value of the assets in respect`
  line `of which particulars have been concealed.`
  line `1. Clause ( i ) omitted by Act 3 of 1989, s. 68 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Earlier it was substituted by Act 41 of 1975, s. 91`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 68, ibid., for clause ( ii ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Earlier it was substituted by Act 41 of 1975, s. 91 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 91, for clause ( iii ) and the Explanations (w.e.f. 1-4-1975). Earlier clause ( iii ) and the Explanations`
  line `were substituted by Act 19 of 1968, s. 32 (w.e.f. 1-4-1968).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 68, for the proviso (w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Earlier it was inserted by Act 46 of 1986, s. 33`
  line `(w.e.f. 10-9-1986).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 127, ibid., for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 110 (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 46 of 1986, s. 33, for “not able to substantiate” (w.e.f. 10 -9-1986).`
