  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  sourcePage 35
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line 35
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `2 [ Explanation 3. — Where any person 3 *** fails, without reasonable cause, to furnish within the period`
  line `specified in sub-section ( 1 ) of section 17A, a return of his net wealth which he is required to furnish under`
  line `section 14 in respect of any assessment year commencing on or after the 1st day of April, 1989, and until`
  line `the expiry of the period aforesaid, no notice has been issued to him under clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 4 ) of`
  line `section 16 or sub-section ( 1 ) of section 17 and the Assessing Officer or the Deputy Commissioner`
  line `(Appeals) or the Commissioner (Appeals) is satisfied that in respect of such assessment year such person`
  line `has assessable net wealth, then, such person shall, for the purposes of clause ( c ) of this sub-section, be`
  line `deemed to have concealed the particulars of his assets or furnished inaccurate particulars of any assets or`
  line `debts in respect of such assessment year, notwithstanding that such person furnishes a return of his net`
  line `wealth at any time after the expiry of either of the periods aforesaid applicable to him in pursuance of a`
  line `notice under section 17.]`
  line `Explanation 4. — Where the value of any asset returned by any person is less than seventy per cent. of`
  line `the value of such asset as determined in an assessment under section 16 or section 17, such person shall`
  line `be deemed to have furnished inaccurate particulars of such asset within the meaning of clause ( c ) of this`
  line `sub-section, unless he proves that the value of the asset as returned by him is the correct value.]`
  line `4 [ Explanation 5. — Where in the course of a search under section 37A, the assessee is found to be the`
  line `owner of any money, bullion, jewellery or other valuable article or thing (hereafter in`
  line `this Explanation referred to as assets) and the assessee claims that such assets represent or form part of`
  line `his net wealth, —`
  line `( a ) on any valuation date falling before the date of the search, but the return in respect of the net`
  line `wealth on such date has not been furnished before the date of the search or, where such return has`
  line `been furnished before the said date, such assets have not been declared in such return; or`
  line `( b ) on any valuation date falling on or after the date of the search,`
  line `then, notwithstanding that such assets are declared by him in any return of net wealth furnished on or after`
  line `the date of the search, he shall, for the purposes of imposition of a penalty under clause ( c ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of this section, be deemed to have concealed the particulars of such assets or furnished`
  line `inaccurate particulars of such assets, 5 [unless —`
  line `( 1 ) such assets are recorded, —`
  line `( i ) in a case falling under clause ( a ), before the date of the search; and`
  line `( ii ) in a case falling under clause ( b ), on or before such date,`
  line `in the books of account, if any, maintained by him or such assets are otherwise disclosed to the 6 [Chief`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner] before the said date; or`
  line `( 2 ) he, in the course of the search, makes a statement under sub-section ( 4 ) of section 37A that any`
  line `money, bullion, jewellery or other valuable article or thing found in his possession or under his control,`
  line `forms part of his net wealth which has not been disclosed so far in his return of net wealth to be furnished`
  line `before the expiry of the time specified in sub-section ( 1 ) of section 14, and also specifies in the statement`
  line `the manner in which such net wealth has been acquired and pays the tax, together with interest, if any, in`
  line `respect of such net wealth].]`
  line `1. The proviso omitted by Act 46 of 1986, s. 33 (w.e.f. 10-9-1986).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 68, for Explanation 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. The words “who has not previously been assessed under this Act” omitted by Act 20 of 2002, s. 110 (w.e.f. 1 -4-2003).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 57 (w.e.f. 1-10-1984).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 46 of 1986, s. 33, for certain words (w.e.f. 10-9-1986).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
