  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  sourcePage 36
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line 36
  line `1 [ Explanation 6. — Where any adjustment is made in the wealth declared in the return under the`
  line `proviso to clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 16 and additional wealth-tax charged under that section,`
  line `the provisions of this sub-section shall not apply in relation to the adjustments so made.]`
  line `2 [( 1A ) Where any amount is added or disallowed in computing the net wealth of an assessee in any`
  line `order of assessment or reassessment and the said order contains a direction for initiation of penalty`
  line `proceedings under clause ( c ) of sub-section ( 1 ), such an order of assessment or reassessment shall be`
  line `deemed to constitute satisfaction of the Assessing Officer for initiation of the penalty proceedings under`
  line `the said clause ( c ).]`
  line `( 2 ) No order shall be made under sub-section ( 1 ) unless the person concerned has been given a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `4 [( 3 ) No order imposing a penalty under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be made, —`
  line `( i ) by the Income-tax Officer, where the penalty exceeds ten thousand rupees;`
  line `( ii ) by the 5 [Assistant Commissioner or Deputy Commissioner], where the penalty exceeds`
  line `twenty thousand rupees,`
  line `except with the prior approval of the 6 [Joint Commissioner].]`
  line `7 * * * * *`
  line `( 4 ) A 8 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)], 9 [a Commissioner (Appeals),] a 10 [Chief Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner] or the Appellate Tribunal on making an order under this section imposing a penalty, shall`
  line `forthwith send a copy of the same to the 11 [Assessing Officer.]`
  line `12 [( 5 ) No order imposing a penalty under this section shall be passed —`
  line `( i ) in a case where the assessment to which the proceedings for imposition of penalty relate is the`
  line `subject-matter of an appeal to the Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) or the Commissioner (Appeals)`
  line `under section 23 or an appeal to the Appellate Tribunal under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 24, after the`
  line `expiry of the financial year in which the proceedings, in the course of which action for the imposition`
  line `of penalty has been initiated, are completed, or six months from the end of the month in which the`
  line `order of the Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) or the Commissioner (Appeals) or, as the case may be,`
  line `the Appellate Tribunal is received by the Chief Commissioner or Commissioner, whichever is later;`
  line `( ii ) in a case where the relevant assessment is the subject-matter of revision under sub-section ( 2 )`
  line `of section 25, after the expiry of six months from the end of the month in which such order of`
  line `revision is passed;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 68 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 62 (w.r.e.f. 1-4-1989). Earlier sub-section ( 1 ) was inserted by Act 32 of 1971, s. 33 (w.e.f. 1-4-1972)`
  line `which was later omitted by Act 41 of 1975, s. 91 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `3. Sub-sections ( 2A ) and ( 2B ) omitted by Act 41 of 1975, s. 91 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976). Earlier these sub-sections were inserted by`
  line `Act 15 of 1965, s. 20 (w.e.f. 11-9-1965).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 68, for sub-section ( 3 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 66, for “Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 66, ibid. for “Deputy Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `7. Sub-section ( 3A ) omitted by Act 3 of 1989, s. 68 (w.e.f. 1-4-989).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `11. Subs. by s. 127, ibid., for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `12. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 68, for sub-section ( 5 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
