  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  sourcePage 37
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line 37
  line `( iii ) in any other case, after the expiry of the financial year in which the proceedings, in the course`
  line `of which action for the imposition of penalty has been initiated, are completed, or six months from`
  line `the end of the month in which action for imposition of penalty is initiated, whichever period expires`
  line later.
  line `Explanation. — In computing the period of limitation for the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( i ) any period during which the immunity granted under section 22H remained in force;`
  line `( ii ) the time taken in giving an opportunity to the assessee to be reheard under the proviso to`
  line `section 39; and`
  line `( iii ) any period during which a proceeding under this section for the levy of penalty is stayed by`
  line `an order or injunction of any court,`
  line `shall be excluded.`
  line `( 6 ) The provisions of this section as they stood immediately before their amendment by the Direct`
  line `Tax Laws (Amendment) Act, 1989 (3 of 1989) shall apply to and in relation to any assessment for the`
  line `assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1988, or any earlier assessment year and references`
  line `in this section to the other provisions of this Act shall be construed as references to those provisions as for`
  line `the time being in force and applicable to the relevant assessment year.]`
  line `1 [ 18A. Penalty for failure to answer questions, sign statements, furnish information, allow`
  line `inspection, etc. — ( 1 ) If any person, —`
  line `( a ) being legally bound to state the truth of any matter touching the subject of his assessment,`
  line `refuses to answer any question put to him by a wealth-tax authority in the exercise of his powers`
  line `under this Act; or`
  line `( b ) refuses to sign any statement made by him in the course of any proceedings under this Act,`
  line `which a wealth-tax authority may legally require him to sign; or`
  line `( c ) to whom a summons is issued under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 37 either to attend to give`
  line `evidence or produce books of account or other documents at a certain place and time, omits to attend`
  line `or produce the books of account or documents at the place and time,`
  line `he shall pay, by way of penalty, a sum which shall not be less than five hundred rupees but which may`
  line `extend to ten thousand rupees for each such default or failure:`
  line `Provided that no penalty shall be imposable under clause ( c ) if the person proves that there was`
  line `reasonable cause for the said failure.`
  line `( 2 ) If a person fails to furnish in due time any statement or information which such person is bound to`
  line `furnish to the Assessing Officer under section 38, he shall pay, by way of penalty, a sum which shall not`
  line `be less than one hundred rupees but which may extend to two hundred rupees for every day during which`
  line `the failure continues:`
  line `Provided that no penalty shall be imposable under this sub-section if the person proves that there was`
  line `reasonable cause for the said failure.`
  line `1. Restored by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Substituted by Act 3 of 1989, s. 69, for section 18A (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `Earlier section 18A was amended by 46 of 1986, s. 34 (w.e.f. 10-9-1986) and Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 10-7-1978) which was inserted by Act 41 of 1975, s. 92 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-38
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Page 38`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  sourcePage 38
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line 38
  line `( 3 ) Any penalty imposable under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ) shall be imposed —`
  line `( a ) in a case where the contravention, failure or default in respect of which such penalty is`
  line `imposable occurs in the course of any proceeding before a wealth-tax authority not lower in rank than`
  line `a 1 [Joint Director] or a 2 [Joint Commissioner], by such wealth-tax authority;`
  line `( b ) in any other case, by the 1 [Joint Director] or the 2 [Joint Commissioner].`
  line `( 4 ) No order under this section shall be passed by any wealth-tax authority referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 3 ) unless the person on whom the penalty is proposed to be imposed has been heard, or has`
  line `been given a reasonable opportunity of being heard in the matter, by such authority.`
  line `Explanation. — In this section, “ wealth-tax authority ” includes a Director General, Director, 1 [Joint`
  line `Director], 3 [Assistant Director or Deputy Director] and a Valuation Officer while exercising the powers`
  line `vested in a court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), when trying a suit in respect of the`
  line `matters specified in sub-section ( 1 ) of section 37.]`
  line `4 [ 18B. Power to reduce or waive penalty in certain cases. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in this Act, the 5 [ 6 *** Commissioner] may, in his discretion, whether on his own motion or`
  line `otherwise, —`
  line `7 * * * * *`
  line `( ii ) reduce or waive the amount of penalty imposed or imposable on a person under clause ( iii ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 18,`
  line `if he is satisfied that such person, —`
  line `8 * * * * *`
  line `( b ) in the case referred to in clause ( ii ), has, prior to the detection by the 9 [Assessing Officer], of`
  line `the concealment of particulars of assets or of the inaccuracy of particulars furnished in respect of any`
  line `asset or debt in respect of which the penalty is imposable, voluntarily and in good faith made full and`
  line `true disclosure of such particulars,`
  line `and also has co-operated in any inquiry relating to the assessment of his net wealth and has either paid or`
  line `made satisfactory arrangements for the payment of any tax or interest payable in consequence of an order`
  line `passed under this Act in respect of the relevant assessment year.`
  line `Explanation 10 ***. — For the purposes of this sub-section, a person shall be deemed to have made full`
  line `and true disclosure of the particulars of his assets or debts in any case where the excess of net wealth`
  line `assessed over the net wealth returned is of such a nature as not to attract the provisions of clause ( c ) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 18.`
  line `11 * * * * *`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 66, for “Deputy Director” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 66, ibid. for “Deputy Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 66, ibid. for “Assistant Director” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 92 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `6. The words “Chief Commissioner or” omitted by Act 38 of 1993, s. 40 (w.e.f. 1 -6-1993).`
  line `7. Clause ( i ) omitted by Act 3 of 1989, s. 70 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `8. Clause ( a ) omitted by s. 70, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `10. The figure “1” omitted by Act 32 of 1985, s. 38 (w.e.f. 24 -5-1985). Earlier the Explanation renumbered as Explanation 1`
  line `thereof by Act 67 of 1984, s. 58 (w.e.f. 1-10-1984).`
  line `11. Explanation 2 omitted by s. 38, ibid. (w.e.f. 24-5-1985). Earlier it was inserted by Act 67 of 1984, s. 58 (w.e.f. 1-10-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-39
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Page 39`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  sourcePage 39
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line 39
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), if in a case falling under clause ( c ) of`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) of section 18, the net wealth in respect of which the penalty is imposed or imposable for`
  line `the relevant assessment year, or, where such disclosure relates to more than one assessment year, the net`
  line `wealth for any one of the relevant assessment years, exceeds five hundred thousand rupees, no order`
  line `reducing or waiving the penalty under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be made by 1 [the Commissioner except with`
  line `the previous approval of the Chief Commissioner or Director General, as the case may be].`
  line `( 3 ) Where an order has been made under sub-section ( 1 ) in favour of any person, whether such order`
  line `relates to one or more assessment years, he shall not be entitled to any relief under this section in relation`
  line `to any other assessment year at any time after the making of such order:`
  line `2 [Provided that where an order has been made in favour of any person under sub-section ( 1 ) on or`
  line `before the 24th day of July, 1991, such person shall be entitled to further relief only once in relation to`
  line `other assessment year or years if he makes an application to the wealth-tax authority referred to in`
  line `sub-section (4) at any time before the 1st day of April, 1992.]`
  line `( 4 ) Without prejudice to the powers conferred on him by any other provision of this Act, the 3 [ 4 ***`
  line `Commissioner] may, on an application made in this behalf by an assessee, and after recording his reasons`
  line `for so doing, reduce or waive the amount of any penalty payable by the assessee under this Act or stay or`
  line `compound any proceeding for the recovery of any such amount, if he is satisfied that —`
  line `( i ) to do otherwise would cause genuine hardship to the assessee, having regard to the`
  line `circumstances of the case, and`
  line `( ii ) the assessee has co-operated in any inquiry relating to the assessment or any proceeding for`
  line `the recovery of any amount due from him.`
  line `( 5 ) Every order made under this section shall be final and shall not be called into question by any`
  line `court or any other authority.]`
  line `5 [( 6 ) The provisions of this section as they stood immediately before their amendment by the Direct`
  line `Tax Laws (Amendment) Act, 1989 (3 of 1989), shall apply to and in relation to any assessment for the`
  line `assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1988, or any earlier assessment year, and references`
  line `in this section to the other provisions of this Act shall be construed as references to those provisions as for`
  line `the time being in force and applicable to the relevant assessment year.]`
  line `6 [ 18BA. Power of Commissioner to grant immunity from penalty. — ( 1 ) A person may make an`
  line `application to the Commissioner for granting immunity from penalty, if —`
  line `( a ) he has made an application for settlement under section 22C and the proceedings for`
  line `settlement have abated under section 22HA; and`
  line `( b ) the penalty proceedings have been initiated under this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) The application to the Commissioner under sub-section ( 1 ) shall not be made after the imposition`
  line `of penalty after abatement.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 1993, s. 40, for “the Chief Commissioner or Commissioner, except with the previous approval of the`
  line `Board” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1993).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 76 (w.e.f. 27-9-1991).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. T he words “Chief Commissioner or” omitted by Act 38 of 1993, s. 40 (w.e.f. 1 -6-1993).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 70 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 63 (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
