  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  sourcePage 40
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line 40
  line `( 3 ) The Commissioner may, subject to such conditions as he may think fit to impose, grant to the`
  line `person immunity from the imposition of any penalty under this Act, if he is satisfied that the person has,`
  line `after the abatement, co-operated with the wealth-tax authority in the proceedings before him and has`
  line `made a full and true disclosure of his net wealth and the manner in which such net wealth has been`
  line derived.
  line `( 4 ) The immunity granted to a person under sub-section ( 3 ) shall stand withdrawn, if such person fails`
  line `to comply with any condition subject to which the immunity was granted and thereupon the provisions of`
  line `this Act shall apply as if such immunity had not been granted.`
  line `( 5 ) The immunity granted to a person under sub-section ( 3 ) may, at any time, be withdrawn by the`
  line `Commissioner, if he is satisfied that such person had, in the course of any proceedings, after abatement,`
  line `concealed any particulars, material to the assessment, from the wealth-tax authority or had given false`
  line `evidence, and thereupon such person shall become liable to the imposition of any penalty under this Act`
  line `to which such person would have been liable, had not such immunity been granted.]`
  line `1 [CHAPTER IVA`
  line `S PECIAL PROVISION FOR AVOIDING REPETITIVE APPEALS`
  line `18C. Procedure when assessee claims identical question of law is pending before High Court or`
  line `Supreme Court. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, where an assessee claims that any`
  line `question of law arising in his case for an assessment year which is pending before the 2 [Assessing`
  line `Officer] or any appellate authority (such case being hereafter in this section referred to as the relevant`
  line `case) is identical with a question of law arising in his case for another assessment year which is pending`
  line `before the High Court or the Supreme Court on a reference under section 27 3 [or in appeal under section`
  line `27A before the High Court] or in appeal before the Supreme Court under section 29 (such case being`
  line `hereafter in this section referred to as the other case), he may furnish to the 2 [Assessing Officer] or the`
  line `appellate authority, as the case may be, a declaration in the prescribed form and verified in the prescribed`
  line `manner, that if the 2 [Assessing Officer] or the appellate authority, as the case may be, agrees to apply to`
  line `the relevant case the final decision on the question of law in the other case, he shall not raise such`
  line `question of law in the relevant case in appeal before any appellate authority or 4 [in appeal before the High`
  line `Court under section 27A or the Supreme Court under section 29].`
  line `( 2 ) Where a declaration under sub-section ( 1 ) is furnished to any appellate authority, the appellate`
  line `authority shall call for a report from the 2 [Assessing Officer] on the correctness of the claim made by the`
  line `assessee and, where the 2 [Assessing Officer] makes a request to the appellate authority to give him an`
  line `opportunity of being heard in the matter, the appellate authority shall allow him such opportunity.`
  line `( 3 ) The 2 [Assessing Officer] or the appellate authority, as the case may be, may, by order in`
  line `writing, —`
  line `( i ) admit the claim of the assessee if he or it is satisfied that the question of law arising in the`
  line `relevant case is identical with the question of law in the other case; or`
  line `( ii ) reject the claim if he or it is not so satisfied.`
  line `( 4 ) Where a claim is admitted under sub-section ( 3 ), —`
  line `( a ) the 2 [Assessing Officer] or, as the case may be, the appellate authority may make an order`
  line `disposing of the relevant case without awaiting the final decision on the question of law in the other`
  line `case; and`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 59 (w.e.f. 1-10-1984).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 111 (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 111, ibid., for “for a reference before the High Court or the Supreme Court under section 27 or in appeal before the`
  line `Supreme Court under section 29” (w.e.f.1 -6-2002).`
