obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line 41
  line `( b ) the assessee shall not be entitled to raise, in relation to the relevant case, such question of law`
  line `in appeal before any appellate authority or 1 [in appeal before the High Court under section 27A or the`
  line `Supreme Court under section 29].`
  line `( 5 ) When the decision on the question of law in the other case becomes final, it shall be applied to the`
  line `relevant case and the 2 [Assessing Officer] or the appellate authority, as the case may be, shall, if`
  line `necessary, amend the order referred to in clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 4 ) conformably to such decision.`
  line `( 6 ) An order under sub-section ( 3 ) shall be final and shall not be called in question in any proceeding`
  line `by way of appeal, reference or revision under this Act.`
  line `Explanation. — In this section, —`
  line `( a ) “ appellate authority ” means the 3 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)], or the Commissioner`
  line `(Appeals) or the Appellate Tribunal;`
  line `( b ) “ case ”, in relation to an assessee, means any proceeding under this Act for the assessment of`
  line `the net wealth of the assessee or for the imposition of any penalty on him.]`
  line `CHAPTER IVB`
  line `C HARGE OF ADDITIONAL WEALTH-TAX IN CERTAIN CASES`
  line `18D. [ Additional wealth-tax ]. — Omitted by the Direct Tax Laws ( Amendment ) Act, 1989 (3 of 1989),`
  line `s. 95 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1989. Earlier it was inserted by the Direct Tax Laws ( Amendment ) Act, 1987 (4 of 1988),`
  line `s. 143 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `CHAPTER V`
  line `L IABILITY TO ASSESSMENT IN SPECIAL CASES`
  line `19. Tax of deceased person payable by legal representative. — ( 1 ) Where a person dies, his`
  line `executor, administrator or other legal representative shall be liable to pay out of the estate of the deceased`
  line `person, to the extent to which the estate is capable of meeting the charge, the wealth-tax assessed as`
  line `payable by such person, or any sum, which would have been payable by him under this Act if he had not`
  line died.
  line `( 2 ) Where a person dies without having furnished a return under the provisions of section 14 or after`
  line `having furnished a return which the 2 [Assessing Officer] has reason to believe to be incorrect or`
  line `incomplete, the 2 [Assessing Officer] may make an assessment of the net wealth of such person and`
  line `determine the wealth-tax payable by the person on the basis of such assessment, and for this purpose may,`
  line `by the issue of the appropriate notice which would have had to be served upon the deceased person if he`
  line `had survived, require from the executor, administrator or other legal representative of the deceased person`
  line `any accounts, documents or other evidence which might under the provisions of section 16 have been`
  line `required from the deceased person.`
  line `( 3 ) The provisions of sections 14, 15 and 17 shall apply to an executor, administrator or other legal`
  line `representative as they apply to any person referred to in those sections.`
  line `4 [ 19A. Assessment in the case of executors. — ( 1 ) Subject as hereinafter provided, the net wealth of`
  line `the estate of a deceased person shall be chargeable to tax in the hands of the executor or executors.`
  line `( 2 ) The executor or executors shall for the purposes of this Act be treated as an individual.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 20 of 2002, s. 111, for “for a reference before the High Court or the Supreme Court under section 27 or in ap peal`
  line `before the Supreme Court under section 29” (w.e.f.1 -6-2002).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1 988, s. 127, for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 127, ibid. for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 46 of 1964, s. 19 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
