obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line 43
  line `21. Assessment when assets are held by courts of wards, administrators-general,`
  line `etc. — ( 1 ) 1 [Subject to the provisions of sub-section ( 1A ), in the case of assets chargeable to tax under this`
  line `Act], which are held by a court of wards or an administrator-general or an official trustee or any receiver`
  line `or manager or any other person, by whatever name called, appointed under any order of a court to manage`
  line `property on behalf of another, or any trustee appointed under a trust declared by a duly executed`
  line `instrument in writing, whether testamentary or otherwise (including a trustee under a valid deed of wakf),`
  line `the wealth-tax shall be levied upon and recoverable from the court of wards, administrator-general,`
  line `official trustee, receiver, manager or trustee, as the case may be, in the like manner and to the same extent`
  line `as it would be leviable upon and recoverable from the person 2 [on whose behalf or for whose benefit] the`
  line `assets are held, and the provisions of this Act shall apply accordingly.`
  line `3 [ Explanation. — A trust which is not declared by a duly executed instrument in writing (including a`
  line `valid deed of wakf) shall be deemed, for the purposes of this sub-section, to be a trust declared by a duly`
  line `executed instrument in writing if a statement in writing, signed by the trustee or trustees, setting out the`
  line `purpose or purposes of the trust, particulars as to the trustee or trustees, the beneficiary or beneficiaries`
  line `and the trust property, is forwarded to the 4 [Assessing Officer], —`
  line `( i ) where the trust has been declared before the 1st day of June, 1981, within a period of three`
  line `months from that day; and`
  line `( ii ) in any other case, within three months from the date of declaration of the trust.]`
  line `5 [( 1A ) Where the value or aggregate value of the interest or interests of the person or persons on`
  line `whose behalf or for whose benefit such assets are held falls short of the value of any such assets, then, in`
  line `addition to the wealth-tax leviable and recoverable under sub-section ( 1 ), the wealth-tax shall be levied`
  line `upon and recovered from the court of wards, administrator-general, official trustee, receiver, manager or`
  line `other person or trustee aforesaid in respect of the value of such assets, to the extent it exceeds the value or`
  line `aggregate value of such interest or interests, as if such excess value were the net wealth of an individual`
  line `who is a citizen of India and resident in India for the purposes of this Act, and —`
  line `( i ) at the rates specified in Part I of Schedule I; or`
  line `( ii ) at the rate of three per cent.,`
  line `whichever course would be more beneficial to the revenue.]`
  line `( 2 ) Nothing contained in sub-section ( 1 ) shall prevent either the direct assessment of the person 2 [on`
  line `whose behalf or for whose benefit] the assets above referred to are held, or the recovery from such person`
  line `of the tax payable in respect of such assets.`
  line `( 3 ) Where the guardian or trustee of any person being a minor, lunatic or idiot 6 *** holds any assets`
  line `7 [on behalf or for the benefit of such beneficiary], the tax under this Act shall be levied upon and`
  line `recoverable from such guardian or trustee, as the case may be, in the like manner and to the same extent`
  line `as it would be leviable upon and recoverable from any such beneficiary if of full age, of sound mind and`
  line `in direct ownership of such assets.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 40, for “In the case of assets chargeable to tax under this Act” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1980).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 46 of 1964, s. 20, for “on whose behalf” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1965).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 16 of 1981, s. 26 (w.e.f. 1-4-1981).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 40 (w.e.f. 1-4-1980).`
  line `6. The brackets and words “(all of which persons are hereinafter in th is sub- section included in the term “beneficiary”) omitted`
  line `by Act 46 of 1964, s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 20, ibid., for “on behalf of such beneficiary” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1965).`
