obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line 44
  line `1 [( 4 ) 2 [Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing provisions of this section], where the`
  line `shares of the persons on whose behalf or for whose benefit any such assets are held are indeterminate or`
  line `unknown, the wealth-tax shall be levied upon and recovered from the court of wards, administrator-`
  line `general, official trustee, receiver, manager, or other person aforesaid 3 [, as the case may be, in the like`
  line `manner and to the same extent as it would be leviable upon and recoverable from an individual who is a`
  line `citizen of India and resident in India] for the purposes of this Act, and —`
  line `( a ) at the rates specified in Part I of 4 [Schedule I] 5 ***; or`
  line `( b ) at the rate of 6 [three per cent.],`
  line `whichever course would be more beneficial to the revenue:`
  line `Provided that in a case where —`
  line `( i ) such assets are held 7 [under a trust declared by any person by will and such trust is the only`
  line `trust so declared by him]; or`
  line `8 [( ia ) none of the beneficiaries has net wealth exceeding the amount not chargeable to wealth-tax`
  line `in the case of an individual who is a citizen of India and resident in India for the purposes of this Act`
  line `or is a beneficiary under any other trust; or]`
  line `( ii ) such assets are held under a trust created before the 1st day of March, 1970, by a non-`
  line `testamentary instrument and the 9 [Assessing Officer] is satisfied, having regard to all the`
  line `circumstances existing at the relevant time, that the trust was created bona fide exclusively for the`
  line `benefit of the relatives of the settlor or where the settlor is a Hindu undivided family, exclusively for`
  line `the benefit of the members of such family, in circumstances where such relatives or members were`
  line `mainly dependent on the settlor for their support and maintenance; or`
  line `( iii ) such assets are held by the trustees on behalf of a provident fund, superannuation fund,`
  line `gratuity fund, pension fund or any other fund created bona fide by a person carrying on a business or`
  line `profession exclusively for the benefit of persons employed in such business or profession,`
  line `wealth-tax shall be charged at the rates specified in Part I of 4 [Schedule I] 5 ***.]`
  line `8 [ Explanation 1. — For the purposes of this sub-section, the shares of the persons on whose behalf or`
  line `for whose benefit any such assets are held shall be deemed to be indeterminate or unknown unless the`
  line `shares of the persons on whose behalf or for whose benefit such assets are held on the relevant valuation`
  line `date are expressly stated in the order of the court or instrument of trust or deed of wakf, as the case may`
  line `be, and are ascertainable as such on the date of such order, instrument or deed.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 19 of 1970, s. 26, for sub-section ( 4 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1971). Earlier it was amended by Act 46 of 1964,`
  line `s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 16 of 1981, s. 26, for “Notwithstanding anything contained in this section” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1981).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 40, for “as if the persons on whose behalf or for whose benefit assets are held were an individual`
  line `who is a citizen of India and resident in India” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1980).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 66 of 1976, s. 27, for “the Schedule” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1977).`
  line `5. The words “in the case of an individual” omitted by Act 32 of 1971, s. 34 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1972).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 44 of 1980, s. 40, for “one and one - half per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1980).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 40, ibid., for “under a trust declared by him” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1980).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act s. 40, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1980).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
