obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line 45
  line `1 [ 2 [ Explanation 2]. — Notwithstanding anything contained in section 5, in computing the net`
  line `wealth 3 [for the purposes of this sub-section or sub-section ( 4A ) in any case, not being a case referred to`
  line `in the proviso to this sub-section], any assets referred to in clauses ( xv ), ( xvi ), ( xxii ), ( xxiii ), ( xxiv ), ( xxv ),`
  line `( xxvi ), ( xxvii ), ( xxviii ) and ( xxix ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of that section shall not be excluded.]`
  line `4 [( 4A ) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, where the assets chargeable to tax under`
  line `this Act are held by a trustee under an oral trust, the wealth-tax shall be levied upon and recovered from`
  line `such trustee in the like manner and to the same extent as it would be leviable upon and recoverable from`
  line `an individual who is a citizen of India and resident in India for the purposes of this Act, and —`
  line `( a ) at the rates specified in Part I of Schedule I; or`
  line `( b ) at the rate of three per cent.,`
  line `whichever course would be more beneficial to the revenue.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section, “ oral trust ” means a trust which is not declared`
  line `by a duly executed instrument in writing (including a valid deed of wakf) and which is not deemed under`
  line `the Explanation to sub-section ( 1 ) to be a trust declared by a duly executed instrument in writing.]`
  line `5 [( 5 ) Any person who pays any sum by virtue of the provisions of this section in respect of the net`
  line `wealth of any beneficiary, shall be entitled to recover the sum so paid from such beneficiary, and may`
  line `retain out of any assets that he may hold on behalf or for the benefit of such beneficiary, an amount equal`
  line `to the sum so paid.`
  line `Explanation. — In this section, the term “ beneficiary ” means any person including a minor, lunatic or`
  line `idiot on whose behalf or for whose benefit assets are held by any other person.]`
  line `6 [( 6 ) Nothing contained in this section shall apply to and in relation to any assessment for the`
  line `assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1993 or any subsequent assessment year.]`
  line `7 [ 21A. Assessment in cases of diversion of property, or of income from property, held under`
  line `trust for public charitable or religious purposes. — 8 [Notwithstanding anything contained in clause ( i )`
  line `of section 5, where any property is held] under trust for any public purpose of a charitable or religious`
  line `nature in India and —`
  line `9 [( i ) any part of such property or any income of such trust [whether derived from such property or`
  line `from voluntary contributions referred to in sub-clause ( iia ) of clause ( 24 ) of section 2 of the Income-tax`
  line `Act] is used or applied, directly or indirectly, for the benefit of 10 [any person referred to in sub-section ( 3 )`
  line `of section 13 of the Income-tax Act], or`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 1971, s. 34 (w.e.f. 1-4-1972).`
  line `2. Explanation renumbered as Explanation 2 thereof by Act 44 of 1980, s. 40 (w.e.f. 1-4-1980).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 16 of 1981, s. 26, for “for the purposes of this sub - section in any case, not being a case referred to in the proviso”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1981).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 26, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1981).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 46 of 1964, s. 20 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 94 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 16 of 1972, s. 46 (w.e.f. 1-4-1973).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 33 of 1996, s. 58, for “Where any property is held” (w.r.e.f. 1 -4-1993). Earlier the quoted words were substituted`
  line `by Act 18 of 1992, s. 95, for “Notwithstanding anything contained in clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 5, where any`
  line `property is held” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1993).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 21 of 1984, s. 34, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-4-1985).`
  line `10. Restored by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-4- 1989). Earlier the words “any interested person” was substituted by Act 4 of`
  line `1988, s. 144, for the given expression (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
