obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line 46
  line `( ii ) any part of the income of the trust [whether derived from such property or from voluntary`
  line `contributions referred to in sub-clause ( iia ) of clause ( 24 ) of section 2 of the Income-tax Act], being a`
  line `trust created on or after the 1st day of April, 1962, enures, directly or indirectly, for the benefit of 1 [any`
  line `person referred to in sub-section ( 3 ) of section 13 of the said Act, or]`
  line `2 [( iii ) any funds of the trust are invested or deposited, or any shares in a company are held by the`
  line `trust, in contravention of the provision of clause ( d ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 13 of the Income-tax`
  line Act,]
  line `wealth-tax shall be leviable upon, and recoverable from, the trustee or manager (by whatever name`
  line `called) in the like manner and to the same extent as if the property were held by an individual who is a`
  line `citizen of India and resident in India for the purposes of this Act 3 ***:]`
  line `Provided that in the case of a trust created before the 1st day of April, 1962, the provisions of clause`
  line `( i ) shall not apply to any use or application, whether directly or indirectly, of any part of such property or`
  line `any income of such trust for the benefit of 4 [any person referred to in sub-section ( 3 ) of section 13 of the`
  line `Income-tax Act], if such use or application is by way of compliance with a mandatory term of the trust:`
  line `5 * * * * *`
  line `6 [ 7 [Provided further that], —`
  line `8 [( a ) in the case of any association referred to in clause ( 21 ) of section 10 of the Income-tax`
  line `Act, —`
  line `( i ) the provisions of clause ( i ) and clause ( ii ) shall not apply; and`
  line `( ii ) the other provisions of this section shall apply with the modifications that, —`
  line `( 1 ) for the words, brackets, letter and figures “in contravention of the provisions of`
  line `clause ( d ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 13 of the Income- tax Act”, the words, brackets and`
  line `figures “in contravention of the provisions contained in the proviso to clause ( 21 ) of`
  line `section 10 of the Income- tax Act” had been substituted; and`
  line `( 2 ) for the words “at the maximum marginal rate”, the words and figures “at the rates`
  line `specified in 9 [sub-section ( 2 ) of section 3]” had been substituted;]`
  line `( b ) in the case of any institution, fund or trust referred to in clause ( 22 ) or clause ( 22A ) or`
  line `clause ( 23B ) or clause ( 23C ) of section 10 of the Income-tax Act, the provisions of 10 [clauses ( i ) to`
  line `( iii )] shall not apply.]`
  line `1. Restored by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-4- 1989). Earlier the words “any interested person,” was substituted by Act 4 of 1988,`
  line `s. 144, for the given expression (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Restored by s. 95, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Earlier clause ( iii ) was omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 144 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. The words “but without excluding the value of any asset under sub -section ( 1 ) of section 5, and at the maximum marginal rate”`
  line `omitted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `4. Restored by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-4- 1989). Earlier the words “any interested person” was substituted by Act 4 of 1988,`
  line `s. 144, for the given expression (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `5. The second proviso omitted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993). Earlier the second proviso was amended by Act 3 of`
  line `1989, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989) and Act 4 of 1988, s. 144 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 21 of 1984, s. 34 (w.e.f. 1-4-1985).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 95, for “Provided also that” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1993).`
  line `8. Restored by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Earlier clause ( a ) was substituted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 144`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 95, for “Part I of Schedule I in the case of an individual” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1993).`
  line `10. Restored by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-4- 1989). Earlier “clauses ( i ) and ( ii )” was substituted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 1 44, for`
  line `the given expression (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
