  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  sourcePage 47
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line 47
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `1 [( a ) any part of the property or income of a trust shall be deemed to have been used or applied`
  line `for the benefit of any person referred to in sub-section ( 3 ) of section 13 of the Income-tax Act in`
  line `every case in which it can be so deemed to have been used or applied within the meaning of clause ( c )`
  line `of sub-section ( 1 ) of that section at any time during the period of twelve months ending with the`
  line `relevant valuation date;`
  line `2 * * * * *]`
  line `( b ) “trust” includes any other legal obligation.]`
  line `3 [ 21AA. Assessment when assets are held by certain associations of persons. — ( 1 ) Where assets`
  line `chargeable to tax under this Act are held by an association of persons, other than a company or co-`
  line `operative society 4 [or society registered under the Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860) or under`
  line `any law corresponding to that Act in force in any part of India], and the individual shares of the members`
  line `of the said association in the income or assets or both of the said association on the date of its formation`
  line `or at any time thereafter are indeterminate or unknown, the wealth-tax shall be levied upon and recovered`
  line `from such association in the like manner and to the same extent as it would be leviable upon and`
  line `recoverable from an individual who is a citizen of India and resident in India for the 5 [purposes of this`
  line `Act 6 ***].`
  line `( 2 ) Where any business or profession carried on by an association of persons referred to in sub-`
  line `section ( 1 ) has been discontinued or where such association of persons is dissolved, the 7 [Assessing`
  line `Officer] shall make an assessment of the net wealth of the association of persons as if no such`
  line `discontinuance or dissolution had taken place and all the provisions of this Act, including the provisions`
  line `relating to the levy of penalty or any other sum chargeable under any provisions of this Act, so far as may`
  line `be, shall apply to such assessment.`
  line `( 3 ) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section ( 2 ), if the 7 [Assessing Officer]`
  line `or the 8 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] or the Commissioner (Appeals) in the course of any`
  line `proceedings under this Act in respect of any such association of persons as is referred to in sub-section ( 1 )`
  line `is satisfied that the association of persons was guilty of any of the acts specified in section 18 or section`
  line `18A, he may impose or direct the imposition of a penalty in accordance with the provisions of the said`
  line sections.
  line `( 4 ) Every person who was at the time of such discontinuance or dissolution a member of the`
  line `association of persons, and the legal representative of any such person who is deceased, shall be jointly`
  line `and severally liable for the amount of tax, penalty or other sum payable, and all the provisions of this Act,`
  line `so far as may be, shall apply to any such assessment or imposition of penalty or other sum.`
  line `( 5 ) Where such discontinuance or dissolution takes place after any proceedings in respect of an`
  line `assessment year have commenced, the proceedings may be continued against the persons referred to in`
  line `sub-section ( 4 ) from the stage at which the proceedings stood at the time of such discontinuance or`
  line `dissolution, and all the provisions of this Act shall, so far as may be, apply accordingly.`
  line `1. Restored by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Earlier clause ( a ) and ( ab ) was substituted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 144, for`
  line `clause ( a ) and ( aa ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Clause ( aa ) omitted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993). Earlier it was inserted by Act 21 of 1984, s. 34`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1985).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 16 of 1981, s. 27 (w.e.f. 1-4-1981).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 13 of 1989, s. 29 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 145, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `6. The words “, and at the maximum marginal rate” omitted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 96 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1993).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 127, ibid., for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
