  sourcePage 48
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line 48
  line `1 * * * * * ]`
  line `22. Assessment of persons residing outside India. — ( 1 ) Where the person liable to tax under this`
  line `Act resides outside India, the tax may be levied upon and recovered from his agent, and the agent shall be`
  line `deemed to be, for all the purposes of this Act, the assessee in respect of such tax.`
  line `( 2 ) Any person employed by or on behalf of a person referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) or through whom`
  line `such person is in the receipt of any income, profits or gains, or who is in possession or has custody of any`
  line `asset of such person and upon whom the 2 [Assessing Officer] has caused a notice to be served of his`
  line `intention of treating him as the agent of such person shall, for the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ), be deemed`
  line `to be the agent of such person.`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `4 [( 3 ) No person shall be deemed to be the agent of any person residing outside India unless he has had`
  line `an opportunity of being heard by the 2 [Assessing Officer] as to his being treated as such.`
  line `( 4 ) Any agent, who, as such, pays any sum under this Act, shall be entitled to recover the sum so paid`
  line `from the person on whose behalf it is paid or to retain out of any moneys that may be in his possession or`
  line `may come to him in his capacity as such agent, an amount equal to the sum so paid.`
  line `( 5 ) Any agent, or any person who apprehends that he may be assessed as an agent, may retain out of`
  line `any money payable by him to the person residing outside India on whose behalf he is liable to pay tax`
  line `(hereinafter in this section referred to as the principal), a sum equal to his estimated liability under this`
  line `section, and in the event of any disagreement between the principal and such agent or person, as to the`
  line `amount to be so retained, such agent or person may secure from the 2 [Assessing Officer] a certificate`
  line `stating the amount to be so retained pending final settlement of the liability, and the certificate so`
  line `obtained shall be his warrant for retaining that amount.`
  line `( 6 ) The amount recoverable from such agent or person at the time of final settlement shall not exceed`
  line `the amount specified in such certificate, except to the extent to which such agent or person may at such`
  line `time have in his hands additional assets of the principal.`
  line `( 7 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, any arrears of tax due from a person residing`
  line `outside India may be recovered also in accordance with the provisions of this Act from any assets of such`
  line `person which are or may at any time come within India.]`
  line `5 [CHAPTER VA`
  line `S ETTLEMENT OF CASES`
  line `6 [ 22A. Definitions. — In this Chapter, unless the context otherwise requires, —`
  line `( a ) “Bench” means a Bench of the Settlement Commission;`
  line `7 [( b ) “case” means any proceeding for assessment under this Act, of any person in respect of any`
  line `assessment year or assessment years which may be pending before an Assessing Officer on the date`
  line `on which an application under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 22C is made:`
  line `1. The Explanation omitted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 96 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. The proviso omitted by Act 46 of 1964, s. 21 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 21, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 93 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 77, for section 22A (w.e.f. 1-6-1987).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 84, for clause ( b ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
