  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  sourcePage 49
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line 49
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause —`
  line `( i ) a proceeding for assessment or reassessment referred to in 2 [section 17 shall, in case where`
  line `a notice under the said section] is issued but not on the basis of search under section 37A or`
  line `requisition under section 37B, be deemed to have commenced from the date on which a notice`
  line `under section 17 is issued;`
  line `3 [( ii ) a proceeding for making fresh assessment in pursuance of an order under section 23A or`
  line `section 24 or section 25, setting aside or cancelling an assessment shall be deemed to have been`
  line `commenced from the date on which such order, setting aside or cancelling an assessment was`
  line passed.]
  line `4 [( iii ) a proceeding for assessment or reassessment for any of the assessment years, in`
  line `consequence of a search initiated under section 37A or requisition made under section 37B, shall`
  line `be deemed to have commenced on the date of issue of notice initiating such proceedings and`
  line `concluded on the date on which the assessment is made;]`
  line `( iv ) a proceeding for assessment for an assessment year, other than the proceeding of`
  line `assessment or reassessment referred to in 5 [clause ( i ) or clause ( ii ) clause ( iii )], shall be deemed`
  line `to have commenced from the 1st day of the assessment year and concluded on the date on which`
  line `the assessment is made;]`
  line `( c ) “ Chairman ” means the Chairman of the Settlement Commission;`
  line `( d ) “ Member ” means a Member of the Settlement Commission, and includes the Chairman and a`
  line Vice-Chairman;
  line `( e ) “ Settlement Commission ” means the Income-tax Settlement Commission constituted under`
  line `section 245B of the Income-tax Act;`
  line `( f ) “ Vice-Chairman ” means a Vice-Chairman of the Settlement Commission 6 [and includes a`
  line `Member who is senior amongst the Members of a Bench];`
  line `( g ) “ wealth-tax authority ” means an income-tax authority specified in section 116 of the Income-`
  line `tax Act who is treated as a wealth-tax authority under section 8.]`
  line `22B. Wealth-tax Settlement Commission. — ( 1 ) The Central Government shall constitute a`
  line `Commission to be called the Wealth-tax Settlement Commission 7 *** for the settlement of cases under`
  line `this Chapter.`
  line `( 2 ) The Settlement Commission shall consist of a Chairman 8 [and as many Vice-Chairmen and other`
  line `members as the Central Government thinks fit] and shall function within the Department of the Central`
  line `Government dealing with direct taxes.`
  line `1. The proviso omitted by Act 25 of 2014, s. 77 (w.e.f. 1-10-2014). Earlier it was amended by Act 14 of 2010, s. 53`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-6-2010).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 77, ibid., for “ clause ( i ) of the proviso shall, in case where a notice under section 17” (w.e.f. 1 -10-2014).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 77, ibid., for clause ( ii ) (w.e.f. 1-10-2014).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 53, for clasue ( iii ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2010).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 25 of 2014, s. 77, for “clause ( i ) or clause ( ii ) of the proviso or clause ( iii ) of the Explanation ”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-10-2014). Ealier it was amended by Act 14 of 2010, s. 53 (w.e.f. 1-6-2010).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 84 (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line `7. The brackets and words “(hereafter in this Chapter referred to as “the Settlement Commission”)” omitted by Act 11 of 1987, s.`
  line `78 (w.e.f. 1-6-1987).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 46 of 1986, s. 35, for “and two other members” (w.e.f. 10 -9-1986).`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-50
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Page 50`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  sourcePage 50
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line 50
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `( 3 ) The Chairman 2 [, Vice-Chairman] and other members of the Settlement Commission shall be`
  line `appointed by the Central Government from amongst persons of integrity and outstanding ability, having`
  line `special knowledge of, and experience in, problems relating to direct taxes and business accounts:`
  line `Provided that, where a member of the Board is appointed as the Chairman 2 [, Vice-Chairman] or as a`
  line `member of the Settlement Commission, he shall cease to be a member of the Board.`
  line `3 * * * * *`
  line `4 [ 22BA. Jurisdiction and powers of Settlement Commission. — ( 1 ) Subject to the other provisions`
  line `of this Chapter, the jurisdiction, powers and authority of the Settlement Commission may be exercised by`
  line `Benches thereof.`
  line `( 2 ) Subject to the other provisions of this section, a Bench shall be presided over by the Chairman or`
  line `a Vice-Chairman and shall consist of two other Members.`
  line `( 3 ) The Bench for which the Chairman is the Presiding Officer shall be the principal Bench and the`
  line `other Benches shall be known as additional Benches.`
  line `( 4 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ), the Chairman may authorise the`
  line `Vice-Chairman or other Member appointed to one Bench to discharge also the functions of the`
  line `Vice-Chairman or, as the case may be, other Member of another Bench.`
  line `( 5 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing provisions of this section, and subject to any`
  line `rules that may be made in this behalf, when one of the persons constituting a Bench (whether such person`
  line `be the Presiding Officer or other Member of the Bench) is unable to discharge his functions owing to`
  line `absence, illness or any other cause or in the event of the occurrence of any vacancy either in the office of`
  line `the Presiding Officer or in the office of one or the other Members of the Bench, the remaining two`
  line `persons may function as the Bench and if the Presiding Officer of the Bench is not one of the remaining`
  line `two persons, the senior among the remaining persons shall act as the Presiding Officer of the Bench:`
  line `Provided that if at any stage of the hearing of any case or matter, it appears to the Presiding Officer`
  line `that the case or matter is of such a nature that it ought to be heard by a Bench consisting of three`
  line `Members, the case or matter may be referred by the Presiding Officer of such Bench to the Chairman for`
  line `transfer to such Bench as the Chairman may deem fit.`
  line `5 [( 5A ) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing provisions of this section, the Chairman`
  line `may, for the disposal of any particular case, constitute a Special Bench consisting of more than three`
  line Members.]
  line `( 6 ) Subject to the other provisions of this Chapter, the places at which the principal Bench and the`
  line `additional Benches shall ordinarily sit, shall be such as the Central Government may, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, specify 5 [and the Special Bench shall sit at a place to be fixed by the Chairman].`
  line `1. Sub-section ( 2A ) omitted by Act 46 of 1986, s. 35 (w.e.f. 10-9-1986). Earlier sub-section ( 2A ) was inserted by Act 14 of 1982,`
  line `s. 36 (w.e.f. 1-4-1982).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 35, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-9-1986).`
  line `3. The second proviso omitted by s. 35, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-9-1986).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 79 (w.e.f. 1-6-1987).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 77 (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-51
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Page 51`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  sourcePage 51
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line 51
  line `22BB. Vice-Chairman to act as Chairman or to discharge his functions in certain`
  line `circumstances. — ( 1 ) In the event of the occurrence of any vacancy in the office of the Chairman by`
  line `reason of his death, resignation or otherwise, the Vice- Chairman or, as the case may be, such one of the`
  line `Vice-Chairmen as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, authorise in this`
  line `behalf, shall act as the Chairman until the date on which a new Chairman, appointed in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of this Chapter to fill such vacancy, enters upon his office.`
  line `( 2 ) When the Chairman is unable to discharge his functions owing to absence, illness or any other`
  line `cause, the Vice-Chairman or, as the case may be, such one of the Vice-Chairmen as the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, authorise in this behalf, shall discharge the`
  line `functions of the Chairman until the date on which the Chairman resumes his duties.`
  line `22BC. Power of Chairman to transfer cases from one Bench to another. — On the application of`
  line `the assessee or the 1 [Chief Commissioner or Commissioner] and after notice to them, and after hearing`
  line `such of them as may desire to be heard, or on his own motion without such notice, the Chairman may`
  line `transfer any case pending before one Bench, for disposal, to another Bench.`
  line `22BD. Decision to be by majority. — If the Members of a Bench differ in opinion on any point, the`
  line `point shall be decided according to the opinion of the majority, if there is a majority, but if the Members`
  line `are equally divided, they shall state the point or points on which they differ, and make a reference to the`
  line `Chairman who shall either hear the point or points himself or refer the case for hearing on such point or`
  line `points by one or more of the other Members of the Settlement Commission and such point or points shall`
  line `be decided according to the opinion of the majority of the Members of the Settlement Commission who`
  line `have heard the case, including those who first heard it.]`
  line `22C. Application for settlement of cases. — 2 [( 1 ) An assessee may, at any stage of a case relating to`
  line `him, make an application in such form and in such manner as may be prescribed, and containing a full`
  line `and true disclosure of his wealth which has not been disclosed before the 3 [Assessing Officer], the manner`
  line `in which such wealth has been derived, the additional amount of wealth-tax payable on such wealth and`
  line `such other particulars as may be prescribed, to the Settlement Commission to have the case settled and`
  line `any such application shall be disposed of in the manner hereinafter provided:`
  line `4 [Provided that no such application shall be made unless such wealth-tax and the interest thereon,`
  line `which would have been paid under the provisions of this Act had the wealth declared in the application`
  line `been declared in the return of wealth before the Assessing Officer on the date of application, has been`
  line `paid on or before the date of making the application and the proof of such payment is attached with the`
  line application.]
  line `( 1A ) For the purposes of sub-section ( 1 ) of this section 5 *** the additional amount of wealth-tax`
  line `payable in respect of the wealth disclosed in an application made under sub-section ( 1 ) of this section`
  line `shall be the amount calculated in accordance with the provisions of sub-sections ( 1B ) to ( 1D ).`
  line `6 [ 7 [( 1B ) Where the wealth disclosed in the application relates to only one previous year, —`
  line `( i ) if the applicant has not furnished a return in respect of the net wealth of that year, then,`
  line `wealth-tax shall be calculated on the wealth disclosed in the application as if such wealth were the net`
  line wealth;
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 60, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-10-1984).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 85, for the proviso (w.e.f. 1-6-2007). Earlier it was inserted by Act 11 of 1987, s. 80`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-6-1987).`
  line `5. The words, brackets, figures and letters “and sub -sections ( 2A ) to ( 2D ) of section 22D ” o mitted by s. 85, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-`
  line `2007).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 80, for sub-sections ( 1B ) and ( 1C ) (w.e.f. 1-6-1987).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 85, for sub-section ( 1B ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-52
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Page 52`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  sourcePage 52
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line 52
  line `( ii ) if the applicant has furnished a return in respect of the net wealth of that year, wealth-tax shall`
  line `be calculated on the aggregate of the net wealth returned and the wealth disclosed in the application`
  line `as if such aggregate were the net wealth.]`
  line `( 1C ) The additional amount of wealth-tax payable in respect of the wealth disclosed in the application`
  line `relating to the previous year referred to in sub-section ( 1B ) shall be, —`
  line `( a ) in a case referred to in clause ( i ) of that sub-section, the amount of wealth-tax calculated under`
  line `that clause;`
  line `( b ) in a case referred to in clause ( ii ) of that sub-section, the amount of wealth-tax calculated`
  line `under that clause as reduced by the amount of wealth-tax calculated on the net wealth returned for`
  line `that year;`
  line `1 * * * * *]`
  line `( 1D ) Where the wealth disclosed in the application relates to more than one assessment year, the`
  line `additional amount of wealth-tax payable in respect of the wealth disclosed for each of the years shall first`
  line `be calculated in accordance with the provisions of sub-sections ( 1B ) and ( 1C ) and the aggregate of the`
  line `amount so arrived at in respect of each of the years for which the application has been made under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) shall be the additional amount of wealth-tax payable in respect of the wealth disclosed in`
  line `the application.`
  line `( 1E ) Where any books of account or other documents belonging to an assessee are seized under`
  line `section 37A, the assessee shall not be entitled to make an application under sub-section ( 1 ) before the`
  line `expiry of one hundred and twenty days from the date of the seizure.]`
  line `( 2 ) Every application made under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be accompanied by such fees as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line `( 3 ) An application made under sub-section ( 1 ) shall not be allowed to be withdrawn by the applicant.`
  line `2 [( 4 ) An assessee shall, on the date on which he makes an application under sub-section ( 1 ) to the`
  line `Settlement Commission, also intimate the Assessing Officer in the prescribed manner of having made`
  line `such application to the said Commission.]`
  line `22D. Procedure on receipt of an application under section 22C. — 3 [( 1 ) On receipt of an`
  line `application under section 22C, the Settlement Commission shall, within seven days from the date of`
  line `receipt of the application, issue a notice to the applicant requiring him to explain as to why the application`
  line `made by him be allowed to be proceeded with, and on hearing the applicant, the Settlement Commission`
  line `shall, within a period of fourteen days from the date of the application, by an order in writing, reject the`
  line `application or allow the application to be proceeded with:`
  line `Provided that where no order has been passed within the aforesaid period by the Settlement`
  line `Commission, the application shall be deemed to have been allowed to be proceeded with.]`
  line `4 * * * * *`
  line `1. Clause ( c ) omitted by Act 22 of 2007, s. 85 (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 85, ibid. (w.e.f.1-6-2007).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 86, ibid., for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2007). Earlier it was amended by Act 49 of 1991, s. 78 (w.e.f. 27-9-1991)`
  line `and Act 20 of 2002, s. 112 (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
  line `4. Sub-section ( 1A ) omitted by Act 49 of 1991, s. 78 (w.e.f. 27-9-1991). Earlier it was inserted by Act 21 of 1979, s. 24`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1979).`
