  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  sourcePage 53
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line 53
  line `( 2 ) A copy of every order under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be sent to the applicant and to the`
  line Commissioner.
  line `1 [( 2A ) Where an application was made under section 22C before the 1st day of June, 2007 but an`
  line `order under the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ) of this section, as they stood immediately before their`
  line `amendment by the Finance Act, 2007 (22 of 2007), has not been made before the 1st day of June, 2007,`
  line `such application shall be deemed to have been allowed to be proceeded with if the additional wealth-tax`
  line `on the wealth disclosed in such application and the interest thereon is paid on or before the 31st day of`
  line `July, 2007.`
  line `Explanation. — In respect of the applications referred to in this sub-section, the 31st day of July, 2007`
  line `shall be deemed to be the date of the order of rejection or allowing the application to be proceeded with`
  line `under sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `( 2B ) The Settlement Commission shall, —`
  line `( i ) in respect of an application which is allowed to be proceeded with under sub-section ( 1 ),`
  line `within thirty days from the date on which the application was made; or`
  line `( ii ) in respect of an application referred to in sub-section ( 2A ) which is deemed to have been`
  line `allowed to be proceeded with under that sub-section, on or before the 7th day of August, 2007,`
  line `call for a report from the Commissioner, and the Commissioner shall furnish the report within a period of`
  line `thirty days of the receipt of communication from the Settlement Commission.`
  line `( 2C ) Where a report of the Commissioner called for under sub-section ( 2B ) has been furnished within`
  line `the period specified therein, the Settlement Commission may, on the basis of the material contained in`
  line `such report and within a period of fifteen days of the receipt of the report, by an order in writing, declare`
  line `the application in question as invalid, and shall send the copy of such order to the applicant and the`
  line `Commissioner:`
  line `Provided that an application shall not be declared invalid unless an opportunity has been given to the`
  line `applicant of being heard:`
  line `Provided further that where the Commissioner has not furnished the report within the aforesaid`
  line `period, the Settlement Commission shall proceed further in the matter without the report of the`
  line Commissioner.
  line `( 2D ) Where an application was made under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 22C before the 1st day of June,`
  line `2007 and an order under the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ) of this section, as they stood immediately`
  line `before their amendment by the Finance Act, 2007 (22 of 2007), allowing the application to have been`
  line `proceeded with, has been passed before the 1st day of June, 2007, but an order under the provisions of`
  line `sub-section ( 4 ), as they stood immediately before their amendment by the Finance Act, 2007, was not`
  line `passed before the 1st day of June, 2007, such application shall not be allowed to be further proceeded`
  line `with unless the additional wealth-tax on the wealth disclosed in such application and the interest thereon,`
  line `is, notwithstanding any extension of time already granted by the Settlement Commission, paid on or`
  line `before the 31st day of July, 2007.]`
  line `2 [( 3 ) The Settlement Commission, in respect of —`
  line `( i ) an application which has not been declared invalid under sub-section ( 2C ); or`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 86, for sub-sections ( 2A ), ( 2B ), ( 2C ) and ( 2D ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 86, ibid., for sub-sections ( 3 ) ( 4 ) and ( 4A ) (w.e.f. 1-6-2007). Earlier sub-section ( 4A ) was inserted by Act 20 of`
  line `2002, s. 112 (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
