  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-54
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Page 54`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  sourcePage 54
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line 54
  line `( ii ) an application referred to in sub-section ( 2D ) which has been allowed to be further proceeded`
  line `with under that sub-section,`
  line `may call for the records from the Commissioner and after examination of such records, if the Settlement`
  line `Commission is of the opinion that any further enquiry or investigation in the matter is necessary, it may`
  line `direct the Commissioner to make or cause to be made such further enquiry or investigation and furnish a`
  line `report on the matters covered by the application and any other matter relating to the case, and the`
  line `Commissioner shall furnish the report within a period of ninety days of the receipt of communication`
  line `from the Settlement Commission:`
  line `Provided that where the Commissioner does not furnish his report within the aforesaid period, the`
  line `Settlement Commission may proceed to pass an order under sub-section ( 4 ) without such report.`
  line `( 4 ) After examination of the records and the report of the Commissioner, if any, received under —`
  line `( i ) sub-section ( 2B ) or sub-section ( 3 ), or`
  line `( ii ) the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ), as they stood immediately before their amendment by the`
  line `Finance Act, 2007 (22 of 2007),`
  line `and after giving an opportunity to the applicant and to the Commissioner to be heard, either in person or`
  line `through a representative duly authorised in this behalf, and after examining such further evidence as may`
  line `be placed before it or obtained by it, the Settlement Commission may, in accordance with the provisions`
  line `of this Act, pass such order, as it thinks fit, on the matters covered by the application and any other matter`
  line `relating to the case not covered by the application, but referred to in the report of the Commissioner.`
  line `( 4A ) The Settlement Commission shall pass an order under sub-section ( 4 ), —`
  line `( i ) in respect of an application referred to in sub-section ( 2A ) or sub-section ( 2D ), on or before the`
  line `31st day of March, 2008;`
  line `( ii ) in respect of an application made on or after the 1st day of June, 2007 1 [but before the 1st day`
  line `of June, 2010], within twelve months from the end of the month in which the application was made;`
  line `2 [( iii ) in respect of an application made on or after the 1st day of June, 2010, within eighteen`
  line `months from the end of the month in which the application was made.]]`
  line `3 [( 5 ) Subject to the provisions of section 22BA, the materials brought on record before the Settlement`
  line `Commission shall be considered by the Members of the concerned Bench before passing any order under`
  line `sub-section (4) and, in relation to the passing of such order, the provisions of section 22BD shall apply.]`
  line `( 6 ) Every order passed under sub-section ( 4 ) shall provide for the terms of settlement including any`
  line `demand by way of 4 [tax, penalty or interest], the manner in which any sum due under the settlement shall`
  line `be paid and all other matters to make the settlement effective and shall also provide that the settlement`
  line `shall be void if it is subsequently found by the Settlement Commission that it has been obtained by fraud`
  line `or misrepresentation of facts.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 14 of 2010, s. 54 (w.e.f. 1-4-2010).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 54, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-2010).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 81 (w.e.f. 1-6-1987). Earlier it was amended by Act 14 of 1982, s. 37 (w.e.f. 1-4-1982) which was`
  line `later omitted by Act 46 of 1986, s. 36 (w.e.f. 10-9-1986).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 81, ibid., for “tax or penalty” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1987). Earlier the quoted wo rds were substituted for “tax, penalty or`
  line `interest” by Act 67 of 1984, s. 62 (w.e.f. 1 -10-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-55
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Page 55`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  sourcePage 55
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line 55
  line `1 [( 6A ) Where any tax payable in pursuance of an order under sub-section ( 4 ) is not paid by the`
  line `assessee within thirty-five days of the receipt of a copy of the order by him, then, whether or not the`
  line `Settlement Commission has extended the time for payment of such tax or has allowed payment thereof by`
  line `instalments, the assessee shall be liable to pay simple interest at 2 [one and one-fourth per cent. for every`
  line `month or part of a month] on the amount remaining unpaid from the date of expiry of the period of thirty-`
  line `five days aforesaid.]`
  line `3 [( 6B ) The Settlement Commission may, at any time within a period of six months from the date of`
  line `the order, with a view to rectifying any mistake apparent from the record, amend any order passed by it`
  line `under sub-section ( 4 ):`
  line `Provided that an amendment which has the effect of modifying the liability of the applicant shall not`
  line `be made under this sub-section unless the Settlement Commission has given notice to the applicant and`
  line `the Commissioner of its intention to do so and has allowed the applicant and the Commissioner an`
  line `opportunity of being heard.]`
  line `( 7 ) Where a settlement becomes void as provided in sub-section ( 6 ), the proceedings with respect to`
  line `the matters covered by the settlement shall be deemed to have been revived from the stage at which the`
  line `application was allowed to be proceeded with by the Settlement Commission and the wealth-tax authority`
  line `concerned may, notwithstanding anything contained in any other provision of this Act, complete such`
  line `proceedings at any time before the expiry of two years from the end of the financial year in which the`
  line `settlement became void.`
  line `1 [( 8 ) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that nothing contained in section 17A shall`
  line `apply to any order passed under sub-section ( 4 ) or to any order of assessment or reassessment required to`
  line `be made by the 4 [Assessing Officer] in pursuance of any directions contained in such order passed by the`
  line `Settlement Commission.]`
  line `5 [ 22DD. Power of Settlement Commission to order provisional attachment to protect`
  line `revenue. — ( 1 ) Where, during the pendency of any proceeding before it, the Settlement Commission is of`
  line `the opinion that for the purpose of protecting the interests of the revenue it is necessary so to do, it may,`
  line `by order, attach provisionally any property belonging to the applicant in the manner provided in the`
  line `Second Schedule to the Income-tax Act as made applicable to this Act by section 32:`
  line `Provided that where a provisional attachment made under section 34C is pending immediately before`
  line `an application is made under section 22C, an order under this sub-section shall continue such provisional`
  line `attachment up to the period up to which an order made under section 34C would have continued if such`
  line `application had not been made:`
  line `Provided further that where the Settlement Commission passes an order under this sub-section after`
  line `the expiry of the period referred to in the preceding proviso, the provisions of sub-section ( 2 ) shall apply`
  line `to such order as if the said order had originally been passed by the Settlement Commission.`
  line `( 2 ) Every provisional attachment made by the Settlement Commission under sub-section ( 1 ) shall`
  line `cease to have effect after the expiry of a period of six months from the date of the order made under sub-`
  line `section ( 1 ):`
  line `Provided that the Settlement Commission may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, extend the`
  line `aforesaid period by such further period or periods as it thinks fit 6 ***.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 62 (w.e.f. 1-10-1984).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 86, for “fifteen per cent. per annum” (w.e.f. 1 -4-2008).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 8 of 2011, s. 35 (w.e.f. 1-6-2011).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 56 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `6. The words “, so, however, that the total period of extension shall not in any case exceed two years” omitted by Act 22 of 2007,`
  line `s. 87 (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
