obj_root_law_sections_56:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-56
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Page 56`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  sourcePage 56
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line 56
  line `22E. Power of Settlement Commission to reopen completed proceedings. — If the Settlement`
  line `Commission is of the opinion (the reasons for such opinion to be recorded by it in writing) that, for the`
  line `proper disposal of the case pending before it, it is necessary or expedient to reopen any proceeding`
  line `connected with the case, but which has been completed under this Act by any wealth-tax authority before`
  line `the application under section 22C was made, it may, with the concurrence of the applicant, reopen such`
  line `proceeding and pass such order thereon as it thinks fit as if the case in relation to which the application`
  line `for settlement had been made by the applicant under that section covered such proceeding also:`
  line `1 [Provided that no proceeding shall be reopened by the Settlement Commission under this section if`
  line `the period between the end of the assessment year to which such a proceeding relates and the date of`
  line `application for settlement under section 22C exceeds nine years:]`
  line `2 [Provided further that no proceeding shall be reopened by the Settlement Commission under this`
  line `section in a case where an application under section 22C is made on or after the 1st day of June, 2007.]`
  line `22F. Powers and procedure of Settlement Commission. — ( 1 ) In addition to the powers conferred`
  line `on the Settlement Commission under this Chapter, it shall have all the powers which are vested in a`
  line `wealth-tax authority under this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) Where an application made under section 22C has been allowed to be proceeded with under`
  line `section 22D, the Settlement Commission shall, until an order is passed under sub-section ( 4 ) of section`
  line `22D, have, subject to the provisions of sub-section ( 3 ) of that section, exclusive jurisdiction to exercise`
  line `the powers and perform the functions of a wealth-tax authority under this Act in relation to the case:`
  line `3 [Provided that where an application has been made under section 22C on or after the 1st day of June,`
  line `2007, the Settlement Commission shall have such exclusive jurisdiction from the date on which the`
  line `application was made:`
  line `Provided further that where —`
  line `( i ) an application made on or after the 1st day of June, 2007, is rejected under sub-section ( 1 ) of`
  line `section 22D; or`
  line `( ii ) an application is not allowed to be proceeded with under sub-section ( 2A ) of section 22D, or,`
  line `as the case may be, is declared invalid under sub-section ( 2C ) of that section; or`
  line `( iii ) an application is not allowed to be further proceeded with under sub-section ( 2D ) of section`
  line 22D,
  line `the Settlement Commission, in respect of such application shall have such exclusive jurisdiction up to the`
  line `date on which the application is rejected, or, not allowed to be proceeded with, or, declared invalid, or,`
  line `not allowed to be further proceeded with, as the case may be.]`
  line `( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 2 ) and in the absence of any express direction`
  line `to the contrary by the Settlement Commission, nothing contained in this section shall affect the operation`
  line `of any other provisions of this Act requiring the applicant to pay tax on the basis of self-assessment in`
  line `relation to the matters before the Settlement Commission.`
  line `( 4 ) For the removal of doubt, it is hereby declared that, in the absence of any express direction by the`
  line `Settlement Commission to the contrary, nothing in this Chapter shall affect the operation of the provisions`
  line `of this Act in so far as they relate to any matters other than those before the Settlement Commission.`
  line `4 [ 5 * * * * *`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 82, for the proviso (w.e.f. 1-6-1987).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 88 (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 89, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 46 of 1986, s. 37, for sub-section ( 5 ) (w.e.f. 10-9-1986).`
  line `5. Sub-sections ( 5 ) and ( 6 ) omitted by Act 11 of 1987, s. 83 (w.e.f. 1-6-1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-57
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Page 57`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  sourcePage 57
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line 57
  line `( 7 ) The Settlement Commission shall, subject to the provisions of this Chapter, have power to`
  line `regulate its own procedure and the procedure of Benches thereof in all matters arising out of the exercise`
  line `of its powers or of the discharge of its functions, including the places at which the Benches shall hold`
  line `their sittings.]`
  line `22G. Inspection, etc., of reports. — No person shall be entitled to inspect, or obtain copies of, any`
  line `reports made by any wealth-tax authority to the Settlement Commission; but the Settlement Commission`
  line `may, in its discretion, furnish copies thereof to any such person on an application made to it in this behalf`
  line `and on payment of the prescribed fee:`
  line `Provided that, for the purpose of enabling any person whose case is under consideration to rebut any`
  line `evidence brought on the record against him in any such report, the Settlement Commission shall, on an`
  line `application made in this behalf and on payment of the prescribed fee by such person, furnish him with a`
  line `certified copy of any such report or part thereof relevant for the purpose.`
  line `22H. Powers of Settlement Commission to grant immunity from prosecution. — ( 1 ) The`
  line `Settlement Commission may, if it is satisfied that any person who made the application for settlement`
  line `under section 22C has co-operated with the Settlement Commission in the proceedings before it and has`
  line `made a full and true disclosure of his net wealth and the manner in which such wealth has been acquired,`
  line `grant to such person, subject to such conditions as it may think fit to impose, immunity from prosecution`
  line `for any offence under this Act or under the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) or under any other Central Act`
  line `for the time being in force 1 [and also (either wholly or in part) from the imposition of any penalty] under`
  line `this Act, with respect to the case covered by the settlement:`
  line `2 [Provided that no such immunity shall be granted by the Settlement Commission in cases where the`
  line `proceedings for the prosecution for any such offence have been instituted before the date of receipt of the`
  line `application under section 22C:]`
  line `3 [Provided further that the Settlement Commission shall not grant immunity from prosecution for any`
  line `offence under the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) or under any Central Act other than this Act and`
  line `Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961) to a person who makes an application under section 22C on or after`
  line `the 1st day of June, 2007.]`
  line `2 [( 1A ) An immunity granted to a person under sub-section ( 1 ) shall stand withdrawn if such person`
  line `fails to pay any sum specified in the order of settlement passed under sub-section ( 4 ) of section 22D`
  line `within the time specified in such order or within such further time as may be allowed by the Settlement`
  line `Commission, or fails to comply with any other condition subject to which the immunity was granted and`
  line `thereupon the provisions of this Act shall apply as if such immunity had not been granted.]`
  line `( 2 ) An immunity granted to a person under sub-section ( 1 ) may, at any time, be withdrawn by the`
  line `Settlement Commission, if it is satisfied that such person 4 *** had, in the course of the settlement`
  line `proceedings, concealed any particular material to the settlement or had given false evidence, and`
  line `thereupon such person may be tried for the offence with respect to which the immunity was granted or for`
  line `any other offence of which he appears to have been guilty in connection with the settlement and shall also`
  line `become liable to the imposition of any penalty under this Act to which such person would have been`
  line `liable, had no such immunity been granted.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 63, for “and also from the imposition of any penalty” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1984).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 84 (w.e.f. 1-6-1987).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 90 (w.e.f. 1-6-2007).`
  line `4. The words “has not complied with the conditions subject to which the immunity was granted or that such person” omitted by`
  line `Act 11 of 1987, s. 84 (w.e.f. 1-6-1987).`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-58
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Page 58`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  sourcePage 58
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line 58
  line `1 [ 22HA. Abatement of proceedings before Settlement Commission. — ( 1 ) Where, —`
  line `( i ) an application made under section 22C on or after the 1st day of June, 2007 has been rejected`
  line `under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 22D; or`
  line `( ii ) an application made under section 22C has not been allowed to be proceeded with under sub-`
  line `section (2A) or further proceeded with under sub-section ( 2D ) of section 22D; or`
  line `( iii ) an application made under section 22C has been declared as invalid under sub-section ( 2C )`
  line `of section 22D; or`
  line `( iv ) in respect of any other application made under section 22C, an order under sub-section ( 4 ) of`
  line `section 22D has not been passed within the time or period specified under sub-section ( 4A ) of section`
  line 22D,
  line `the proceedings before the Settlement Commission shall abate on the specified date.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub- section, “ specified date ” means —`
  line `( a ) in respect of an application referred to in clause ( i ), the date on which the application was`
  line rejected;
  line `( b ) in respect of an application referred to in clause ( ii ), the 31st day of July, 2007;`
  line `( c ) in respect of an application referred to in clause ( iii ), the last day of the month in which the`
  line `application was declared invalid;`
  line `( d ) in respect of an application referred to in clause ( iv ), the date on which the time or period`
  line `specified in sub-section ( 4A ) of section 22D expires.`
  line `( 2 ) Where a proceeding before the Settlement Commission abates, the Assessing Officer, or, as the`
  line `case may be, any other wealth-tax authority before whom the proceeding at the time of making the`
  line `application was pending, shall dispose of the case in accordance with the provisions of this Act as if no`
  line `application under section 22C had been made.`
  line `( 3 ) For the purposes of sub-section ( 2 ), the Assessing Officer, or, as the case may be, other wealth-tax`
  line `authority, shall be entitled to use all the material and other information produced by the assessee before`
  line `the Settlement Commission or the results of the inquiry held or evidence recorded by the Settlement`
  line `Commission in the course of the proceedings before it, as if such material, information, inquiry and`
  line `evidence had been produced before the Assessing Officer or other wealth-tax authority or held or`
  line `recorded by him in the course of the proceedings before him.`
  line `( 4 ) For the purposes of the time-limit under sections 17A, 32 and 35 and for the purposes of payment`
  line `of interest under section 34A, in case referred to in sub-section ( 2 ), the period commencing on and from`
  line `the date of an application to the Settlement Commission under section 22C and ending with “ specified`
  line `date ” referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) shall be excluded.`
  line `22HAA. Credit for tax paid in case of abatement of proceedings. — Where an application made`
  line `under section 22C on or after the 1st day of June, 2007, is rejected under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 22D,`
  line `or any other application made under section 22C is not allowed to be proceeded with under sub-section`
  line `( 2A ) of section 22D or is declared invalid under sub-section ( 2C ) of section 22D or has not been allowed`
  line `to be further proceeded with under sub-section ( 2D ) of section 22D or an order under sub-section ( 4 ) of`
  line `section 22D has not been passed within the time or period specified under sub-section ( 4A ) of section`
  line `22D, the Assessing Officer shall allow the credit for the tax and interest paid on or before the date of`
  line `making the application or during the pendency of the case before the Settlement Commission.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 91 (w.e.f. 1-6-2007). Earlier section 22HA was inserted by Act 11 of 1987, s. 85 (w.e.f. 1-6-1987)`
  line `and amended by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988) which was later omitted by Act 20 of 2002, s. 113 (w.e.f. 1-6-2002).`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
