obj_root_law_sections_59:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-59
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Page 59`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  sourcePage 59
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line 59
  line `22-I. Order of settlement to be conclusive. — Every order of settlement passed under sub-section ( 4 )`
  line `of section 22D shall be conclusive as to the matters stated therein and no matter covered by such order`
  line `shall, save as otherwise provided in this Chapter, be reopened in any proceeding under this Act or under`
  line `any other law for the time being in force.`
  line `22J. Recovery of sums due under order of settlement. — Any sum specified in an order of`
  line `settlement passed under sub-section (4) of section 22D may, subject to such conditions, if any, as may be`
  line `specified therein, be recovered, and any penalty for default in making payment of such sum may be`
  line `imposed and recovered in accordance with the provisions of section 32 by the 1 [Assessing Officer] having`
  line `jurisdiction over the person who made the application for settlement under section 22C.`
  line `2 [ 22K. Bar on subsequent application for settlement. — ( 1 ) Where, —`
  line `( i ) an order of settlement passed under sub-section ( 4 ) of section 22D provides for the imposition`
  line `of a penalty on the person who made the application under section 22C for settlement, on the ground`
  line `of concealment of particulars of his net wealth; or`
  line `( ii ) after the passing of an order of settlement under the said sub-section ( 4 ) in relation to a case,`
  line `such person is convicted of any offence under Chapter VIII in relation to that case; or`
  line `( iii ) the case of any such person was sent back to the Assessing Officer by the Settlement`
  line `Commission on or before the 1st day of June, 2002,`
  line `then, he shall not be entitled to apply for settlement under section 22C in relation to any other matter.`
  line `( 2 ) Where a person has made an application under section 22C on or after the 1st day of June, 2007`
  line `and if such application has been allowed to be proceeded with under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 22D, such`
  line `person shall not be subsequently entitled to make an application under section 22C.]`
  line `22L. Proceedings before the Settlement Commission to be judicial proceedings. — Any`
  line `proceeding under this Chapter before the Settlement Commission shall be deemed to be a judicial`
  line `proceeding within the meaning of sections 193 and 228, and for the purposes of section 196, of the Indian`
  line `Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line `22M. [ Certain persons who have filed appeals to the Appellate Tribunal entitled to make applications`
  line `to the Settlement Commission.] — Omitted by the Finance Act, 1987, s. 87 ( w.e.f. 1 - 6 - 1987). Earlier it was`
  line `inserted by Act 41 of 1975, s. 93 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1976) which was later amended by Act 67 of 1984, s. 64`
  line `( w.e.f. 1-10-1984).`
  line `CHAPTER VI`
  line `A PPEALS, REVISIONS AND REFERENCES`
  line `23. Appeal to the 3 [ Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] from orders of 1 [Assessing`
  line `Officer.] — ( 1 ) 4 [Subject to the provisions of sub-section ( 1A ), any person], —`
  line `( a ) objecting to the amount of 5 [net wealth] determined under this Act; or`
  line `( b ) objecting to the amount of wealth-tax determined as payable by him under this Act; or`
  line `1. Subs. b y Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 92, for section 22K (w.e.f. 1-6-2007). Earlier it was amended by Act 11 of 1987, s. 86`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-6-1987).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule, for “Any person” (w.e.f. 10 -7-1978).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 46 of 1964, s. 22, for “his net wealth” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1965).`
