  line 60
  line `( c ) denying his liability to be assessed under this Act; or`
  line `1 [( d ) objecting to any penalty imposed by the Assessing Officer under section 18 2 ***; or]`
  line `( e ) objecting to any order of the 3 [Assessing Officer] under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 20; or`
  line `( f ) objecting to any penalty imposed by the 3 [Assessing Officer] under the provisions of`
  line `4 [section 221] of the Income-tax Act as applied under section 32 for the purposes of wealth-tax; 5 [or]`
  line `5 [( g ) objecting to any order made by the 3 [Assessing Officer] under section 22 treating him as the`
  line `agent of a person residing outside India; or`
  line `( h ) objecting to any order of the 3 [Assessing Officer] under section 35 having the effect of`
  line `enhancing the assessment or reducing a refund or refusing to allow the claim made by the assessee`
  line `under the said section; or`
  line `6 [( ha ) objecting to any order of the Valuation Officer under section 35 having the effect of`
  line `enhancing the valuation of any asset or refusing to allow the claim made by the assessee under the`
  line `said section; or]`
  line `7 * * * * *]`
  line `may appeal to the 8 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] 9 [before the 1st day of June, 2000,] against the`
  line `assessment or order, as the case may be, in the prescribed form and verified in the prescribed manner.`
  line `10 [( 1A ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), any person, —`
  line `( a ) objecting to the amount of net wealth determined under this Act or objecting to the amount of`
  line `wealth-tax determined as payable by him under this Act or denying his liability to be assessed under`
  line `this Act, where the net wealth determined on assessment made under section 16 exceeds fifteen lakh`
  line `rupees; or`
  line `11 [ 12 [( b ) objecting to any penalty imposed under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 18 with the previous`
  line `approval of the Deputy Commissioner as specified in sub-section ( 3 ) of that section; or]`
  line `( c ) objecting to any assessment or order referred to in clauses ( a ) to ( h ) (both inclusive) of sub-`
  line `section ( 1 ), where such assessment or order has been made by the Deputy Commissioner in exercise`
  line `of the powers or functions conferred on or assigned to him under section 8 or section 11; or`
  line `( d ) objecting to any penalty imposed by the Deputy Director or the Deputy Commissioner under`
  line `section 18A; or]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 146, for clause ( d ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Earlier it was amended by Act 46 of 1964, s. 22`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1964).`
  line `2. The words “as it stood immediately before the 1st day of April, 1989 or under section. 18 as amended by the Direct Tax Laws`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 1987 (4 of 1988)” omitted by Act 3 of 1989, s. 71 (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 46 of 1964, s. 22, for “sub -section ( 1 ) of section 46” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1965).`
  line `5. Ins. by s. 22, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 45 of 1972, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-1-1973).`
  line `7. Clause ( i ) omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 146 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Earlier it was amended by Act 45 of 1972, s. 11`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-1-1973).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 127, ibid., for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 72 (w.e.f. 1-6-2000).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `11. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 146, for clauses ( b ), ( c ) and ( d ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `12. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 71, for clause ( b ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
