obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line 61
  line `( e ) objecting to an order made by an 1 [Assessing Officer] in the case of such persons or classes of`
  line `persons as the Board may, having regard to the nature of the cases, the complexities involved and`
  line `other relevant considerations, direct,`
  line `may appeal to the Commissioner (Appeals) 2 [before the 1st day of June, 2000,] against the assessment or`
  line `order, as the case may be, in the prescribed form and verified in the prescribed manner.`
  line `2 [( 1AA ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), every appeal filed, on or after the 1st`
  line `day of October, 1998, but before the 1st day of June, 2000, before the Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)`
  line `and any matter arising out of or connected with such appeal and which is so pending shall stand`
  line `transferred to the Commissioner (Appeals) and the Commissioner (Appeals) may proceed with such`
  line `appeal or matter from the stage at which it was on that day.]`
  line `3 [( 1B ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), the Board or the Director General or`
  line `Chief Commissioner or Commissioner, if so authorised by the Board, may, by order in writing, transfer`
  line `any appeal which is pending before a Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) and any matter arising out of or`
  line `connected with such appeal and which is so pending, to the Commissioner (Appeals) if the Board or, as`
  line `the case may be, the Director General, Chief Commissioner or Commissioner (at the request of the`
  line `appellant or otherwise) is satisfied that it is necessary or expedient so to do having regard to the nature of`
  line `the case, the complexities involved and other relevant considerations and the Commissioner (Appeals)`
  line `may proceed with such appeal or matter from the stage at which it was before it was so transferred:`
  line `Provided that the appellant may demand that before proceeding further with the appeal or matter, the`
  line `previous proceeding or any part thereof be re-opened or that he be reheard.]]`
  line `( 2 ) An appeal shall be presented within thirty days of the receipt of the notice of demand relating to`
  line `the assessment or penalty objected to, or the date on which any order objected to, is communicated to`
  line `him, but the 4 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] 5 [or, as the case may be, the Commissioner (Appeals)]`
  line `may admit an appeal after the expiration of the period aforesaid if he is satisfied that the appellant had`
  line `sufficient cause for not presenting the appeal within that period.`
  line `6 [( 2A ) Where a return has been filed by an assessee, no appeal under this section shall be admitted`
  line `unless at the time of filing of the appeal he has paid the tax due on the net wealth returned by him.`
  line `7 * * * * *]`
  line `( 3 ) The 4 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] 5 [or, as the case may be, the Commissioner (Appeals)]`
  line `shall fix a day and place for the hearing of the appeal and may, from time to time, adjourn the hearing.`
  line `8 [( 3A ) If the valuation of any asset is objected to in an appeal under clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 1 ) 5 [or`
  line `of sub-section ( 1A )], the 4 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] 5 [or, as the case may be, the Commissioner`
  line `(Appeals)] shall, —`
  line `( a ) in a case where such valuation has been made by a Valuation Officer under section 16A, give`
  line `such Valuation Officer an opportunity of being heard;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 72 (w.e.f. 1-6-2000).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 146, for sub-sections ( 1B ) and ( 1C ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Earlier sub-section ( 1B ) was inserted by`
  line `Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978) and sub-section ( 1C ) was inserted by Act 21 of 1979, s. 25`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-6-1979).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 127, ibid., for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 94 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `7. The proviso omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 146 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 45 of 1972, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-1-1973).`
