obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line 62
  line `( b ) in any other case, on a request being made in this behalf by the 1 [Assessing Officer], give an`
  line `opportunity of being heard to any Valuation Officer nominated for the purpose by the 1 [Assessing`
  line `Officer]. ]`
  line `( 4 ) The 2 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] 3 [or, as the case may be, the Commissioner (Appeals)]`
  line `may —`
  line `( a ) at the hearing of an appeal, allow an appellant to go into any ground of appeal not specified in`
  line `the grounds of appeal;`
  line `( b ) before disposing of an appeal, make such further inquiry as he thinks fit or cause further`
  line `inquiry to be made by the 4 [ 1 [Assessing Officer] or, as the case may be, the Valuation Officer].`
  line `( 5 ) In disposing of an appeal, the 2 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] 3 [or, as the case may be, the`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals)] may pass such order as he thinks fit which may include an order enhancing the`
  line `assessment or penalty:`
  line `Provided that no order enhancing the assessment or penalty shall be made unless the person affected`
  line `thereby has been given a reasonable opportunity of showing cause against such enhancement.`
  line `5 [( 5A ) In disposing of an appeal, the 2 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] 3 [or, as the case may be, the`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals)] may consider and decide any matter arising out of the proceedings in which the`
  line `order appealed against was passed, notwithstanding that such matter was not raised before the 2 [Deputy`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals)] 3 [or, as the case may be, the Commissioner (Appeals)] by the appellant.`
  line `( 5B ) The order of the 2 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] 3 [or, as the case may be, the Commissioner`
  line `(Appeals)] disposing of the appeal shall be in writing and shall state the points for determination, the`
  line `decision thereon and the reasons for the decision.]`
  line `( 6 ) A copy of every order passed by the 2 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] 3 [or, as the case may be,`
  line `the Commissioner (Appeals)] under this section shall be forwarded to the appellant and the 6 [Chief`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner].`
  line `7 [ 23A. Appealable orders before Commissioner (Appeals). — ( 1 ) Any person —`
  line `( a ) objecting to the amount of net wealth determined under this Act; or`
  line `( b ) objecting to the amount of wealth-tax determined as payable by him under this Act; or`
  line `( c ) denying his liability to be assessed under this Act; or`
  line `( d ) objecting to any penalty imposed by the Assessing Officer under section 18 or section 18A; or`
  line `( e ) objecting to any order of the Assessing Officer under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 20; or`
  line `( f ) objecting to any penalty imposed by the Assessing Officer under the provisions of section 221`
  line `of the Income-tax Act as applied under section 32 for the purposes of wealth-tax; or`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 127, ibid., for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 45 of 1972, s. 11, for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -1-1973).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 46 of 1964, s. 22 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 69 (w.e.f. 1-10-1998). Earlier section 23A was inserted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 147 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989)`
  line `which was later omitted by Act 3 of 1989, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
