obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line 63
  line `( g ) objecting to any order made by the Assessing Officer under section 22 treating him as the`
  line `agent of a person residing outside India; or`
  line `( h ) objecting to any order of the Assessing Officer under section 35 having the effect of`
  line `enhancing the assessment or reducing a refund or refusing to allow the claim made by the assessee`
  line `under the said section; or`
  line `( i ) objecting to any order of the Valuation Officer under section 35 having the effect of enhancing`
  line `the valuation of any asset or refusing to allow the claim made by the assessee under the said section;`
  line or
  line `( j ) objecting to any penalty imposed by the Deputy Director or Deputy Commissioner under`
  line `section 18A,`
  line `may appeal to the Commissioner (Appeals) against the assessment or order, as the case may be, in the`
  line `prescribed form and verified in the prescribed manner and on payment of a fee of two hundred and fifty`
  line rupees.
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section, where on or before the 1st day of October, 1998,`
  line `the post of Deputy Commissioner has been redesignated as Joint Commissioner and the post of Deputy`
  line `Director has been redesignated as Joint Director, the references in this sub-section for “ Deputy`
  line `Commissioner ” and “ Deputy Director ” shall be substituted by “ Joint Commissioner ” and “ Joint Director ”`
  line respectively.
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ) of section 23, every appeal under this Act`
  line `which is pending immediately before the appointed day, before the Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) and`
  line `any matter arising out of or connected with such appeal and which is so pending shall stand transferred on`
  line `that day to the Commissioner (Appeals) and the Commissioner (Appeals) may proceed with such appeals`
  line `or matter from the stage on which it was on that day:`
  line `Provided that the appellant may demand that before proceeding further with the appeal or matter, the`
  line `previous proceedings or any part thereof be re-opened or that he be re-heard.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section, “ appointed day ” means the day appointed under`
  line `section 246A of the Income-tax Act.`
  line `( 3 ) An appeal shall be presented within thirty days of the receipt of the notice of demand relating to`
  line `the assessment or penalty objected to or the day on which any order objected to is communicated to him,`
  line `but the Commissioner (Appeals) may admit an appeal after the expiration of the period aforesaid, if he is`
  line `satisfied that the appellant had sufficient cause for not presenting the appeal within that period.`
  line `( 4 ) Where a return has been filed by an assessee, no appeal under this section shall be admitted unless`
  line `at the time of filing of the appeal, he has paid the tax due on the net wealth returned by him.`
  line `( 5 ) The Commissioner (Appeals) shall fix a day and place for the hearing of the appeal and may, from`
  line `time to time, adjourn the hearing.`
  line `( 6 ) If the valuation of any asset is objected to in an appeal under clause ( a ) or clause ( i ) of sub-section`
  line `( 1 ), the Commissioner (Appeals) shall, —`
  line `( a ) in case where such valuation has been made by a Valuation Officer under section 16A, give`
  line `such Valuation Officer an opportunity of being heard;`
  line `( b ) in any other case on request being made in this behalf by the Assessing Officer, give an`
  line `opportunity of being heard to any Valuation Officer nominated for the purpose by the Assessing`
  line Officer.
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-64
  sectionNo (64)
