  title `Page 64`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  sourcePage 64
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line 64
  line `( 7 ) The Commissioner (Appeals) may, —`
  line `( a ) at the hearing of an appeal, allow an appellant to go into any ground of appeal not specified in`
  line `the grounds of appeal;`
  line `( b ) before disposing of any appeal, make such further enquiry as he thinks fit or cause further`
  line `enquiry to be made by the Assessing Officer or, as the case may be, by the Valuation Officer.`
  line `( 8 ) In disposing of an appeal, the Commissioner (Appeals) may pass such order as he thinks fit which`
  line `may include an order enhancing the assessment or penalty:`
  line `Provided that no order enhancing the assessment or penalty shall be made unless the person affected`
  line `thereby has been given a reasonable opportunity of showing cause against such enhancement.`
  line `1 [( 8A ) In every appeal, the Commissioner (Appeals), where it is possible, may hear and decide such`
  line `appeal within a period of one year from the end of the financial year in which such appeal is filed under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ).]`
  line `( 9 ) In disposing of an appeal, the Commissioner (Appeals) may consider and decide any matter`
  line `arising out of the proceedings in which the order appealed against was passed, notwithstanding that such`
  line `matter was not placed before the Commissioner (Appeals) by the appellant.`
  line `2 [( 9A ) In disposing of an appeal against the order of assessment in respect of which the proceeding`
  line `before the Settlement Commission abates under section 22HA, he may, after taking into consideration all`
  line `the material and other information produced by the assessee before, or the results of the inquiry held or`
  line `evidence recorded by, the Settlement Commission, in the course of the proceedings before it and such`
  line `other material as may be brought on his record, confirm, reduce, enhance or annul the assessment.]`
  line `( 10 ) The order of the Commissioner (Appeals) disposing of the appeal shall be in writing and shall`
  line `state the points for determining the decision thereon and reasons for the decision.`
  line `( 11 ) A copy of every order passed by the Commissioner (Appeals) under this section shall be`
  line `forwarded to the appellant and the Chief Commissioner or Commissioner.]`
  line `24. Appeal to the Appellate Tribunal from orders of the 3 [ Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)]. —`
  line `4 [( 1 ) An assessee objecting to an order passed by the 3 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)], 5 [or the`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals)] under section 18 or section 18A or section 23 6 [, section 23A] or`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ) of section 37 7 *** may appeal to the Appellate Tribunal within sixty days of the date on`
  line `which the order is communicated to him.]`
  line `( 2 ) The Commissioner may, if he is not satisfied as to the correctness of any order passed`
  line `by 8 [a Commissioner (Appeals) under sub-section ( 10 ) of section 23A], direct the 9 [Assessing Officer]`
  line `to appeal to the Appellate Tribunal against such order, and such appeal may be made at any time before`
  line `the expiry of sixty days of the date on which the order is communicated to the Commissioner.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 93 (w.e.f. 1-6-1999).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 64 (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 95, for sub-section ( 1 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1976). Earlier it was substituted by Act 46 of 1964,`
  line `s. 23 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 70 (w.e.f. 1-10-998).`
  line `7. The words, figures and letter “, or to an order passed by the Inspecting Assistant Commissioner under section 18A” omitted by`
  line `Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 70, for “a Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) or a Commissioner (Appeals) under section 23”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-10-1998). Earlier it was amended by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978) and later by`
  line `Act 4 of 1988, s. 127 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Wealth -tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
