obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line 65
  line `1 [( 2A ) The 2 [Assessing Officer] or the assessee, as the case may be, on receipt of notice that an appeal`
  line `against the order of 3 [*** the Commissioner (Appeals)] has been preferred under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-`
  line `section ( 2 ) by the other party, may, notwithstanding that he may not have appealed against such order or`
  line `any part thereof, within thirty days of the receipt of the notice, file a memorandum of cross-objections`
  line `verified in the prescribed manner, against any part of the order of 3 [*** the Commissioner (Appeals)] and`
  line `such memorandum shall be disposed of by the Appellate Tribunal as if it were an appeal presented within`
  line `the time specified in sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ).]`
  line `4 [( 3 ) The Appellate Tribunal may admit an appeal or permit the filing of a memorandum of cross-`
  line `objections after the expiry of the relevant period referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ) or sub-`
  line `section ( 2A ), if it is satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not presenting it within that period.]`
  line `( 4 ) An appeal to the Appellate Tribunal shall be in the prescribed form and shall be verified in the`
  line `prescribed manner and shall, except in the case of an appeal referred to in sub-section ( 2 ), be`
  line `accompanied by a fee of 5 [one thousand rupees]:`
  line `6 [Provided that in the case of an appeal not relatable to net wealth as computed by the Assessing`
  line `Officer, the appeal shall be accompanied by a fee of five hundred rupees.]`
  line `( 5 ) The Appellate Tribunal may, after giving both parties to the appeal an opportunity of being heard,`
  line `pass such orders thereon as it thinks fit, and any such orders may include an order enhancing the`
  line `assessment or penalty:`
  line `7 [Provided that if the valuation of any asset is objected to, the Appellate Tribunal shall, —`
  line `( a ) in a case where such valuation has been made by a Valuation Officer under section 16A, also`
  line `give such Valuation Officer an opportunity of being heard;`
  line `( b ) in any other case, on a request being made in this behalf by the 2 [Assessing Officer], give an`
  line `opportunity of being heard also to any Valuation Officer nominated for the purpose by the`
  line `2 [Assessing Officer]:`
  line `Provided further that] no order enhancing an assessment or penalty shall be made unless the person`
  line `affected thereby has been given a reasonable opportunity of showing cause against such enhancement.`
  line `6 [( 5A ) In every appeal, the Appellate Tribunal, where it is possible, may hear and decide such appeal`
  line `within a period of four years from the end of the financial year in which such appeal is filed under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) 8 [or sub-section ( 2 )].`
  line `( 5B ) The cost of any appeal to the Appellate Tribunal shall be at the discretion of that Tribunal.]`
  line `9 * * * * *`
  line `( 9 ) A copy of every order passed by the Appellate Tribunal under this section shall be forwarded to`
  line `the assessee and the Commissioner.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 46 of 1964, 23 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. The words and brackets “the Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) or” omitted by Act 21 of 1998, s. 70 ( w.e.f. 1-10-1998). Earlier`
  line `it was amended by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978) and by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127 (w.e.f. 1-4-`
  line `1988).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 46 of 1964, s. 23, for sub-section ( 3 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 21 of 199 8, s. 70, for “two hundred rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 94 (w.e.f. 1-6-1999).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 45 of 1972, s. 12, for “Provided that” (w.e.f. 1 -1-1973).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 73 (w.e.f. 1-6-2000).`
  line `9. Sub-sections ( 6 ), ( 7 ), ( 8 ), ( 8A ) and ( 8B ) omitted by Act 45 of 1972, s. 12 (w.e.f. 1-1-1973). Earlier these sub-sections were`
  line `substituted by Act 46 of 1964, s. 23 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
