  title `Page 66`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  sourcePage 66
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line 66
  line `( 10 ) Save as provided in section 27 1 [or section 27A], any order passed by the Appellate Tribunal on`
  line `appeal shall be final.`
  line `( 11 ) The provisions of 2 [sub-sections ( 1 ), ( 4 ) and ( 5 ) of section 255] of the Income-tax Act shall`
  line `apply to the Appellate Tribunal in the discharge of its functions under this Act as they apply to it in the`
  line `discharge of its functions under the Income-tax Act.`
  line `25. Powers of Commissioner to revise orders of subordinate authorities. — ( 1 ) The Commissioner`
  line `may, either of his own motion or on application made by an assessee in this behalf, call for the record of`
  line `any proceeding under this Act in which an order has been passed by any authority subordinate to him, and`
  line `may make such inquiry, or cause such enquiry to be made, and, subject to the provisions of this Act, pass`
  line `such order thereon, not being an order prejudicial to the assessee, as the Commissioner thinks fit:`
  line `Provided that the Commissioner shall not revise any order under this sub-section in any case —`
  line `( a ) where an appeal against the order lies to the 3 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] 4 [or to the`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals)] or to the Appellate Tribunal, the time within which such appeal can be`
  line `made has not expired or in the case of an appeal 4 [to the Commissioner (Appeals) or] to the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal the assessee has not waived his right of appeal;`
  line `( b ) where the order is the subject of an appeal before the 3 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] 4 [or`
  line `the Commissioner (Appeals)] or the Appellate Tribunal;`
  line `( c ) where the application is made by the assessee for such revision, unless —`
  line `( i ) the application is accompanied by a fee of twenty-five rupees; and`
  line `( ii ) the application is made within one year from the date of the order sought to be revised or`
  line `within such further period as the Commissioner may think fit to allow on being satisfied that the`
  line `assessee was prevented by sufficient cause from making the application within that period; and`
  line `( d ) where the order is sought to be revised by the Commissioner of his own motion, if such order`
  line `is made more than one year previously.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section, —`
  line `( a ) the 3 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] shall be deemed to be an authority subordinate to the`
  line `Commissioner; and`
  line `( b ) an order by the Commissioner declining to interfere shall be deemed not to be an order`
  line `prejudicial to the assessee.`
  line `( 2 ) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-section ( 1 ), the Commissioner may call for`
  line `and examine the record of any proceeding under this Act, and if he considers that any order passed therein`
  line `by an 5 [Assessing Officer] is erroneous in so far as it is prejudicial to the interests of revenue, he may,`
  line `after giving the assessee an opportunity of being heard, and after making or causing to be made such`
  line `inquiry as he deems necessary, pass such order thereon as the circumstances of the case justify, including`
  line `an order enhancing or modifying the assessment or cancelling it and directing a fresh assessment.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 94 (w.e.f. 1-6-1999).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 46 of 1964, s. 23, for “s ub-sections ( 5 ), ( 7 ) and ( 8 ) of section 5A” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1965).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 4 of 198 8, s. 127, for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
