obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line 67
  line `1 [ Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that, for the purposes of this`
  line `sub-section, —`
  line `( a ) an order passed 2 [on or before or after the 1st day of June, 1988,] by the Assessing Officer`
  line `shall include an order made by the 3 [Joint Commissioner] in exercise of the powers or in the`
  line `performance of the functions of an Assessing Officer conferred on or assigned to him under orders or`
  line `directions issued by the Board or by the Chief Commissioner or Director General or Commissioner`
  line `authorised by the Board in this behalf under section 120 of the Income-tax Act read with section 8 of`
  line `this Act;`
  line `( b ) “ record ”, 4 [shall include and shall be deemed always to have included] all records relating to`
  line `any proceeding under this Act available at the time of examination by the Commissioner;`
  line `( c ) where any order referred to in this sub-section and passed by the Assessing Officer had been`
  line `the subject matter of any appeal 2 [filed on or before or after the 1st day of June, 1988], the powers of`
  line `the Commissioner under this sub-section shall extend 2 [and shall be deemed always to have extended]`
  line `to such matters as had not been considered and decided in such appeal.]`
  line `5 [( 3 ) No order shall be made under sub-section ( 2 ) after the expiry of two years 6 [from the end of the`
  line `financial year in which the order sought to be revised was passed].`
  line `Explanation. — In computing the period of limitation for the purposes of sub-section ( 3 ), the time`
  line `taken in giving an opportunity to the assessee to be reheard under the proviso to section 39 and any period`
  line `during which any proceeding under this section is stayed by an order or injunction of any court shall be`
  line excluded.
  line `7 [( 3A ) On every application made by an assessee for revision under sub-section ( 1 ), an order shall be`
  line `passed by the Commissioner within one year from the end of financial year in which such application is`
  line `made by the assessee for revision.`
  line `Explanation. — In computing the period of limitation for the purposes of this sub-section, the time`
  line `taken in giving an opportunity to the assessee to be re-heard under the proviso to section 39 and any`
  line `period during which any proceeding under this section is stayed by an order or injunction of any court`
  line `shall be excluded.]`
  line `8 [( 4 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 3 ) or sub-section ( 3A ), an order in revision`
  line `under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ) may be passed at any time in consequence of, or to give effect to,`
  line `any finding or direction contained in an order of the Appellate Tribunal 9 [National Tax Tribunal], the`
  line `High Court or the Supreme Court.]]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 57, for the Explanation (w.e.f. 1-6-1988). Earlier it was inserted by Act 67 of 1984, s. 65`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-10-1984) and later amended by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 13 of 1989, s. 30 (w.r.e.f. 1-6-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 66, for “Deputy Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 13 of 1989, s. 30, for “includes” (w.r.e.f. 1 -6-1988).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 46 of 1964, s. 24 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 65, for “from the date of the order sought to be revised” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1984).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 71 (w.e.f. 1-10-1998).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 71, ibid., for sub-section ( 4 ) (w.e.f. 1-10-1998).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 49 of 2005, s. 30 and the Schedule. This Act has been struck down by the Supreme Court’s Order dated 25th`
  line `September, 2014 in the Madras Bar Association Vs. Union of India.`
