  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  sourcePage 68
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line 68
  line `26. Appeal to the Appellate Tribunal from orders of enhancement by 1 [Chief Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner ]. — ( 1 ) Any assessee objecting to 2 [an order passed by the 1 [Chief Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner] under section 18 3 [or section 18A] or sub-section ( 2 ) of section 25] 4 [or an order passed`
  line `by the Director General or Director under section 18A] may appeal to the Appellate Tribunal within sixty`
  line `days of the date on which the order is communicated to him.`
  line `( 2 ) An Appeal to the Appellate Tribunal under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be in the prescribed form and`
  line `shall be verified in the prescribed manner and shall be accompanied by a fee of 5 [two hundred rupees].`
  line `( 3 ) The provisions of 6 [sub-sections ( 3 ), ( 5 ), ( 9 ) and ( 10 )] of section 24 shall apply in relation to any`
  line `appeal under this section as they apply in relation to any appeal under that section.`
  line `27. Reference to High Court. — 7 [( 1 ) The assessee or the 1 [Chief Commissioner or Commissioner]`
  line `may, within sixty days of the date upon which he is served with notice of an order 8 [passed before the 1st`
  line `day of June, 1999] under section 24 or section 26 9 [or clause ( e ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 35], by`
  line `application in the prescribed form, accompanied, where the application is made by the assessee, by a fee`
  line `of 5 [two hundred rupees], require the Appellate Tribunal to refer to the High Court any question of law`
  line `arising out of such order and, subject to the other provisions contained in this section, the Appellate`
  line `Tribunal shall, within one hundred and twenty days of the receipt of such application, draw up a statement`
  line `of the case and refer it to the High Court.`
  line `( 2 ) The Appellate Tribunal may, if it is satisfied that the applicant was prevented by sufficient cause`
  line `from presenting the application within the period specified in sub-section ( 1 ), allow it to be presented`
  line `within a further period not exceeding thirty days.]`
  line `( 3 ) If, on an application made under sub-section ( 1 ), the Appellate Tribunal —`
  line `( a ) refuses to state a case on the ground that no question of law arises, or`
  line `( b ) rejects it on the ground that it is time barred;`
  line `the applicant may, within 10 [ninety days] from the date on which he is served with a notice of refusal or`
  line `rejection, as the case may be, apply to the High Court, and the High Court may, if it is not satisfied with`
  line `the correctness of the decision of the Appellate Tribunal, require the Appellate Tribunal to state the case`
  line `to the High Court, and on receipt of such requisition, the Appellate Tribunal shall state the case:`
  line `Provided that, if in any case where the Appellate Tribunal has been required by an assessee to state a`
  line `case, the Appellate Tribunal refuses to do so on the ground that no question of law arises, the assessee`
  line `may, within thirty days from the date on which he receives notice of refusal to state the case, withdraw his`
  line `application, and if he does so, the fee paid by him under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be refunded to him.`
  line `11 [( 3A ) If, on an application made under this section, the Appellate Tribunal is of the opinion that, on`
  line `account of a conflict in the decisions of the High Courts in respect of any particular question of law, it is`
  line `expedient that a reference should be made direct to the Supreme Court, the Appellate Tribunal may draw`
  line `up a statement of the case and refer it through its President direct to the Supreme Court.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 46 of 1964, s. 25, for “an order of enhancement made by the Commissioner under section 25” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1965).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 96 (w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 72 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 16 of 198 1, s. 29, for “one hundred and twenty - five rupees” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1981).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 45 of 1972, s. 13, for “sub -sections ( 3 ) and ( 5 ) to ( 10 ) inclusive” (w.e.f. 1 -1-1973).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 46 of 1964, s. 26, for sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 95 (w.e.f. 1-6-1999).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 79 (w.e.f. 27-9-1991).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 46 of 1964, s. 26, for “three months” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1965).`
  line `11. Ins. by s. 26, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
