  title `Page 70`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  sourcePage 70
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line 70
  line `( 6 ) The High Court shall decide the question of law so formulated and deliver such judgment thereon`
  line `containing the grounds on which such decision is founded and may award such cost as it deems fit.`
  line `( 7 ) The Assessing Officer shall give effect to the order of the High Court on the basis of a certified`
  line `copy of judgment delivered under sub-section ( 6 ).]`
  line `1 [( 8 ) The provisions of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) relating to appeals to High`
  line `Court shall, so far as may be, apply in the case of appeals under this section.]`
  line `28. Hearing by High Court. — When a case has been stated to the High Court 2 [under section 27 or`
  line `an appeal filed before the High Court under section 27A], it shall be heard by a Bench of not less than`
  line `two Judges of the High Court and shall be decided in accordance with the opinion of such Judges or of`
  line `the majority of such Judges, if any:`
  line `Provided that where there is no such majority, the Judges shall state the point of law upon which they`
  line `differ and the case shall then be heard upon that point only by one or more of the Judges of the High`
  line `Court, and such point shall be decided according to the opinion of the majority of the Judges who have`
  line `heard the case, including those who first heard it.`
  line `29. Appeal to Supreme Court. — ( 1 ) An appeal shall lie to the Supreme Court from any judgment of`
  line `the High Court delivered 3 [before the date of establishment of the National Tax Tribunal] on a case stated`
  line `4 [under section 27 or an appeal filed under section 27A] in any case which the High Court certifies as a fit`
  line `case for appeal to the Supreme Court.`
  line `( 2 ) Where the judgment of the High Court is varied or reversed on appeal under this section, effect`
  line `shall be given to the order of the Supreme Court in the manner provided in sub-section ( 6 ) of section 27`
  line `5 [or in sub-section ( 7 ) of section 27A].`
  line `( 3 ) The High Court may, on application made to it for the execution of any order of the Supreme`
  line `Court in respect of any costs awarded by it, transmit the order for execution to any court subordinate to`
  line `the High Court.`
  line `6 [ 29A. Tax to be paid notwithstanding reference, etc. — Notwithstanding that a reference has been`
  line `made to the High Court or the Supreme Court or an appeal has been preferred to the Supreme`
  line `Court, 3 [under this Act before the commencement of the National Tax Tribunal Act, 2005] wealth-tax`
  line `shall be payable in accordance with the assessment made in the case.`
  line `29B. Definition of High Court. — In this Cha pter, “High Court” means —`
  line `( i ) in relation to any State, the High Court of that State;`
  line `7 [( ii ) in relation to the Union territory of Delhi, the High Court of Delhi;`
  line `8 * * * * *]`
  line `9 [( iii ) in relation to the Union territories of Arunachal Pradesh and Mizoram, the Gauhati High`
  line `Court (the High Court of Assam, Nagaland, Meghalaya, Manipur and Tripura);]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 96 (w.e.f. 1-6-1999).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 73, for “under section 27” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 49 o f 2005, s. 30 and the Schedule. This Act has been struck down by the Supreme Court’s Order dated 25th`
  line `September, 2014 in the Madras Bar Association Vs. Union of India.`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 74, for “under section 27” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `5. Ins. by s. 74, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-10-1998).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 46 of 1964, s. 27 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `7. Subs. by the Punjab Reorganisation and Delhi High Court (Adaptation of Laws on Union Subjects) Order, 1968, for`
  line `clause ( ii ) (w.e.f. 1-11-1966).`
  line `8. Clause ( iia ) omitted by the State of Himachal Pradesh (Adaptation of Laws on Union Subjects) Order, 1973`
  line `(w.e.f. 25-1-1971).`
  line `9. Subs. by the North-Eastern Areas (Reorganisation) (Arunachal of Laws on Union Subjects) Order, 1974, for clause ( iii ) (w.e.f.`
  line `21-1-1972).`
