  line `( iv ) in relation to the Union territory of Andaman and Nicobar Islands, the High Court at`
  line Calcutta;
  line `( v ) in relation to the Union territory of 1 [Lakshadweep], the High Court of Kerala;`
  line `( vi ) in relation to the Union territories of Dadra and Nagar Haveli and Goa, Daman and Diu, the`
  line `High Court at Bombay;`
  line `( vii ) in relation to the Union territory of Pondicherry, the High Court at Madras;`
  line `2 [( viii ) in relation to the Union territory of Chandigarh, the High Court of Punjab and Haryana.]]`
  line `CHAPTER VII`
  line `P AYMENT AND RECOVERY OF WEALTH-TAX`
  line `3 [ 30. Notice of demand. — When any tax, interest, penalty, fine or any other sum is payable in`
  line `consequence of any order passed under this Act, the 4 [Assessing Officer] shall serve upon the assessee a`
  line `notice of demand in the prescribed form specifying the sum so payable.`
  line `31. When tax, etc., payable and when assessee deemed in default. — ( 1 ) Any amount specified as`
  line `payable in a notice of demand under section 30 shall be paid within 5 [thirty days] of the service of the`
  line `notice at the place and to the person mentioned in the notice:`
  line `Provided that, where the 4 [Assessing Officer] has any reason to believe that it will be detrimental to`
  line `revenue if the full period of 5 [thirty days] aforesaid is allowed, he may, with the previous approval of`
  line `the 6 [Joint Commissioner], direct that the sum specified in the notice of demand shall be paid within such`
  line `period being a period less than the period of 5 [thirty days] aforesaid, as may be specified by him in the`
  line `notice of demand.`
  line `( 2 ) If the amount specified in any notice of demand under section 30 is not paid within the period`
  line `limited under sub-section ( 1 ), the assessee shall be liable to pay simple interest at 7 [ 8 [one per cent.] for`
  line `every month or part of a month comprised in the period commencing from the day immediately following`
  line `the end of the period mentioned in sub-section ( 1 ) and ending with the day on which the amount is paid]:`
  line `Provided that, where as a result of an order under section 23, 9 [or section 23A,] or section 24, or`
  line `section 25, or section 26, or section 27, or section 29, or section 35 10 [or any order of the Wealth-tax`
  line `Settlement Commission under sub-section ( 4 ) of section 22D], the amount on which interest was payable`
  line `under this section had been reduced, the interest shall be reduced accordingly and the excess interest paid,`
  line `if any, shall be refunded:`
  line `1. Subs. by the Laccadive, Minicoy and Amindivi Islands (Alteration of Name) Adaptation of Laws Order, 1974, for “the`
  line `Laccadive, Minicoy and Amindivi Islands” (w.e.f. 1 -11-1973).`
  line `2. Ins. by the Punjab Reorganisation and Delhi High Court (Adaptation of Laws on Union Subjects) Order, 1968`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-11-1966).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 46 of 1964, s. 28, for sections 30, 31 and 32 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 148, ibid., for “thirty - five days” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 66, for “Deputy Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998). Earlier the quoted words were substituted by`
  line `Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Inspecting Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 148, for “fifteen per cent. per annum from the day commencing after the end of the period`
  line `mentioned in sub-section ( 1 )” (w.e.f. 1 -4- 1989). Earlier “fifteen per cent.” was substituted by Act 67 of 1984, s. 66, for “twelve`
  line `per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1984).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 54 of 2003, s. 20, for “one and one - fourth per cent.” (w.e.f. 8 -9-2003). Earlier the quoted words were substituted`
  line `by Act 14 of 2001, s. 99, for “one and one - half per cent.” (w.e.f. 1-6-2001).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 74 (w.e.f. 1-6-2000).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 148 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
