obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line 72
  line `1 [Provided further that in respect of any period commencing on or before the 31st day of March,`
  line `1989, and ending after that date, such interest shall, in respect of so much of such period as falls after that`
  line `date, be calculated at the rate of 2 [one per cent.] for every month or part of a month.]`
  line `3 [( 2A ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 2 ), the 4 [ 5 [Chief Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner] may] reduce or waive the amount of 6 [interest paid or payable by an assessee] under the`
  line `said sub-section if 7 [he is satisfied that] —`
  line `8 [( i ) payment of such amount has caused or would cause genuine hardship to the assessee;`
  line `( ii ) default in the payment of the amount on which interest has been paid or was payable under`
  line `the said sub-section was due to circumstances beyond the control of the assessee; and]`
  line `( iii ) the assessee has co-operated in any inquiry relating to the assessment or any proceeding for`
  line `the recovery of any amount due from him.]`
  line `( 3 ) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-section ( 2 ), on an application made by the`
  line `assessee before the expiry of the due date under sub-section ( 1 ), the 9 [Assessing Officer] may extend the`
  line `time for payment or allow payment by instalments, subject to such conditions as he may think fit to`
  line `impose in the circumstances of the case.`
  line `( 4 ) If the amount is not paid within the time limited under sub-section ( 1 ) or extended under sub-`
  line `section ( 3 ), as the case may be, at the place and to the person mentioned in the said notice, the assessee`
  line `shall be deemed to be in default.`
  line `( 5 ) If in a case where payment by instalments is allowed under sub-section ( 3 ), the assessee commits`
  line `default in paying any one of the instalments within the time fixed under that sub-section, the assessee`
  line `shall be deemed to be in default as to the whole of the amount then outstanding, and the other instalment`
  line `or instalments shall be deemed to have been due on the same date as the instalment actually in default.`
  line `( 6 ) Where an assessee has presented an appeal under section 23 10 [or section 23A], the 9 [Assessing`
  line `Officer] may, in his discretion, and subject to such conditions as he may think fit to impose in the`
  line `circumstances of the case, treat the assessee as not being in default in respect of the amount in dispute in`
  line `the appeal, even though the time for payment has expired, as long as such appeal remains undisposed of.`
  line `( 7 ) Where an assessee has been assessed in respect of assets located in a country outside India, the`
  line `laws of which prohibit or restrict the remittance of money to India, the 9 [Assessing Officer] shall not treat`
  line `the assessee as in default in respect of that part of the tax which is attributable to those assets, and shall`
  line `continue to treat the assessee as not in default in respect of that part of the tax until the prohibition or`
  line `restriction of remittance is removed.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 148 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 54 of 2003, s. 20, for “one and one - fourth per cent.” (w.e.f. 8 -9-2003). Earlier the quoted words were substituted`
  line `by Act 14 of 2001, s. 99, for “one and one - half per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2001).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 66 (w.e.f. 1-10-1984).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 88, for “the Board may” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1987).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 11 of 1987, s. 88, for “interest payable by an assessee” (w.r.e.f. 1 -10-1984).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 88, ibid., for “, on the recommendation made by the Commissioner in this behalf, it is satisfied that” (w.e.f. 1 -4-`
  line `1987).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 88, ibid., for clauses ( i ) and ( ii ) (w.r.e.f. 1-10-1984).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 74 (w.e.f. 1-6-2000).`
