  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  sourcePage 73
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line 73
  line `32. Mode of recovery. — The provisions contained in 1 [sections 221 to 227, 228A], 229, 231 and 232`
  line `of the Income-tax Act and the Second and Third Schedules to that Act and any rules made thereunder`
  line `shall, so far as may be, apply as if the said provisions were provisions of this Act and referred to`
  line `wealth-tax and sums imposed by way of penalty, fine and interest under this Act instead of to income-tax`
  line `and sums imposed by way of penalty, fine and interest under that Act 2 [and to the corresponding`
  line `wealth-tax authorities instead of to the income-tax authorities specified therein].`
  line `Explanation I. — Any reference to section 173 and sub-section ( 2 ) or sub-section ( 6 ) or sub-section ( 7 )`
  line `of section 220 of the Income-tax Act in the said provisions of that Act or the rules made thereunder shall`
  line `be construed as references to sub-section ( 7 ) of section 22 and sub-section ( 2 ) or sub-section ( 6 ) or`
  line `sub-section ( 7 ) of section 31 of this Act, respectively.`
  line `3 [ Explanation II. — The Chief Commissioner or Commissioner and the Tax Recovery Officer referred`
  line `to in the Income-tax Act shall be deemed to be the corresponding wealth-tax authorities for the purpose of`
  line `recovery of wealth-tax and sums imposed by way of penalty, fine and interest under this Act.]]`
  line `33. Liability of transferees of properties in certain cases. — ( 1 ) Where by reason of the provisions`
  line `contained in section 4, the value of any assets transferred to any of the persons mentioned in that section`
  line `have to be included in the net wealth of an individual, the person in whose name such assets stand shall,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in any law to the contrary, be liable, on the service of a notice of`
  line `demand by the 4 [Assessing Officer] in this behalf, to pay that portion of the tax assessed on the assessee`
  line `as is attributable to the value of the asset standing in his name as aforesaid:`
  line `Provided that where any such asset is held jointly by more than one person, they shall be jointly and`
  line `severally liable to pay the tax as is attributable to the value of the asset so jointly held.`
  line `( 2 ) Where any such person as is referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) defaults in making payment of any tax`
  line `demanded from him, he shall be deemed to be an assessee in default in respect of such sum, and all the`
  line `provisions of this Act relating to recovery shall apply accordingly.`
  line `34. [ Restrictions on registration of transfers of immovable property in certain cases.] — Omitted by`
  line `the Wealth-tax ( Amendment ) Act, 1964, s. 29 ( w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `5 [CHAPTER VIIA`
  line `R EFUNDS`
  line `34A. Refunds. — ( 1 ) Where, as a result of any order passed in appeal or other proceeding (including a`
  line `rectification proceeding) under this Act, refund of any amount becomes due to the assessee,`
  line `the 4 [Assessing Officer] shall, except as otherwise provided in this Act, refund the amount to the assessee`
  line `without his having to make any claim in that behalf:`
  line `6 [Provided that where, by the order aforesaid, —`
  line `( a ) an assessment is set aside or cancelled and an order of fresh assessment is directed to be`
  line `made, the refund, if any, shall become due only on the making of such fresh assessment;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 16 of 1972, s. 48, for “sections 221 to 227” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1972).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 149, for “and to Wealth -tax Officer and Commissioner of Wealth-tax instead of to Income-tax`
  line `Officer and Commissioner of Income- tax” (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 149, ibid., for Explanation II (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 127, ibid., for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 46 of 1964, s. 30 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `6. The proviso added by Act 4 of 1988, s. 150 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
