obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line 74
  line `( b ) the assessment is annulled, the refund shall become due only of the amount, if any, of the tax`
  line `paid in excess of the tax chargeable on the 1 [net wealth] returned by the assessee.]`
  line `2 [( 2 ) Where refund of any amount becomes due to the assessee as a result of an order under this Act`
  line `or under the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 16 after a return has been made under section 14 or`
  line `section 15 or in response to a notice under clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 4 ) of section 16 and the Assessing`
  line `Officer is of the opinion, having regard to the fact that —`
  line `( i ) a notice has been issued, or is likely to be issued, under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 16 in`
  line `respect of the said return; or`
  line `( ii ) the order is the subject-matter of an appeal or further proceeding; or`
  line `( iii ) any other proceeding under this Act is pending,`
  line `that the grant of the refund is likely to adversely affect the revenue, the Assessing Officer may, with the`
  line `previous approval of the Chief Commissioner or Commissioner, withhold the refund till such time as the`
  line `Chief Commissioner or Commissioner may determine.]`
  line `( 3 ) Where a refund is due to the assessee in pursuance of an order referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) and`
  line `the 3 [Assessing Officer] does not grant the refund within a period of six months from the date of such`
  line `order, the Central Government shall pay to the assessee simple interest at 4 [six per cent.] per annum on`
  line `the amount of refund due from the date immediately following the expiry of the period of six months`
  line `aforesaid to the date on which the refund is granted.`
  line `5 [( 3A ) Where the whole or any part of the refund referred to in sub-section ( 3 ) is due to the assessee`
  line `as a result of any amount having been paid by him after the 31st day of March, 1975, in pursuance of any`
  line `order of assessment or penalty and such amount or any part thereof having been found in appeal or other`
  line `proceeding under this Act to be in excess of the amount which such assessee is liable to pay as tax or`
  line `penalty, as the case may be, under this Act, the Central Government shall pay to such assessee simple`
  line `interest at the rate specified in sub-section ( 3 ) on the amount so found to be in excess from the date on`
  line `which such amount was paid to the date on which the refund is granted:`
  line `Provided that, where the amount so found to be in excess was paid in instalments, such interest shall`
  line `be payable on the amount of each such instalment or any part of such instalment, which was in excess,`
  line `from the date on which such instalment was paid to the date on which the refund is granted:`
  line `Provided further that no interest under this sub-section shall be payable for a period of one month`
  line `from the date of the passing of the order in appeal or other proceeding:`
  line `Provided also that, where any interest is payable to an assessee under this sub-section, no interest`
  line `under sub-section ( 3 ) shall be payable to him in respect of the amount so found to be in excess.]`
  line `( 4 ) Where a refund is withheld under the provisions of sub-section ( 2 ), the Central Government shall`
  line `pay interest at the aforesaid rate on the amount of refund ultimately determined to be due as a result of the`
  line `appeal or further proceeding for the period commencing after the expiry of six months from the date of`
  line `the order referred to in that sub-section to the date the refund is granted.`
  line `6 [( 4A ) The provisions of sub-sections ( 3 ), ( 3A ) and ( 4 ) shall not apply in respect of any assessment for`
  line `the assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1989, or any subsequent assessment year.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 73, for “total income” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 36 of 1989, s. 29, for sub-section ( 2 ) (w.r.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 54 of 2003, s. 21, for “eight per cent.” (w.e.f. 8 -9-2003).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 97 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 150 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
