obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line 75
  line `( 4B ) ( a ) 1 [Where refund of any amount becomes due to the assessee under this Act,] he shall, subject`
  line `to the provisions of this sub-section, be entitled to receive, in addition to the said amount, simple interest`
  line `thereon calculated at the rate of 2 [one-half 3 *** per cent.] for every month or part of a month comprised in`
  line `the period or periods from the date or, as the case may be, dates of payment of the tax or penalty to the`
  line `date on which the refund is granted.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this clause, “ date of payment of the tax or penalty ” means the date`
  line `on and from which the amount of tax or penalty specified in the notice of demand issued under section 30`
  line `is paid in excess of such demand.`
  line `( b ) If the proceedings resulting in the refund are delayed for reasons attributable to the assessee,`
  line `whether wholly or in part, period of the delay so attributable to him shall be excluded from the period for`
  line `which interest is payable and where any question arises as to the period to be excluded, it shall be decided`
  line `by the Chief Commissioner or Commissioner whose decision thereon shall be final.`
  line `( c ) Where as a result of an order under 4 [sub-section ( 3 ) or sub-section ( 5 ) of section 16 or] section 17`
  line `or section 23 5 [or section 23A] or section 24 or section 25 or section 27 or section 29 or section 35 or any`
  line `order of the Wealth-tax Settlement Commission under sub-section ( 4 ) of section 22D, the amount on`
  line `which interest was payable under clause ( a ) has been increased or reduced, as the case may be, the`
  line `interest shall be increased or reduced accordingly and, in a case where the interest is reduced, the`
  line `Assessing Officer shall serve on the assessee a notice of demand in the prescribed form specifying the`
  line `amount of the excess interest paid and requiring him to pay such amount; and such notice of demand shall`
  line `be deemed to be a notice under section 30 and the provisions of this Act shall apply accordingly.`
  line `( d ) The provisions of this sub-section shall apply in respect of assessments for the assessment year`
  line `commencing on the 1st day of April, 1989, and subsequent assessment years.]`
  line `( 5 ) Where under any of the provisions of this Act, a refund is found to be due to any person, the`
  line `6 [Assessing Officer], 7 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] 8 [, Commissioner (Appeals)] or 9 [Chief`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner], as the case may be, may, in lieu of payment of the refund, set off the`
  line `amount to be refunded or any part of that amount, against the sum, if any, remaining payable under this`
  line `Act by the person to whom the refund is due, after giving an intimation in writing to such person of the`
  line `action proposed to be taken under this section. ]`
  line `10 [ CHAPTER VIIB`
  line `R EGISTERED VALUERS`
  line `34AA. Appearance by registered valuers. — Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, any`
  line `assessee who is entitled to or required to attend before any wealth-tax authority or the Appellate Tribunal`
  line `in connection with any matter relating to the valuation of any asset, except where he is required under this`
  line `Act to attend in person, may attend by a registered valuer.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 73, for “Where, in pursuance of any order passed under this Act, t he refund of any amount becomes`
  line `due to the assessee” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 54 of 2003, s. 21, for “two - third per cent.” (w.e.f. 8 -9-2003). Earlier the quoted words were substituted by Act 20`
  line `of 2002, s. 114, for “three fourth per cent.” (w.e.f. 1-6- 2002) which were earlier substituted by Act 14 of 2001, s. 100, for “one`
  line `per cent.” (w.e.f. 1 -6-2001).`
  line `3. The words “and a half per cent.” omitted by Act 49 of 1991, s. 80 (w.e.f. 1 -10-1991).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 73 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 75 (w.e.f. 1-6-2000).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `7. Subs. by s. 127, ibid., for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 45 of 1972, s. 14 (w.e.f. 15-11-1972).`
