obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line 76
  line `34AB. Registration of valuers. — ( 1 ) The 1 [Chief Commissioner or Director General] shall maintain`
  line `a register to be called the Register of Valuers in which shall be entered the names and addresses of`
  line `persons registered under sub-section ( 2 ) as valuers.`
  line `( 2 ) Any person who possesses the qualifications prescribed in this behalf may apply to the 1 [Chief`
  line `Commissioner or Director General] in the prescribed form for being registered as a valuer under this`
  line `section:`
  line `Provided that different qualifications may be prescribed for valuers of different classes of assets.`
  line `( 3 ) Every application under sub-section ( 2 ) shall be verified in the prescribed manner, shall be`
  line `accompanied by such fees as may be prescribed and shall contain a declaration to the effect that the`
  line `applicant will —`
  line `( i ) make an impartial and true valuation of any asset which he may be required to value;`
  line `( ii ) furnish a report of such valuation in the prescribed form;`
  line `( iii ) charge fees at a rate not exceeding the rate or rates prescribed in this behalf;`
  line `( iv ) not undertake valuation of any asset in which he has a direct or indirect interest.`
  line `( 4 ) The report of valuation of any asset by a registered valuer shall be in the prescribed form and be`
  line `verified in the prescribed manner.`
  line `34AC. Restrictions on practice as registered valuer. — ( 1 ) No person, either alone, or in partnership`
  line `with any other person, shall practise, describe himself or hold himself out as a registered valuer for the`
  line `purposes of this Act or permit himself to be so described or held out unless he is registered as a valuer or,`
  line `as the case may be, unless he and all his partners are so registered under this Chapter.`
  line `( 2 ) No company or other body corporate shall practise, describe itself or hold itself out as registered`
  line `valuers for the purposes of this Act or permit itself to be so described or held out.`
  line `2 [ 34ACC. Furnishing of particulars in certain cases. — Where any person who is registered as a`
  line `valuer under section 34AB or who has made an application for registration as a valuer under that section`
  line `is, at any time thereafter, —`
  line `( a ) convicted of any offence and sentenced to a term of imprisonment; or`
  line `( b ) in a case where he is a member of any association or institution established in India having as`
  line `its object the control, supervision, regulation or encouragement of the profession of architecture,`
  line `accountancy, or company secretaries or such other profession as the Board may specify in this behalf`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, found guilty of misconduct in his professional capacity, by`
  line `such association or institution,`
  line `he shall immediately after such conviction or, as the case may be, finding, intimate the particulars thereof`
  line `3 [to the Chief Commissioner or Director General].]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 58, for “Board” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1988).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 68 (w.e.f. 1-10-1984).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 59, for “to the Board” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1988).`
