obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line 77
  line `34AD. Removal from register of names of valuers and restoration. — ( 1 ) The 1 [Chief`
  line `Commissioner or Director General] may remove the name of any person from the register of valuers`
  line `where 2 [he is satisfied], after giving that person a reasonable opportunity of being heard and after such`
  line `further inquiry, if any, as 3 [he thinks fit] to make, —`
  line `( i ) that his name has been entered in the register by error or on account of misrepresentation or`
  line `suppression of a material fact;`
  line `( ii ) that he has been convicted of any offence and sentenced to a term of imprisonment or has`
  line `been guilty of misconduct in his professional capacity which, in the opinion of the 1 [Chief`
  line `Commissioner or Director General], renders him unfit to be kept in the register.`
  line `( 2 ) The 1 [Chief Commissioner or Director General] may, on application and on sufficient cause being`
  line `shown, restore to the register the name of any person removed therefrom.`
  line `4 [( 3 ) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ), the Chief Commissioner or`
  line `Director General shall, once in three years review the performance of all the registered valuers and may`
  line `remove the name of any person from the Register of Valuers where he is satisfied, after giving that person`
  line `a reasonable opportunity of being heard and after such further inquiry, if any, as he thinks fit to make, that`
  line `his performance is such that his name should not remain on the Register of Valuers.`
  line `( 4 ) The Chief Commissioner or Director General may himself conduct the inquiry referred to in sub-`
  line `section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 3 ) or appoint an Inquiry Officer not below the rank of a Commissioner to`
  line `conduct such inquiry, and for the purposes of such inquiry, the Chief Commissioner or Director General`
  line `and the Inquiry Officer so appointed shall have the same powers as are vested in a court under the Code`
  line `of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908 ), when trying a suit in respect of the following matters, namely: —`
  line `( a ) discovery and inspection;`
  line `( b ) enforcing the attendance of any person including any officer of a banking company and`
  line `examining him on oath;`
  line `( c ) compelling the production of books of account and other documents;`
  line `( d ) issuing commission.] ]`
  line `5 [ 34AE. Existing registered valuers to apply afresh. — ( 1 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `this Chapter, every person whose name is included in the Register of Valuers immediately before the 1st`
  line `day of June, 1988, shall, if he intends to continue to be registered under this Act, make an application`
  line `under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 34AB within a period of three months from that date, for being registered`
  line `afresh as a valuer under this Chapter and the provisions of sub-section ( 3 ) of that section and the rules`
  line `made thereunder shall be applicable in respect of the verification of the application, the fees that shall`
  line `accompany such application and the declaration to be made by the applicant.`
  line `( 2 ) The provisions of this Chapter regarding the registration of a person as a valuer and other matters`
  line `shall, so far as may be, apply to every application made under sub-section ( 1 ).`
  line `( 3 ) Every application pending before the Board immediately before the 1st day of June,1988, shall be`
  line `deemed to be an application received by the Chief Commissioner or Director General under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ).]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 60, for “Board” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 60, ibid., for “it is satisfied” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 60, ibid., for “it thinks fit” (w.e.f. 1 -6-1988).`
  line `4. Ins. by s. 60, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-1988).`
  line `5. Ins. by s. 61, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-1988).`
