obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line 78
  line `CHAPTER VIII`
  line `M ISCELLANEOUS`
  line `1 [ 34B. Transfers to defraud revenue to be void. — ( 1 ) Where, during the pendency of any`
  line `proceeding under this Act or after the completion thereof, but before the service of notice under rule 2 of`
  line `the Second Schedule to the Income-tax Act as made applicable to this Act by section 32, any assessee`
  line `creates a charge on, or parts with (by way of sale, mortgage, gift, exchange or any other mode of transfer`
  line `whatsoever) the possession of, any of his assets in favour of any other person, such charge or transfer`
  line `shall be void as against any claim in respect of any tax or any other sum payable by the assessee as a`
  line `result of the completion of the said proceeding or otherwise:`
  line `Provided that such charge or transfer shall not be void, if it is made —`
  line `( i ) for adequate consideration and without notice of the pendency of such proceeding or, as the`
  line `case may be, without notice of such tax or other sum payable by the assessee; or`
  line `( ii ) with the previous permission of the 2 [Assessing Officer].`
  line `( 2 ) This section applies to cases where the amount of tax or other sum payable or likely to be payable`
  line `exceeds five thousand rupees and the assets charged or transferred exceed ten thousand rupees in value.`
  line `Explanation. — In this section, “ assets ” means land, building, machinery, plant, shares, securities and`
  line `fixed deposits in banks to the extent to which any of the assets aforesaid does not form part of the stock-`
  line `in-trade of the business of the assessee.`
  line `34C. Provisional attachment to protect revenue in certain cases. — ( 1 ) Where, during the`
  line `pendency of any proceeding for the assessment of net wealth or for the assessment or reassessment of net`
  line `wealth which has escaped assessment, the 2 [Assessing Officer] is of the opinion that for the purpose of`
  line `protecting the interests of the revenue it is necessary so to do, he may, with the previous approval of the`
  line `3 [Chief Commissioner or Commissioner], by order in writing, attach provisionally any property belonging`
  line `to the assessee in the manner provided in the Second Schedule to the Income-tax Act as made applicable`
  line `to this Act by section 32.`
  line `4 [ Explanation. — For the purposes of this sub-section, the proceedings under sub-section ( 5 ) of section`
  line `37A shall be deemed to be proceedings for the assessment of any net wealth or for the assessment or`
  line `reassessment of any net wealth which has escaped assessment.]`
  line `( 2 ) Every such provisional attachment shall cease to have effect after the expiry of a period of six`
  line `months from the date of the order made under sub-section ( 1 ):`
  line `Provided that the 3 [Chief Commissioner or Commissioner] may, for reasons to be recorded in`
  line `writing, extend the aforesaid period by such further period or periods as he thinks fit, so however, that the`
  line `total period of extension shall not in any case exceed two years:`
  line `4 [Provided further that where an application for settlement under section 22C is made, the period`
  line `commencing from the date on which such application is made and ending with the date on which an order`
  line `under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 22D is made shall be excluded from the period specified in the preceding`
  line proviso.]]
  line `1. Subs. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 98, for section 34B (w.e.f. 1-10-1975). Earlier section 34B was inserted by Act 46 of 1964, s. 31`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 127, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 62 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
