obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line 79
  line `1 [ 35. Rectification of mistakes. — ( 1 ) With a view to rectifying any mistake apparent from the`
  line `record —`
  line `( a ) the 2 [Assessing Officer] may amend any order of assessment or of refund or any other order`
  line `passed by him;`
  line `3 [( aa ) a wealth-tax authority may amend any intimation or deemed intimation under sub-section`
  line `( 1 ) of section 16;]`
  line `4 [ 5 [( aaa )] the Valuation Officer may amend any order passed by him under section 16A;]`
  line `6 [( b ) the 7 [Joint Director] or 8 [Joint Commissioner] or Director or Commissioner or Deputy`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals) or Commissioner (Appeals) may amend any order passed by him under`
  line `section 18A;]`
  line `9 [( c ) the Deputy Commissioner (Appeals) or Commissioner (Appeals) may amend any order`
  line `passed by him under section 23 10 [or section 23A];`
  line `( d ) the Commissioner may amend any order passed by him under section 25;`
  line `( e ) the Appellate Tribunal may amend any order passed by it under section 24.]`
  line `( 2 ) Where the amount of tax, penalty or interest determined as a result of the first appeal or revision`
  line `against the order referred to in sub-clause ( iii ) of clause ( m ) of section 2 11 [, as it existed immediately`
  line `before its amendment by the Finance Act, 1992,] is paid within six months of the date of the order passed`
  line `in such appeal or revision, the 2 [Assessing Officer] may, notwithstanding anything to the contrary in this`
  line `Act, rectify the assessment by allowing a deduction to the extent the tax, penalty or interest so paid stood`
  line `disallowed therein as if such rectification were a rectification of a mistake apparent from the record.`
  line `( 3 ) Subject to the other provisions of this section, the authority concerned —`
  line `( a ) may make an amendment under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ) of its own motion;`
  line `( b ) shall make such amendment for rectifying any such mistake which has been brought to its`
  line `notice by the assessee, and where the authority concerned is the 12 [Valuation Officer or the 13 [Deputy`
  line `Commissioner (Appeals)]] 14 [or the Commissioner (Appeals)] or the Appellate Tribunal, by`
  line `the 2 [Assessing Officer] also.`
  line `( 4 ) An amendment, which has the effect of enhancing an assessment or reducing a refund or`
  line `otherwise increasing the liability of the assessee, shall not be made under this section unless the authority`
  line `concerned has given notice to the assessee of its intention so to do and has allowed the assessee a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 46 of 1964, s. 32, for section 35 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 27 of 1999, s. 97, for clause ( aa ) (w.e.f. 1-6-1999). Earlier clause (aa) was inserted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 151`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 45 of 1972, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-1-1973).`
  line `5. Clause ( aa ) renumbered as clause ( aaa ) therof by Act 4 of 1988, s. 151 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 160, for clause ( b ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 66, for “Deputy Director” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 66, ibid., for “Deputy Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 160, for clauses ( d ) and ( e ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Earlier clause ( c ) was omitted by Act 41 of 1975, s. 99`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1976).`
  line `10. Ins. by Act 10 of 2000, s. 76 (w.e.f. 1-6-2000). Earlier it was omitted by Act 3 of 1989, s. 74 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `11. Ins. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 97 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `12. Subs. by Act 45 of 1972, s. 15, for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -1-1973).`
  line `13. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `14. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
