obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line 80
  line `( 5 ) Where an amendment is made under this section, an order shall be passed in writing by the`
  line `wealth-tax authority concerned or the Tribunal, as the case may be.`
  line `( 6 ) Where any such amendment has the effect of enhancing the assessment or reducing a refund`
  line `already made, the 1 [Assessing Officer] shall serve on the assessee a notice of demand in the prescribed`
  line `form specifying the sum payable and such notice of demand shall be deemed to be issued under section`
  line `30 and the provisions of this Act shall apply accordingly.`
  line `2 [( 6A ) Where any amendment made by the Valuation Officer under clause ( aa ) of sub-section ( 1 ) has`
  line `the effect of enhancing the valuation of any asset, he shall send a copy of his order to the 1 [Assessing`
  line `Officer] who shall thereafter proceed to amend the order of assessment in conformity with the order of the`
  line `Valuation Officer and the provisions of sub-section ( 6 ) shall apply accordingly.]`
  line `( 7 ) No amendment under this section shall be made after the expiry of four years —`
  line `( a ) in the case of an amendment under sub-section ( 2 ), 3 [from the end of the financial year in`
  line `which the order was passed in the first appeal or revision] referred to in that sub-section; and`
  line `( b ) in any other case, 4 [from the end of the financial year in which the order sought to be amended`
  line `was passed].`
  line `2 [( 7A ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 7 ), where the valuation of any asset has`
  line `been enhanced by the Valuation Officer under this section, the consequential amendment to the order of`
  line `assessment may be made by the 1 [Assessing Officer] at any time before the expiry of one year from the`
  line `date of the order of the Valuation Officer under this section.]`
  line `( 8 ) Where any matter has been considered and decided in a proceeding by way of an appeal or`
  line `revision relating to an order referred to in sub-section ( 1 ), the authority passing such order may,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, amend the order under`
  line `this section in relation to any matter other than the matter which has been so considered and decided.]`
  line `5 [ 35A. Wilful attempt to evade tax, etc. — ( 1 ) If a person wilfully attempts in any manner`
  line `whatsoever to evade any tax, penalty or interest chargeable or imposable under this Act, he shall, without`
  line `prejudice to any penalty that may be imposable on him under any other provision of this Act, be`
  line `punishable, —`
  line `( i ) in a case where the amount sought to be evaded exceeds one hundred thousand rupees, with`
  line `rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than six months but which may extend to`
  line `seven years and with fine;`
  line `( ii ) in any other case, with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three`
  line `months but which may extend to three years and with fine.`
  line `( 2 ) If a person wilfully attempts in any manner whatsoever to evade the payment of any tax, penalty`
  line `or interest under this Act, he shall, without prejudice to any penalty that may be imposable on him under`
  line `any other provisions of this Act, be punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be`
  line `less than three months but which may extend to three years and shall, in the discretion of the court, also`
  line `be liable to fine.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 45 of 1972, s. 15 (w.e.f. 1-1-1973).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 69, for “from the date of the order passed in the first appeal or revision” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1984).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 69, ibid., for “from the date of the order sought to be amended” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1984).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 100 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
