  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  sourcePage 81
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line 81
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, a wilful attempt to evade any tax, penalty or interest`
  line `chargeable or imposable under this Act or the payment thereof shall include a case where any person —`
  line `( a ) has in his possession or control any books of account or other documents (being books of`
  line `account or other documents relevant to any proceeding under this Act) containing a false entry or`
  line `statement, or`
  line `( b ) makes, or causes to be made, any false entry or statement in such books of account or other`
  line `documents, or`
  line `( c ) wilfully omits, or causes to be omitted, any relevant entry or statement in such books of`
  line `account or other documents, or`
  line `( d ) causes any other circumstances to exist which will have the effect of enabling such person to`
  line `evade any tax, penalty or interest chargeable or imposable under this Act or the payment thereof.`
  line `35B. Failure to furnish returns of net wealth. — If a person wilfully fails to furnish in due time the`
  line `return of his net wealth which he is required to furnish under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 14 or by notice`
  line `given under sub-section ( 2 ) of section 14 or under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 17, he shall be punishable, —`
  line `( i ) in a case where the amount of tax, which would have been evaded if the failure had not been`
  line `discovered, exceeds one hundred thousand rupees, with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall`
  line `not be less than six months but which may extend to seven years and with fine;`
  line `( ii ) in any other case, with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three`
  line `months but which may extend to three years and with fine:`
  line `Provided that a person shall not be proceeded against under this section for failure to furnish in due`
  line `time the return of net wealth under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 14 —`
  line `( i ) for any assessment year commencing prior to the 1st day of April, 1975; or`
  line `( ii ) for any assessment year commencing on or after the 1st day of April, 1975, if —`
  line `( a ) the return is furnished by him before the expiry of the assessment year; or`
  line `( b ) the tax payable by him on his net wealth determined on regular assessment does not`
  line `exceed three thousand rupees.`
  line `35C. Failure to produce accounts, records, etc. — If a person wilfully fails to produce, or cause to`
  line `be produced, on or before the date specified in any notice under sub-section ( 4 ) of section 16, such`
  line `accounts, records and documents as are referred to in the notice, he shall be punishable with rigorous`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year or with fine equal to a sum calculated at a rate`
  line `which shall not be less than four rupees or more than ten rupees for every day during which the default`
  line `continues, or with both.`
  line `35D. False statement in verification, etc., made under certain provisions of the Act. — If a person`
  line `makes a statement in any verification under this Act (other than under section 34AB) or under any rule`
  line `made thereunder, or delivers an account or statement which is false, and which he either knows or`
  line `believes to be false, or does not believe to be true, he shall be punishable, —`
  line `( i ) in a case where the amount of tax which would have been evaded if the statement or account`
  line `had been accepted as true, exceeds one hundred thousand rupees, with rigorous imprisonment for a`
  line `term which shall not be less than six months but which may extend to seven years and with fine;`
  line `( ii ) in any other case, with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three`
  line `months but which may extend to three years and with fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-82
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Page 82`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  sourcePage 82
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line 82
  line `35E. False statement in verification mentioned in section 34AB. — If a person makes a statement in`
  line `a verification mentioned in section 34AB which is false, and which he either knows or believes to be`
  line `false, or does not believe to be true, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to six months or with fine or with both.`
  line `1 [ 35EE. Failure to furnish particulars under section 34ACC. — If a person referred to in section`
  line `34ACC fails 2 *** to intimate to the Board the particulars of conviction or finding referred to in the said`
  line `section, he shall be punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years and`
  line `shall also be liable to fine]:`
  line `3 [Provided that no person shall be punishable under this section if he proves that there was reasonable`
  line `cause or excuse for the said failure.]`
  line `4 [ 35EEE. Contravention of order made under second proviso to sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section`
  line `( 3A ) of section 37A. — If a person contravenes any order referred to in the second proviso to sub-section`
  line `( 1 ) or sub-section ( 3A ) of section 37A, he shall be punishable with rigorous imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to two years and with fine.]`
  line `35F. Abetment of false return, etc. — If a person abets or induces in any manner another person to`
  line `make and deliver an account, statement or declaration relating to any net wealth chargeable to tax which`
  line `is false and which he either knows to be false or does not believe to be true or to commit an offence under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 35A, he shall be punishable, —`
  line `( i ) in a case where the amount of tax, penalty or interest, which would have been evaded, if the`
  line `declaration, account or statement had been accepted as true, or which is wilfully attempted to be`
  line `evaded, exceeds one hundred thousand rupees, with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not`
  line `be less than six months but which may extend to seven years and with fine;`
  line `( ii ) in any other case, with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three`
  line `months but which may extend to three years and with fine.`
  line `35G. Punishment for second and subsequent offences. — If any person convicted of an offence`
  line `under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 35A or section 35B or section 35D or section 35F is again convicted of`
  line `an offence under any of the aforesaid provisions, he shall be punishable for the second and for every`
  line `subsequent offence with rigorous imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than six months but`
  line `which may extend to seven years and with fine.`
  line `5 [ 35GA. Power of Commissioner to grant immunity from prosecution. — ( 1 ) A person may make`
  line `an application to the Commissioner for granting immunity from prosecution, if he has made an`
  line `application for settlement under section 22C and the proceedings for settlement have abated under section`
  line 22HA.
  line `( 2 ) The application to the Commissioner under sub-section ( 1 ) shall not be made after institution of`
  line `the prosecution proceedings after abatement.`
  line `( 3 ) The Commissioner may, subject to such conditions as he may think fit to impose, grant to the`
  line `person immunity from prosecution for any offence under this Act, if he is satisfied that the person has,`
  line `after the abatement, co-operated with the wealth-tax authority in the proceedings before him and has`
  line `made a full and true disclosure of his net wealth and the manner in which such net wealth has been`
  line `derived:`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 67 of 1984, s. 70 (w.e.f. 1-10-1984).`
  line `2. The words “, without reasonable cause or excuse,” omitted by Act 46 of 1986, s. 38 (w.e.f. 10 -9-1986).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 38, ibid. (w.e.f. 10-9-1986).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 56 (w.e.f. 1-4-1990).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 65 (w.e.f. 1-4-2008).`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-83
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Page 83`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  sourcePage 83
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line 83
  line `Provided that where the application for settlement under section 22C had been made before the 1st`
  line `day of June, 2007, the Commissioner may grant immunity from prosecution for any offence under this`
  line `Act or under the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) or under any other Central Act for the time being in`
  line force.
  line `( 4 ) The immunity granted to a person under sub-section ( 3 ) shall stand withdrawn, if such person fails`
  line `to comply with any condition subject to which the immunity was granted and thereupon the provisions of`
  line `this Act shall apply as if such immunity had not been granted.`
  line `( 5 ) The immunity granted to a person under sub-section ( 3 ) may, at any time, be withdrawn by the`
  line `Commissioner, if he is satisfied that such person had, in the course of any proceedings, after abatement,`
  line `concealed any particulars, material to the assessment, from the wealth-tax authority or had given false`
  line `evidence, and thereupon such person may be tried for the offence with respect to which the immunity was`
  line `granted or for any other offence of which he appears to have been guilty in connection with the`
  line proceedings.]
  line `35H. Offences by Hindu undivided families. — ( 1 ) Where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a Hindu undivided family, the karta thereof shall be deemed to be guilty of the offence and`
  line `shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render the karta liable to any punishment if`
  line `he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he had exercised all due`
  line `diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a Hindu undivided family and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the`
  line `consent or connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any member thereof, such`
  line `member shall also be deemed to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and`
  line `punished accordingly.`
  line `1 [ 35HA. Offences by companies. — ( 1 ) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was`
  line `responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company as well as the company shall`
  line `be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished`
  line `accordingly:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he had exercised`
  line `all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section ( 1 ), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall be deemed to be guilty of`
  line `that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line `2 [( 3 ) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a person, being a company and such`
  line `offence is punishable with imprisonment and fine, then, without prejudice to the provisions contained in`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ), such company shall be punished with fine and every person, referred to`
  line `in sub-section ( 1 ) or the director, manager, secretary or other officer of the company referred to in sub-`
  line `section ( 2 ), shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished in accordance with the provisions of this`
  line Act.]
  line `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 98 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 23 of 2004, s. 65 (w.e.f. 1-10-2004).`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-84
  sectionNo (84)
