  title `Page 84`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  sourcePage 84
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line 84
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this section, —`
  line `( a ) “company” means a body corporate, and includes —`
  line `( i ) a firm; and`
  line `( ii ) an association of persons or a body of individuals whether incorporated or not; and`
  line `( b ) “director”, in relation to, —`
  line `( i ) a firm, means a partner in a firm;`
  line `( ii ) any association of persons or a body of individuals, means any member controlling the`
  line `affairs thereof.]`
  line `1 [ 35-I. Prosecutions to be with the previous sanction of certain wealth-tax authorities and their`
  line `power to compound offences. — 2 [( 1 ) A person shall not be proceeded against for an offence under this`
  line `Act except with the previous sanction of the Commissioner or Commissioner (Appeals):`
  line `Provided that the Chief Commissioner or, as the case may be, Director General may issue such`
  line `instructions or directions to the aforesaid wealth-tax authorities as he may deem fit for institution of`
  line `proceedings under this sub-section.`
  line `( 2 ) Any such offence may, either before or after the institution of proceedings, be compounded by the`
  line `Chief Commissioner or a Director General.]`
  line `3 [ Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the power of the Board to issue`
  line `orders, instructions or directions under this Act shall include and shall be deemed always to have included`
  line `the power to issue instructions or directions (including instructions or directions to obtain the previous`
  line `approval of the Board) to other wealth-tax authorities for the proper composition of offences under this`
  line section.]]
  line `35J. Certain offences to be non-cognizable. — Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), an offence punishable under section 35A or section 35B or section`
  line `35D or section 35F shall be deemed to be non-cognizable within the meaning of that Code.`
  line `35K. Bar on prosecution and on inadmissibility of evidence in certain circumstances. — ( 1 ) A`
  line `person shall not be proceeded against for an offence under section 35A or section 35D in relation to the`
  line `assessment for 4 [an assessment year] in respect of which the penalty imposed or imposable on him under`
  line `clause ( iii ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 18 has been reduced or waived by an order under section 18B.`
  line `( 2 ) Where any proceeding for prosecution has been taken against any person under this Act, any`
  line `statement made or account or other document produced by such person before 5 [any Wealth-tax authority`
  line `(not being an Inspector of Income-tax)] shall not be inadmissible as evidence for the purpose of such`
  line `proceedings merely on the ground that such statement was made or such account or other document was`
  line `produced in the belief that the penalty imposable would be reduced or waived under section 18B or that`
  line `the offence in respect of which such proceeding was taken would be compounded.`
  line `35L. Jurisdiction of courts. — No court inferior to that of a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Magistrate`
  line `of the first class shall try any offence under this Act.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 63, for section 35-I (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 81, for sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 1-10-1991).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 81, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1991).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 57, for “the assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1988, or any earlier assessment`
  line `year” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989). Earlier the quoted words were substituted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 152 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 152, for “any of the Wealth -tax authorities spe cified in sections 8, 9, 9A, 10, 10A, and 11”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-85
  sectionNo (85)
