  title `Page 85`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  sourcePage 85
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line 85
  line `35M. Section 360 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973, and the Probation of Offenders Act,`
  line `1958, not to apply. — Nothing contained in section 360 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of`
  line `1974), or in the Probation of Offenders Act, 1958 (20 of 1958), shall apply to a person convicted of an`
  line `offence under this Act unless that person is under eighteen years of age.`
  line `35N. Presumption as to books of account, etc., in certain cases. — ( 1 ) Where during the course of`
  line `any search made under section 37A, any books of account or other documents, articles or things including`
  line `money have been found in the possession or control of any person and such books of account or other`
  line `documents are tendered, or such articles or things including money are relied upon, by the prosecution in`
  line `evidence against such person or against such person and the person referred to in section 35F for an`
  line `offence under this Act, the provisions of sub-section ( 5 ) of section 37A shall, so far as may be, apply in`
  line `relation to such books of account or other documents, articles or things including money.`
  line `( 2 ) Where —`
  line `( i ) any books of account or other documents, taken into custody, from the possession or control of`
  line `any person by any officer or authority under clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 37B,`
  line `are delivered to the requisitioning officer under sub-section ( 2 ) of that section; or`
  line `( ii ) any note or inventory of any articles or things including money taken into custody, from the`
  line `possession of any person, by any officer or authority under clause ( c ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section`
  line `37B, is furnished to the requisitioning officer under sub-section ( 2 ) of that section,`
  line `and such books of account or other documents are tendered, or such note or inventory is relied upon, by`
  line `the prosecution in evidence against such person or against such person and the person referred to in`
  line `section 35F for an offence under this Act, the provisions of sub-section ( 5 ) of section 37A shall, so far as`
  line `may be, apply in relation to such books of account or other documents or, as the case may be, the articles`
  line `or things including money, covered by such note or inventory.`
  line `1 [ 35-O. Presumption as to culpable mental state. — ( 1 ) In any prosecution for any offence under`
  line `this Act which requires a culpable mental state on the part of the accused, the court shall presume the`
  line `existence of such mental state but it shall be a defence for the accused to prove the fact that he had no`
  line `such mental state with respect to the act charged as an offence in that prosecution.`
  line `Explanation. — In this sub-section, “ culpable mental state ” includes intention, motive or knowledge of`
  line `a fact, or belief in, or reason to believe, a fact.`
  line `( 2 ) For the purposes of this section, a fact is said to be proved only when the court believes it to exist`
  line `beyond reasonable doubt and not merely when its existence is established by a preponderance of`
  line probability.]]
  line `2 [ 36. Proof of entries in records or documents. — Entries in the records or other documents in the`
  line `custody of a wealth-tax authority shall be admitted in evidence in any proceedings for the prosecution of`
  line `any person for an offence under this Act, and all such entries may be proved either by the production of`
  line `the records or other documents in the custody of the wealth-tax authority containing such entries or by the`
  line `production of a copy of the entries certified by the wealth-tax authority having custody of the records or`
  line `other documents under its signature and stating that it is a true copy of the original entries and that such`
  line `original entries are contained in the records or other documents in its custody.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 46 of 1986, s. 39 (w.e.f. 10-9-1986).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 75 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989). Earlier it was omitted by Act 41 of 1975, s. 101 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
