obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line 86
  line `1 [ 36A. Power to tender immunity from prosecution. — ( 1 ) The Central Government may, if it is of`
  line `opinion (the reasons for such opinion being recorded in writing) that with a view to obtaining the`
  line `evidence of any person appearing to have been directly or indirectly concerned in or privy to the`
  line `concealment of particulars of net wealth or to the evasion of payment of tax on net wealth, it is necessary`
  line `or expedient so to do, tender to such person immunity from prosecution for any offence under this Act or`
  line `under the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) or under any other Central Act for the time being in force and`
  line `also from the imposition of any penalty under this Act on condition of his making a full and true`
  line `disclosure of the whole circumstances relating to the concealment of particulars of net wealth or evasion`
  line `of payment of tax on net wealth.`
  line `( 2 ) A tender of immunity made to, and accepted by, the person concerned shall, to the extent to which`
  line `the immunity extends, render him immune from prosecution for any offence in respect of which the`
  line `tender was made or from the imposition of any penalty under this Act.`
  line `( 3 ) If it appears to the Central Government that any person to whom immunity has been tendered`
  line `under this section has not complied with the condition on which the tender was made or is wilfully`
  line `concealing anything or is giving false evidence, the Central Government may record a finding to that`
  line `effect, and thereupon the immunity shall be deemed to have been withdrawn, and any such person may be`
  line `tried for the offence in respect of which the tender of immunity was made or for any other offence of`
  line `which he appears to have been guilty in connection with the same matter and shall also become liable to`
  line `the imposition of any penalty under this Act to which he would otherwise have been liable.]`
  line `2 [ 37. Power to take evidence on oath, etc. — ( 1 ) 3 [The 4 [Assessing Officer], Valuation`
  line `Officer,] 5 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)], 6 [Commissioner (Appeals),] 7 [Chief Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner] and the Appellate Tribunal shall, for the purposes of this Act, have the same powers as`
  line `are vested in a court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), when trying a suit in respect of`
  line `the following matters, namely: —`
  line `( a ) discovery and inspection;`
  line `( b ) enforcing the attendance of any person, including any officer of a banking company and`
  line `examining him on oath;`
  line `( c ) compelling the production of books of account and other documents; and`
  line `( d ) issuing commissions.`
  line `8 [( 1A ) If the Director General or Director or 9 [Joint Director] or 10 [Assistant Director or Deputy`
  line `Director], or the authorised officer referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) of section 37A before he takes action`
  line `under clauses ( i ) to ( vi ) of that sub-section, has reason to suspect that any net wealth has been concealed,`
  line `or is likely to be concealed, by any person or class of persons within his jurisdiction, then, for the`
  line `purposes of making any inquiry or investigation relating thereto, it shall be competent for him to exercise`
  line `the powers conferred under sub-section ( 1 ) on the wealth-tax authorities referred to in that sub-section,`
  line `notwithstanding that no proceedings with respect to such person or class of persons are pending before`
  line `him or any other wealth-tax authority.]`
  line `11 * * * * *`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 46 of 1964, s. 34 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 35, ibid., for section 37 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 45 of 1972, s. 17, for “The Wealth - Tax Officer,” (w.e.f. 1 -1-1973).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 127, ibid., for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 64 (w.e.f. 1-6-1988).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 66, for “Deputy Director” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `10. Subs. by s. 66, ibid., for “Assistant Director” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `11. Sub-section ( 2 ) omitted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 153 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
