obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line 87
  line `( 3 ) Subject to any rules made in this behalf, any authority referred to in sub-section ( 1 ) 1 [or sub-`
  line `section ( 1A )] may impound and retain in its custody for such period as it thinks fit any books of account`
  line `or other documents produced before it in any proceeding under this Act:`
  line `Provided that 2 [a 3 [Assessing Officer] or a Valuation Officer] 1 [or an 4 [Assistant Director or Deputy`
  line `Director]] shall not —`
  line `( a ) impound any books of account or other documents without recording his reasons for so doing,`
  line or
  line `( b ) retain in his custody any such books or documents for a period exceeding fifteen days`
  line `(exclusive of holidays) without obtaining the approval of 5 [the Chief Commissioner or Director`
  line `General or Commissioner or Director therefor, as the case may be].`
  line `( 4 ) Any proceeding under this Act before a wealth-tax authority or the Tribunal shall be deemed to be`
  line `a judicial proceeding within the meaning of sections 193 and 228, and for the purposes of section 196 of`
  line `the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).]`
  line `6 [37A. Power of search and seizure. — ( 1 ) Where the 7 [Director General or Director] or the 8 [Chief`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner] or any such 9 [Joint Director] or 10 [Joint Commissioner] as may be`
  line `empowered in this behalf by the Board, in consequence of information in his possession, has reason to`
  line `believe that —`
  line `( a ) any person to whom a notice under sub-section ( 4 ) of section 16 or a summons under section`
  line `37 was issued to produce, or cause to be produced, any books of account or other documents, has`
  line `omitted or failed to produce, or cause to be produced, such books of account or other documents as`
  line `required by such notice or summons, or`
  line `( b ) any person to whom a notice or summons as aforesaid has been or might be issued will not, or`
  line `would not, produce, or cause to be produced, any books of account or other documents which will be`
  line `useful for, or relevant to, any proceeding under this Act, or`
  line `( c ) any person is in possession of 11 [any money, bullion, jewellery or other valuable article or`
  line `thing] disproportionate to his known assets, particulars of which will be useful for, or relevant to, any`
  line `proceeding under this Act,`
  line `then, —`
  line `( A ) the 7 [Director-General or Director] or the 8 [Chief Commissioner or Commissioner], as the`
  line `case may be, may authorise any 9 [Joint Director], 10 [Joint Commissioner], 12 [Assistant Director or`
  line `Deputy Director], 13 [ 14 [Assistant Commissioner or Deputy Commissioner] or Income-tax Officer], or`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 153 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 45 of 1972, s. 17, for “a Wealth - Tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -1-1973).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 6 6, for “Assistant Director” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 64, for “the Chief Commissioner or Commissioner therefor” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988). Earlier the words`
  line `“Chief Commissioner or Commissioner” were substituted by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 102, for section 37A (w.e.f. 1-10-1975). Earlier section 37A was inserted by Act 46 of 1964, s. 36`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Director of Inspection” (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 127, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 66, for “Deputy Director” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998). Earlier the quoted words were substituted by Act 4 of`
  line `1988, s. 127, for “Deputy Director of Inspection” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `10. Subs. by s. 66, ibid., for “Deputy Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998). Earlier the quoted words were substituted by Act 4 of`
  line `1988, s. 127, for “Inspecting Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `11. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 154, for “any articles or things including money” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `12. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 66, for “Assistant Director” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998). Earlier the quoted words were substituted by`
  line `Act 4 of 1988, s. 154, for “Assistant Director of Inspection” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `13. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 154, for “or Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `14. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 66, for “Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
