obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line 88
  line `( B ) such 1 [Joint Director] or 2 [Joint Commissioner] may authorise any 3 [ 4 [Assistant Director or`
  line `Deputy Director]] or 5 [ 6 [Assistant Commissioner or Deputy Commissioner] or Income-tax Officer],`
  line `(the officer so authorised in all cases being hereafter in this section referred to as the authorised officer)`
  line `to —`
  line `( i ) enter and search any building, place, vessel, vehicle or aircraft where he has reason to suspect`
  line `that such books of account or other documents, 7 [money, bullion, jewellery or other valuable article`
  line `or thing] are kept;`
  line `( ii ) search any person who has got out of, or is about to get into, or is in, the building, place,`
  line `vessel, vehicle or aircraft, if the authorised officer has reason to suspect that such person has secreted`
  line `about his person any such books of account or other documents, 7 [money, bullion, jewellery or other`
  line `valuable article or thing];`
  line `( iii ) break open the lock of any door, box, locker, safe, almirah or other receptacle for exercising`
  line `the powers conferred by clause ( i ) where the keys thereof are not available;`
  line `8 [( iv ) seize any such books of account, other documents, money, bullion, jewellery or other`
  line `valuable article or thing found as a result of such search;]`
  line `( v ) place marks of identification on any such books of account or other documents or make, or`
  line `cause to be made, extracts or copies therefrom;`
  line `( vi ) make a note or an inventory of 9 [any money, bullion, jewellery or other valuable article or`
  line `thing] found which, in his opinion, will be useful for, or relevant to, any proceeding under this Act:`
  line `Provided that where any building, place, vessel, vehicle or aircraft referred to in clause ( i ) is`
  line `within the area of jurisdiction of any 10 [Chief Commissioner or Commissioner] but such 10 [Chief`
  line `Commissioner or Commissioner] has no jurisdiction over the person referred to in clause ( a ) or clause`
  line `( b ) or clause ( c ) of this sub-section, then, notwithstanding anything contained in 11 [section 8], it shall`
  line `be competent for him to exercise the powers under this sub-section in all cases where he has reason to`
  line `believe that any delay in getting the authorisation from the 10 [Chief Commissioner or Commissioner]`
  line `having jurisdiction over such person may be prejudicial to the interests of the revenue:`
  line `12 [Provided further that where it is not possible or practicable to take physical possession of any`
  line `valuable article or thing and remove it to a safe place due to its volume, weight or other physical`
  line `characteristics or due to its being of a dangerous nature, the authorised officer may serve an order on`
  line `the owner or the person who is in immediate possession or control thereof that he shall not remove,`
  line `part with or otherwise deal with it except with the previous permission of such authorised officer and`
  line `such action of the authorised officer shall be deemed to be seizure of such valuable article or thing`
  line `under clause ( iv ) of this sub-section.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 66, for “Deputy Director” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998). Earlier the quoted words were substituted by Act 4 of`
  line `1988, s. 127, for “Deputy Director of Inspection” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 66, ibid., for “Deputy Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998). Earlier the quoted words were substituted by Act 4 of`
  line `1988, s. 127, for “Inspecting Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 154, for “Assistant Director of Inspection” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 66, for “Assistant Director” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `5. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 154, for “or Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 66, for “Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 154, for “articles or things including money” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `8. Subs. by s. 154, ibid., for clause ( iv ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `9. Subs. by s. 154, ibid., for “any articles or things including money” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `10. Subs. by s. 127, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `11. Subs. by s. 154, ibid., for “section 10” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `12. Ins. by s. 154, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
