obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line 89
  line `( 2 ) Where any 1 [Chief Commissioner or Commissioner], in consequence of information in his`
  line `possession, has reason to suspect that any books of account or other documents, 2 [money, bullion,`
  line `jewellery or other valuable article or thing] in respect of which an officer has been authorised by`
  line `the 3 [Director General or Director] or any other 1 [Chief Commissioner or Commissioner] or any such`
  line `4 [Joint Director] or 5 [Joint Commissioner] as may be empowered in this behalf by the Board to take`
  line `action under clauses ( i ) to ( vi ) of sub-section ( 1 ) are kept in any building, place, vessel, vehicle or aircraft`
  line `not mentioned in the authorisation under sub-section ( 1 ), such 1 [Chief Commissioner or Commissioner]`
  line `may, notwithstanding anything contained in 6 [section 8], authorise the said officer to take action under`
  line `any of the clauses aforesaid in respect of such building, place, vessel, vehicle or aircraft.`
  line `( 3 ) The authorised officer may requisition the services of any police officer or of any officer of the`
  line `Central Government, or of both, to assist him for all or any of the purposes specified in sub-section ( 1 ) or`
  line `sub-section ( 2 ) and it shall be the duty of every such officer to comply with such requisition.`
  line `7 [( 3A ) The authorised officer may, where it is not practicable to seize any books of account, other`
  line `documents, money, bullion, jewellery or other valuable article or thing, for reasons other than those`
  line `mentioned in the second proviso to sub-section ( 1 ), serve an order on the owner or the person who is in`
  line `immediate possession or control thereof that he shall not remove, part with or otherwise deal with it`
  line `except with the previous permission of such officer and such officer may take such steps as may be`
  line `necessary for ensuring compliance with this sub-section.`
  line `Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that serving of an order as aforesaid`
  line `under this sub-section shall not be deemed to be seizure of such books of account, other documents,`
  line `money, bullion, jewellery or other valuable article or thing under clause ( iv ) of sub-section ( 1 ).]`
  line `( 4 ) The authorised officer may, during the course of the search or seizure, examine on oath any`
  line `person who is found to be in possession or control of any books of account or other documents, articles or`
  line `things including money and any statement made by such person during such examination may thereafter`
  line `be used in evidence in any proceeding under this Act.`
  line `7 [ Explanation. — For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that the examination of any person`
  line `under this sub-section may be not merely in respect of any books of account, other documents or assets`
  line `found as a result of the search, but also in respect of matters relevant for the purposes of any investigation`
  line `connected with any proceedings under this Act.]`
  line `( 5 ) Where any books of account or other documents, articles or things including money are found in`
  line `the possession or control of any person in the course of a search, it may be presumed that —`
  line `( i ) such books of account or other documents, articles or things including money belong to such`
  line person;
  line `( ii ) the contents of such books of account or other documents are true; and`
  line `( iii ) the signature and every other part of such books of account or other documents which`
  line `purport to be in the handwriting of any particular person or which may reasonably be assumed to`
  line `have been signed by, or to be in the handwriting of, any particular person, are in that person ’ s`
  line `handwriting, and in the case of a document stamped, executed or attested, that it was duly stamped`
  line `and executed or attested by the person by whom it purports to have been so executed or attested.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 154, ibid., for “articles or things including money” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 127, ibid., for “Director of Inspection” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 66, for “Deputy Director” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998). Earlier the quoted words were substituted by Act 4 of`
  line `1988, s. 127, for “Deputy Director of Inspection” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 66, ibid., for “Deputy Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998). Earlier the quoted words were substituted by Act 4 of`
  line `1988, s. 127, for “Inspecting Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 154, for “section 10” (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `7. Ins. by s. 154, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-90
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 90
  title `Page 90`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  sourcePage 90
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line 90
  line `1 [( 5A ) Where any money, bullion, jewellery or other valuable article or thing (hereafter in this section`
  line `and in sections 37B and 37C referred to as the assets) is seized under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ),`
  line `the Assessing Officer, after affording a reasonable opportunity to the person concerned of being heard`
  line `and making such inquiry as may be prescribed, shall, within one hundred and twenty days of the seizure,`
  line `make an order, with the previous approval of the 2 [Joint Commissioner], —`
  line `( i ) estimating the undisclosed net wealth in a summary manner to the best of his judgment on the`
  line `basis of such materials as are available with him;`
  line `( ii ) calculating the amount of tax on the net wealth so estimated in accordance with the provisions`
  line `of this Act;`
  line `( iii ) determining the amount of interest payable and the amount of any penalty imposable in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act, as if the order had been the order of regular assessment;`
  line `( iv ) specifying the amount that will be required to satisfy any existing liability under this Act in`
  line `respect of which such person is in default or is deemed to be in default, and retain in his custody such`
  line `assets or part thereof as are in his opinion sufficient to satisfy the aggregate of the amounts referred it`
  line `in clauses ( ii ), ( iii ) and ( iv ) and forthwith release the remaining portion, if any, of the assets to the`
  line `person from whose custody they were seized:`
  line `Provided that where a person has paid or made satisfactory arrangements for payment of all the`
  line `amounts referred to in clauses ( ii ), ( iii ) and ( iv ) or any part thereof, the Assessing Officer, may with`
  line `the previous approval of the Chief Commissioner or Commissioner release the assets or such part`
  line `thereof as he may deem fit in the circumstances of the case.`
  line `( 5B ) The assets retained under sub-section ( 5A ) may be dealt with in accordance with the provisions`
  line `of section 37C.`
  line `( 5C ) If the Assessing Officer is satisfied that the seized assets or any part thereof were held by such`
  line `person for or on behalf of any other person, the Assessing Officer may proceed under sub-section ( 5A )`
  line `against such other person and all the provisions of this section shall apply accordingly.]`
  line `( 6 ) The books of account or other documents, seized under sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ), shall`
  line `not be retained by the authorised officer for a period exceeding one hundred and eighty days from the`
  line `date of the seizure unless the reasons for retaining the same are recorded by him in writing and the`
  line `approval of the 3 [Chief Commissioner or Commissioner] for such retention is obtained:`
  line `Provided that the 3 [Chief Commissioner or Commissioner] shall not authorise the retention of the`
  line `books of account or other documents for a period exceeding thirty days after all the proceedings under`
  line `this Act in respect of the years for which the books of account or other documents are relevant are`
  line completed.
  line `1 [( 6A ) An order under sub-section ( 3A ) shall not be in force for a period exceeding sixty days from`
  line `the date of the order, except where the authorised officer, for reasons to be recorded in writing by him,`
  line `extends the period of operation of the order beyond sixty days, after obtaining the approval of`
  line `the 4 [Director or, as the case may be, Commissioner] for such extension:`
  line `Provided that the 4 [Director or, as the case may be, Commissioner] shall not approve the extension of`
  line `the period for any period beyond the expiry of thirty days after the completion of the proceedings under`
  line `this Act in respect of the years for which the books of account, other documents, money, bullion,`
  line `jewellery or other valuable articles or things are relevant.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 154 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 66, for “Deputy Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 49 of 1991, s. 82, for “Chief Commissioner or Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1991).`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-91
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 91
  title `Page 91`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  sourcePage 91
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line 91
  line `( 7 ) The person from whose custody any books of account or other documents are seized under`
  line `sub-section ( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ) may make copies thereof, or take extracts therefrom, in the presence of`
  line `the authorised officer or any other person empowered by him in this behalf at such place and time as the`
  line `authorised officer may appoint in this behalf.`
  line `( 8 ) Where the authorised officer has no jurisdiction over the person referred to in clause ( a ) or clause`
  line `( b ) or clause ( c ) of sub-section ( 1 ), the books of account or other documents seized under that sub-section`
  line `shall be handed over by the authorised officer to the 1 [Assessing Officer] having jurisdiction over such`
  line `person within a period of fifteen days of such seizure and thereupon the powers exercisable by the`
  line `authorised officer under sub-section ( 6 ) or sub-section ( 7 ) shall be exercisable by such 1 [Assessing`
  line Officer].
  line `( 9 ) If a person legally entitled to the books of account or other documents seized under sub-section`
  line `( 1 ) or sub-section ( 2 ) objects for any reason to the approval given by the 2 [Chief Commissioner or`
  line `Commissioner] under sub-section ( 6 ), he may make an application to the Board stating therein the reasons`
  line `for such objection and requesting for the return of the books of account or other documents.`
  line `3 [( 9A ) If any person objects for any reason to an order made under sub-section ( 5A ), he may, within`
  line `thirty days from the date of such order, make an application to the Chief Commissioner or Commissioner`
  line `stating therein the reasons for such objection and requesting for appropriate relief in the matter.]`
  line `4 [( 10 ) On receipt of the application under sub-section ( 9 ), the Board, or on receipt of the application`
  line `under sub-section ( 9A ), the Chief Commissioner or Commissioner, may, after giving the applicant an`
  line `opportunity of being heard, pass such orders as it or he thinks fit.]`
  line `( 11 ) The provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), relating to searches shall`
  line `apply, so far as may be, to searches under this section.`
  line `( 12 ) The Board may make rules in relation to searches or seizure under this section; and in particular`
  line `and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide for the procedure`
  line `to be followed by the authorised officer —`
  line `( i ) for obtaining ingress into any building, place, vessel, vehicle or aircraft to be searched where`
  line `free ingress thereto is not available;`
  line `( ii ) for ensuring the safe custody of any books of account or other documents seized.`
  line `3 [ Explanation 1. — In computing the period referred to in sub-section ( 5A ) for the purposes of that`
  line `sub-section, any period during which any proceeding under this section is stayed by an order or injunction`
  line `of any court shall be excluded.`
  line `Explanation 2. — In this section, the word “ proceeding ” means any proceeding in respect of any year`
  line `under this Act which may be pending on the date on which a search is authorised under this section or`
  line `which may have been completed on or before such date and includes also proceedings under this Act`
  line `which may be commenced after such date in respect of any year.]`
  line `37B. Power to requisition books of account, etc. — ( 1 ) Where the 5 [Director General or Director] or`
  line `the 2 [Chief Commissioner or Commissioner], in consequence of information in his possession, has reason`
  line `to believe that —`
  line `( a ) any person to whom a notice under sub-section ( 4 ) of section 16 or a summons under section`
  line `37 was issued to produce, or cause to be produced, any books of account or other documents has`
  line `omitted or failed to produce, or cause to be produced, such books of account or other documents as`
  line `required by such notice or summons and the said books of account or other documents have been`
  line `taken into custosdy by any officer or authority under any other law for the time being in force, or`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 127, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 154, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `4. Subs. by s. 154, ibid., for sub-section ( 10 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 127, ibid., for “Director of Inspection” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-92
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 92
  title `Page 92`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  sourcePage 92
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line 92
  line `( b ) any books of account or other documents will be useful for, or relevant to, any proceeding`
  line `under this Act and any person to whom a notice or summons as aforesaid has been or might be issued`
  line `will not, or would not, produce or cause to be produced such books of account or other documents on`
  line `the return of such books of account or other documents by any officer or authority by whom or which`
  line `such books of account or other documents have been taken into custody under any other law for the`
  line `time being in force, or`
  line `( c ) 1 [any assets] disproportionate to the known assets of any person, particulars of which will be`
  line `useful for, or relevant to, any proceeding under this Act, have been taken into custody by any officer`
  line `or authority under any other law for the time being in force, from the possession of such person,`
  line `then, the 2 [Director-General or Director] or the 3 [Chief Commissioner or Commissioner] may authorise`
  line `any 4 [Joint Director], 5 [Joint Commissioner], 6 [Assistant Director or Deputy Director] 7 [, 8 [Assistant`
  line `Commissioner or Deputy Commissioner] or Income-tax Officer] (hereafter in this section referred to as`
  line `the requisitioning officer) to require such officer or authority 9 [to deliver such books of account, other`
  line `documents, or assets to the requisitioning officer].`
  line `( 2 ) On a requisition being made under sub-section ( 1 ), 9 [the officer or authority referred to in`
  line `clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) or clause ( c ), as the case may be, of that sub-section shall deliver the books of`
  line `account, other documents, or assets to the requisitioning officer either forthwith or when such officer or`
  line `authority is of the opinion that it is no longer necessary to retain the same in his or its custody.]`
  line `10 [( 3 ) Where any books of account, other documents, or assets have been delivered to the`
  line `requisitioning officer, the provisions of sub-sections ( 5 ) to ( 12 ) (both inclusive) of section 37A and`
  line `section 37C shall, so far as may be, apply as if such books of account, other documents, or assets had`
  line `been seized under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 37A by the requisitioning officer from the custody of the`
  line `person referred to in clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) or clause ( c ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of this section and as if for the`
  line `words “the authorised officer” occurring in sub -sections ( 5 ) to ( 12 ) aforesaid, the words “the`
  line `requisitioning officer” were substituted.] ]`
  line `11 [ 37C. Application of retained assets. — ( 1 ) The assets retained under sub-section ( 5A ) of section`
  line `37A may be dealt with in the following manner, namely: —`
  line `( i ) the amount of the existing liability referred to in clause ( iv ) of the said sub-section and the`
  line `amount of the liability determined on completion of the regular assessment or reassessment for all the`
  line `assessment years for which the net wealth referred to in clause ( i ) of that sub-section is assessable to`
  line `tax (including any penalty levied or interest payable, in connection with such assessment or`
  line `reassessment) and in respect of which the assessee is in default or is deemed to be in default may be`
  line `recovered out of such assets;`
  line `( ii ) if the assets consist solely of money, or partly of money and partly of other assets, the`
  line `Assessing Officer may apply such money in the discharge of the liabilities referred to in clause ( i ) and`
  line `the assessee shall be discharged of such liabilities to the extent of the money so applied;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 155, for “any articles or things including money” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 127, ibid., for “Director of Inspection” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 127, ibid., for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 66, for “Deputy Director” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998). Earlier the quoted words were substituted`
  line `by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Deputy Director of Inspection” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 66, ibid., for “Deputy Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998). Earlier the quoted words were substituted by`
  line `Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Inspecting Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `6. Subs. by s. 66, ibid., for “Assistant Director” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998). Earlier the quoted words were substituted by Act 4 of 1988,`
  line `s. 154, for “Assistant Director of Inspection” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 155, for “or Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 21 of 1998, s. 66, for “Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -10-1998).`
  line `9. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 155, for clauses ( i ) and ( ii ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `10. Subs. by s. 155, ibid., for sub-section ( 3 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `11. Ins. by s. 156, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
