  title `Page 93`
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  sourcePage 93
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line 93
  line `( iii ) the assets other than money may also be applied for the discharge of any such liability`
  line `referred to in clause ( i ) as remains undischarged and for this purpose such assets shall be deemed to`
  line `be under distraint as if such distraint was effected by the Assessing Officer under authorisation from`
  line `the Chief Commissioner or Commissioner under sub-section ( 5 ) of section 226 of the Income-tax Act`
  line `as made applicable to this Act by section 32, and the Assessing Officer may recover the amount of`
  line `such liabilities by the sale of such assets and such sale shall be effected in the manner laid down in`
  line `the Third Schedule to the Income-tax Act as made applicable to this Act by section 32.`
  line `( 2 ) Nothing contained in sub-section ( 1 ) shall preclude the recovery of the amount of liabilities`
  line `aforesaid by any other mode laid down in this Act.`
  line `( 3 ) Any assets or proceeds thereof which remain after the liabilities referred to in clause ( i ) of sub-`
  line `section ( 1 ) are discharged shall be forthwith made over or paid to the persons from whose custody the`
  line `assets were seized.`
  line `( 4 ) ( a ) The Central Government shall pay simple interest at the rate of fifteen per cent per annum on`
  line `the amount by which the aggregate of the money retained under section 37A and of the proceeds, if any,`
  line `of the assets sold towards the discharge of the existing liability referred to in clause ( iv ) of sub-section`
  line `( 5A ) of that section exceeds the aggregate of the amounts required to meet the liabilities referred to in`
  line `clause ( i ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of this section.`
  line `( b ) Such interest shall run from the date immediately following the expiry of the period of six months`
  line `from the date of the order under sub-section ( 5A ) of section 37A to the date of the regular assessment or`
  line `reassessment referred to in clause ( i ) of sub-section (1) or, as the case may be, to the date of the last of`
  line `such assessments or reassessments.]`
  line `38. Information, returns and statements. — 1 [Where, for the purposes of this Act], it appears`
  line `necessary for 2 [any wealth-tax authority] to obtain any statement or information from any individual,`
  line `company 3 [(including a banking company)], firm, Hindu undivided family or other person, 2 [such`
  line `wealth-tax authority] may serve a notice requiring such individual, company, firm, Hindu undivided`
  line `family or other person, on or before a date to be therein specified, to furnish such statement or`
  line `information on the points specified in the notice, and the individual or the principal officer concerned or`
  line `the manager of the Hindu undivided family, as the case may be, shall, notwithstanding anything in any`
  line `law to the contrary, be bound to furnish such statement or information to 2 [such wealth-tax authority]:`
  line `Provided that no legal practitioner shall be bound to furnish any statement or information under this`
  line `section based on any professional communications made to him otherwise than as permitted by section`
  line `126 of the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872).`
  line `4 [ 38A. Powers of Valuation Officer, etc. — ( 1 ) For the purposes of this Act, a Valuation Officer or`
  line `any overseer, surveyor or assessor authorised by him in this behalf may, subject to any rules made in this`
  line `behalf and at such reasonable times as may be prescribed, —`
  line `( a ) enter any land within the limits of the area assigned to the Valuation Officer, or`
  line `( b ) enter any land, building or other place belonging to or occupied by any person in connection`
  line `with whose assessment a reference has been made under section 16A to the Valuation Officer, or`
  line `( c ) inspect any asset in respect of which a reference under section 16A has been made to the`
  line `Valuation Officer,`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 157, for “Where, for the purposes of determining the wealth - tax payable by any person”`
  line `(w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 157, ibid., for “the Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 157, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `4. Ins. by Act 45 of 1972, s. 18 (w.e.f. 15-11-1972).`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-94
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 94
  title `Page 94`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  sourcePage 94
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line 94
  line `and require any person in charge of, or in occupation or possession of, such land, building or other place`
  line `or asset to afford him the necessary facility to survey or inspect such land, building or other place or asset`
  line `or estimate its value or inspect any books of account, document or record which may be relevant for the`
  line `valuation of such land, building or other place or asset and gather other particulars relating to such land,`
  line `building or other place or asset:`
  line `Provided that no Valuation Officer, overseer, surveyor or assessor shall enter any building or place`
  line `referred to in clause ( b ), or inspect any asset referred to in clause ( c ) (unless with the consent of the`
  line `person in charge of, or in occupation or possession of, such building, place or asset) without previously`
  line `giving t o such person at least two days’ notice in writing of his intention to do so.`
  line `( 2 ) If a person who, under sub-section ( 1 ), is required to afford any facility to the Valuation Officer or`
  line `the overseer, surveyor or assessor, either refuses or evades to afford such facility, the Valuation Officer`
  line `shall have all the powers under sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 2 ) of section 37 for enforcing compliance of the`
  line `requirements made.]`
  line `39. Effect of transfer of authorities on pending proceedings. — Whenever in respect of any`
  line `proceeding under this Act any wealth-tax authority ceases to exercise jurisdiction and is succeeded by`
  line `another who has and exercises such jurisdiction, the authority so succeeding may continue the proceeding`
  line `from the stage at which the proceeding was left by his predecessor:`
  line `1 [Provided that the assessee concerned may demand that before the proceeding is so continued the`
  line `previous proceeding or any part thereof be reopened or that before any order of assessment is passed`
  line `against him, he be reheard.]`
  line `40. Computation of periods of limitation. — In computing the period of limitation prescribed for an`
  line `appeal under this Act or for an application under section 27, the day on which the order complained of`
  line `was made and the time requisite for obtaining a copy of such order shall be excluded.`
  line `41. Service of notice. — ( 1 ) A notice or a requisition under this Act may be served on the person`
  line `therein named either by post or as if it were a summons issued by a court under the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908).`
  line `( 2 ) Any such notice or requisition may, in the case of a firm or a Hindu undivided family, be`
  line `addressed to any member of the firm or to the manager or any adult male member of the family, 2 [and in`
  line `the case of a company or any other association of persons] be addressed to the principal officer thereof.`
  line `3 [( 3 ) After a finding of total partition has been recorded by the 4 [Assessing Officer] under section 20`
  line `in respect of any Hindu family, notices under this Act in respect of the net wealth of the Hindu family`
  line `shall be served on the person who was the last manager of the Hindu family, or, if such person is dead,`
  line `then on all surviving adults who were members of the Hindu family immediately before the partition.]`
  line `5 [( 4 ) Where an association of persons referred to in section 21AA is dissolved, notices under this Act`
  line `in respect of any matter relating to the association may be served on any person who was a member of the`
  line `association immediately before its dissolution.]`
  line `6 [ 42. Notice deemed to be valid in certain circumstances. — Where an assessee has appeared in any`
  line `proceeding or cooperated in any inquiry relating to an assessment or reassessment, it shall be deemed that`
  line `any notice under any provision of this Act, which is required to be served upon him, has been duly served`
  line `upon him in time in accordance with the provisions of this Act and such assessee shall be precluded from`
  line `taking any objection in any proceeding or inquiry under this Act that the notice was —`
  line `( a ) not served upon him; or`
  line `1. Added by Act 46 of 1964, s. 37 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 76, for “and in the case of any other association of persons” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 46 of 1964, s. 38 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1989).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 16 of 1981, s. 31 (w.e.f. 1-4-1981).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 66 (w.e.f. 1-4-2008). Earlier section 42 was omitted by Act 5 of 1964, s. 50 (w.e.f. 1-4-1964).`
