obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line 95
  line `( b ) not served upon him in time; or`
  line `( c ) served upon him in an improper manner:`
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall apply where the assessee has raised such`
  line `objection before the completion of such assessment or reassessment.]`
  line `1 [ 42A. Publication of information respecting assessees. — ( 1 ) If the Central Government is of`
  line `opinion that it is necessary or expedient in the public interest to publish the names of any assessees and`
  line `any other particulars relating to any proceedings 2 [or prosecutions] under this Act in respect of such`
  line `assessees, it may cause to be published such names and particulars in such manner as it thinks fit.]`
  line `3 [( 2 ) No publication under this section shall be made in relation to any penalty imposed under this Act`
  line `until the time for presenting an appeal to the 4 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] 5 [or, as the case may be,`
  line `the Commissioner (Appeals)] has expired without an appeal having been presented or the appeal, if`
  line `presented, has been disposed of.]`
  line `6 [ Explanation. — In the case of a company, the names of the directors, secretaries and treasurers, or`
  line `managers of the company, may also be published if, in the opinion of the Central Government, the`
  line `circumstances of the case justify it.]`
  line `42B. Disclosure of information respecting assessees. — Where a person makes an application to the`
  line `7 [Chief Commissioner or Commissioner] in the prescribed form for any information relating to any`
  line `assessee in respect of any assessment made under this Act, the 7 [Chief Commissioner or Commissioner]`
  line `may, if he is satisfied that it is in the public interest so to do, furnish or cause to be furnished the`
  line `information asked for in respect of that assessment only and his decision in this behalf shall be final and`
  line `shall not be called in question in any court of law.]`
  line `2 [ 42C. Return of wealth, etc., not to be invalid on certain grounds. — No return of wealth,`
  line `assessment, notice, summons or other proceeding furnished or made or issued or taken or purported to`
  line `have been furnished or made or issued or taken in pursuance of any of the provisions of this Act shall be`
  line `invalid or shall be deemed to be invalid merely by reason of any mistake, defect or omission in such`
  line `return of wealth, assessment, notice, summons or other proceeding if such return of wealth, assessment,`
  line `notice, summons or other proceeding is in substance and effect in conformity with or according to the`
  line `intent and purpose of this Act.]`
  line `8 [ 42D. Presumption as to assets, books of account, etc. — 9 [( 1 )] Where any books of account or`
  line `other documents, articles or things including money are found in the possession or control of any person`
  line `in the course of a search under section 37A, it may, in any proceeding under this Act, be presumed that —`
  line `( i ) such books of account or other documents, articles or things including money belong to such`
  line person;
  line `( ii ) the contents of such books of account or other documents are true; and`
  line `( iii ) the signature and every other part of such books of account or other documents which`
  line `purport to be in the handwriting of any particular person or which may reasonably be assumed to`
  line `have been signed by, or to be in the handwriting of, any particular person, are in that person ’ s`
  line `handwriting, and in the case of a document stamped, executed or attested, that it was duly stamped`
  line `and executed or attested by the person by whom it purports to have been so executed or attested.]`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 1964, s. 50, for sections 42A and 42B (w.e.f. 1-4-1964). Earlier these sections were inserted by Act 28 of`
  line `1960, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-4-1960).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 103 (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 103, ibid., for sub-section ( 2 ) (w.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 77 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 22 of 2007, s. 93 (w.r.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `9. Section 42D renumbered as sub-section ( 1 ) thereof by Act 18 of 2008, s. 67 (w.r.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
