obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line 96
  line `1 [( 2 ) Where any books of account, other documents or assets have been delivered to the requisitioning`
  line `officer in accordance with the provisions of section 37B, then, the provisions of sub-section ( 1 ) shall`
  line `apply as if such books of account, other documents or assets which had been taken into custody from the`
  line `person referred to in clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) or clause ( c ), as the case may be, of sub-section ( 1 ) of section`
  line `37B, had been found in the possession or control of that person in the course of a search under section`
  line 37A.]
  line `43. Bar of jurisdiction. — No suit shall lie in any civil court to set aside or modify 2 [any proceeding`
  line `taken or order made] under this Act, and no prosecution, suit or other legal proceeding shall lie`
  line `against 3 [the Government or] any officer of the Government for anything in good faith done or intended`
  line `to be done under this Act.`
  line `4 [ 44. Appearance before wealth-tax authorities by authorised representatives. — ( 1 ) Any assessee`
  line `who is entitled to or required to attend before any wealth- tax authority or the Appellate Tribunal in`
  line `connection with any proceeding under this Act, except where he is required under this Act to attend in`
  line `person, may attend by a person who would be entitled to represent him before any income-tax authority`
  line `or the Appellate Tribunal under section 288 of the Income-tax Act.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything in sub-section ( 1 ) —`
  line `( i ) no person who has been convicted of an offence connected with any wealth-tax proceeding or`
  line `on whom a penalty has been imposed under this Act other than a penalty imposed on him under`
  line `clause ( i ) or clause ( ii ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 18 shall be qualified to represent an assessee`
  line `under sub-section ( 1 ) for such time as the 5 [Chief Commissioner or Commissioner] may by order`
  line determine;
  line `( ii ) if any person who is not a legal practitioner or a chartered accountant, is found guilty of`
  line `misconduct in connection with any wealth-tax proceeding by the prescribed authority, the prescribed`
  line `authority may direct that he shall thenceforth be disqualified to represent an assessee under sub-`
  line `section ( 1 );`
  line `( iii ) no person not qualified to represent an assessee under the Indian Income-tax Act, 1922 (11 of`
  line `1922), the Estate Duty Act, 1953 (34 of 1953), the Expenditure-tax Act, 1957 (29 of 1957), or the`
  line `Gift-tax Act, 1958 (18 of 1958), shall be entitled to appear on behalf of any assessee under this Act:`
  line `Provided that any order or direction under clause ( i ) or clause ( ii ) shall be subject to the following`
  line `conditions, namely: —`
  line `( a ) no such order or direction shall be made in respect of any person unless he has been given`
  line `a reasonable opportunity of being heard;`
  line `( b ) any person against whom any such order or direction is made may, within one month of`
  line `the making of the order or direction, appeal to the Board to have the order or direction cancelled;`
  line and
  line `( c ) no such order or direction shall take effect until the expiration of one month from the`
  line `making thereof, or, where an appeal has been preferred, until the disposal of the appeal.`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 18 of 2008, s. 67 (w.r.e.f. 1-10-1975).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 26 of 1988, s. 65, for “any order made” (w.r.e.f. 1-3-1988). Earlier the quoted words were substituted by Act 11`
  line `of 1987, s. 89, for “any assessment made” (w.r.e.f. 1 -3-1987).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 5 of 1964, s. 50 (w.e.f. 1-4-1964).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 46 of 1964, s. 39, for section 44 (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `5. Subs. b y Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
