obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line 97
  line `44A. Agreement for avoidance or relief of double taxation with respect to wealth-tax. — 1 [The`
  line `Central Government may enter into an agreement with the Government of any reciprocating country —`
  line `( a ) for the avoidance or relief of double taxation with respect to wealth-tax payable under this Act`
  line `and under the corresponding law in force in the reciprocating country, or`
  line `( b ) for exchange of information for the prevention of evasion or avoidance of wealth-tax`
  line `chargeable under this Act or under the corresponding law in force in that country or investigation of`
  line `cases of such evasion or avoidance, or`
  line `( c ) for recovery of tax under this Act and under the corresponding law in force in that country,`
  line `and may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make such provision as may be necessary for`
  line `implementing the agreement.]`
  line `Explanation. — The expression “ reciprocating country ” for the purposes of this Act means 2 [any`
  line `country outside India or any territory outside India] which the Central Government may, by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette, declare to be a reciprocating country.`
  line `44B. Countries with which no agreement exists. — Where the net wealth of any assessee includes`
  line `any foreign wealth and he proves that, in respect of such foreign wealth, he has paid in any country, with`
  line `which there is no reciprocal arrangement under section 44A for the relief or avoidance of double taxation,`
  line `a tax in respect of wealth, under the law in force in that country, he shall be entitled to the deduction from`
  line `the Indian wealth-tax payable by him of a sum calculated on such doubly taxed foreign wealth at the`
  line `Indian rate of tax or the rate of tax of the said country, whichever is the lower, or at the Indian rate of tax`
  line `if both the rates are equal.`
  line `Explanation. — In this section —`
  line `( 1 ) the expression “Indian wealth - tax” means wealth -tax charged in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this Act;`
  line `( 2 ) the expression “Indian rate of tax” means the rate determined by dividing the amount of`
  line `Indian wealth-tax after deduction of any relief due under the provisions of this Act but before the`
  line `deduction of any relief due under this section by the net wealth;`
  line `( 3 ) the expression “rate of tax of the said country” means any tax in respect of wealth, actually`
  line `paid in the said country, in accordance with the corresponding laws in force in the said country after`
  line `deduction of all relief due but before deduction of any relief due in the said country in respect of`
  line `double taxation, divided by the whole amount of the wealth assessed in the said country;`
  line `( 4 ) the expression “foreign wealth”, in relation to any assessee, means the value of all his assets`
  line `located in any country outside India as reduced by the value of his debts in that country.]`
  line `3 [ 44C. Rounding off of net wealth. — The amount of net wealth computed in accordance with the`
  line `foregoing provisions of this Act shall be rounded off to the nearest multiple of one hundred rupees and,`
  line `for this purpose, any part of a rupee consisting of paise shall be ignored and thereafter, if such amount`
  line `contains a part of one hundred rupees, then, if such part is fifty rupees or more, the amount shall be`
  line `increased to the next higher amount which is a multiple of one hundred and, if such part is less than fifty`
  line `rupees, the amount shall be reduced to the next lower amount which is a multiple of one hundred; and the`
  line `amount so rounded off shall be deemed to be the net wealth of the assessee for the purposes of this Act.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 16 of 1972, s. 49, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-4-1972).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 33 of 2009, s. 84, for “any country” (w.e.f. 1 -10-2009).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 42 of 1970, s. 65 (w.e.f. 1-4-1971).`
