obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line 98
  line `44D. Rounding off of tax, etc. — The amount of wealth-tax, interest, penalty, fine or any other sum`
  line `payable, and the amount of refund due, under the provisions of this Act, shall be rounded off to the`
  line `nearest rupee and, for this purpose, where such amount contains a part of a rupee consisting of paise,`
  line `then, if such part is fifty paise or more, it shall be increased to one rupee, and if such part is less than fifty`
  line `paise, it shall be ignored.]`
  line `45. Act not to apply in certain cases. — 1 [No tax shall be levied under this Act in respect of the net`
  line `wealth of — ]`
  line `2 * * * * *`
  line `( f ) any company registered under section 25 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956);`
  line `3 [( g ) any co-operative society;]`
  line `4 [( h ) any social club;]`
  line `5 [( i ) any political party.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of clause ( i ), “political party” shall have the meaning assigned to it in`
  line `the Explanation to section 13A of the Income-tax Act;]`
  line `6 [( j ) a Mutual Fund specified under clause ( 23D ) of section 10 of the Income-tax Act;]`
  line `7 [( k ) the Reserve Bank of India incorporated under the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of`
  line `1934).]`
  line `46. Power to make rules. — ( 1 ) The Board may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules`
  line `for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, rules made under this`
  line `section may provide for —`
  line `( a ) the manner in which the market value of any asset may be determined;`
  line `( b ) the form in which returns under this Act shall be made and the manner in which they shall be`
  line verified;
  line `8 [( ba ) the documents, statements, receipts, certificates, audit reports, reports of registered valuer`
  line `or any other documents which may not be furnished along with the return but shall be produced`
  line `before the Assessing Officer on demand under section 14A;`
  line `( bb ) the class or classes of persons who shall be required to furnish the return in electronic form;`
  line `the form and the manner in which the return in electronic form may be furnished; the documents,`
  line `statements, receipts, certificates, audit reports, reports of registered valuer or any other documents`
  line `which may not be furnished along with the return in electronic form and the computer resource or`
  line `electronic record to which such return may be transmitted under section 14B;]`
  line `( c ) the form in which appeals and applications under this Act may be made, and the manner in`
  line `which they shall be verified;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 16 of 1972, s. 50, for “The provisions of this Act shall not apply to — ” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1972).`
  line `2. Clauses ( a ) to ( e ) omitted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 99 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).]`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 16 of 1972, s. 50 (w.r.e.f. 1-4-1957).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 99, for clause ( h ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1993). Earlier clause ( h ) was inserted by Act 25 of 1975, s. 28`
  line `(w.r.e.f. 1-4-1957)`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 29 of 1978, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-4-1979).`
  line `6. Ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 158 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `7. Ins. by Act 23 of 2012, s. 118 (w.r.e.f. 1-4-1957).`
  line `8. Ins. by Act 17 of 2013, s. 63 (w.e.f. 1-6-2013).`
