obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line 99
  line `1 [( cc ) the circumstances in which, the conditions subject to which, and the manner in which, the`
  line `2 [Deputy Commissioner (Appeals)] 3 [or the Commissioner (Appeals)] may permit an appellant to`
  line `produce evidence which he did not produce or which he was not allowed to produce before`
  line `the 4 [Assessing Officer];]`
  line `( d ) the form of any notice of demand under this Act;`
  line `5 [( dd ) the procedure to be followed in calculating interest payable by assessees or interest payable`
  line `by the Government to assessees under any provision of this Act, including the rounding off of the`
  line `period for which such interest is to be calculated in cases where such period includes a fraction of a`
  line `month, and specifying the circumstances in which and the extent to which petty amounts of interest`
  line `payable by assessees may be ignored;]`
  line `6 [( e ) the areas within which Valuation Officers may exercise jurisdiction;`
  line `( ee ) the manner in which and the conditions subject to which Valuation Officers, overseers,`
  line `surveyors and assessors may exercise their powers under sub-section ( 1 ) of section 38A;]`
  line `( f ) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed for the purposes of this Act.`
  line `7 [( 3 ) The power to make rules conferred by this section shall include the power to give retrospective`
  line `effect, from a date not earlier than the date of commencement of this Act, to the rules or any of them and,`
  line `unless the contrary is permitted (whether expressly or by necessary implication), no retrospective effect`
  line `shall be given to any rule so as to prejudicially affect the interests of assessees.]`
  line `8 [( 4 ) The Central Government shall cause every rule made under this Act 9 [and the rules of procedure`
  line `framed by the Settlement Commission under sub-section ( 7 ) of section 22F] to be laid as soon as may be`
  line `after it is made before each House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days`
  line `which may be comprised in one session 10 [or in two or more successive sessions], and if before the expiry`
  line `of the session 11 [immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid], both Houses`
  line `agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the`
  line `rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be, so`
  line `however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything`
  line `previously done under that rule.]`
  line `12 [ 46A. Power to make exemption, etc., in relation to certain Union territories. — If the Central`
  line `Government considers it necessary or expedient so to do for avoiding any hardship or anomaly or`
  line `removing any difficulty that may arise as a result of the application of this Act to the Union territories of`
  line `Dadra and Nagar Haveli, Goa, Daman and Diu, and Pondicherry, or in the case of the Union territory of`
  line `Pondicherry, for implementing any provision of the Treaty of Cession concluded between France and`
  line `India on the 28th day of May, 1956, that Government may, by general or special order, make an`
  line `exemption, reduction in rate or other modification in respect of wealth-tax in favour of any class of assets`
  line `or in regard to the whole or any part of the net wealth of any assessee or class of assessees:`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 16 of 1972, s. 51 (w.e.f. 1-4-1972).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Appellate Assistant Commissioner” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 29 of 1977, s. 39 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 10-7-1978).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 127, for “Wealth - tax Officer” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1988).`
  line `5. Ins. by Act 42 of 1970, s. 65 (w.e.f. 1-4-1971).`
  line `6. Subs. by Act 45 of 1972, s. 19, for clause ( e ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `7. Subs. by Act 26 of 1974, s. 17, for sub-section ( 3 ) (w.e.f. 18-8-1974).`
  line `8. Subs. by Act 46 of 1964, s. 40, for sub-section ( 4 ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1965).`
  line `9. Ins. by Act 32 of 1994, s. 53 (w.e.f. 1-6-1994).`
  line `10. Subs. by Act 41 of 1975, s. 105, for “or in two successive sessions” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1976).`
  line `11. Subs. by s. 105, ibid., for “in which it is so laid or the session immediately following” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1976).`
  line `12. Ins. by the Taxation Laws (Extension to Union Territories) Regulation, 1963 (3 of 1963) (w.e.f. 1-4-1963).`
