  line 100
  line `Provided that the power conferred by this section shall not be exercisable after the 31st day of March,`
  line `1967, except for the purposes of rescinding an exemption, reduction or modification already made.]`
  line `1 [ 47. Power to remove difficulties. — ( 1 ) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act as amended by the Direct Tax Laws (Amendment) Act, 1987, the Central Government may, by`
  line `order, do anything not inconsistent with such provisions for the purpose of removing the difficulty:`
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiration of three years from the 1st day of April,`
  line 1988.
  line `( 2 ) Every order made under sub-section ( 1 ) shall be laid before each House of Parliament.]`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 4 of 1988, s. 159 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
