obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line 101
  line `1 [ SCHEDULE I ]`
  line `2 [[ See section 3(1)]]`
  line `RATES OF WEALTH-TAX`
  line `3 [ PART I`
  line `( 1 ) In the case of every individual or Hindu undivided family, not being a Hindu undivided family, to`
  line `which item (2) of this Part applies, —`
  line `Rate of tax`
  line `( a ) where the net wealth does not exceed Rs. 2,50,000 Nil;`
  line `( b ) where the net wealth exceeds Rs. 2,50,000 but does`
  line `not exceed Rs. 10,00,000`
  line `½ per cent. of the amount by which the net wealth`
  line `exceeds Rs. 2,50,000;`
  line `( c ) where the net wealth exceeds Rs 10,00,000 but does`
  line `not exceed Rs. 20,00,000`
  line `Rs. 3,750 plus 1 per cent. of the amount by which`
  line `the net wealth exceeds Rs. 10,00,000;`
  line `( d ) where the net wealth exceeds Rs. 20,00,000 Rs. 13,750 plus 2 per cent. of the amount by which`
  line `the net wealth exceeds Rs. 20,00,000.`
  line `(2) In the case of every Hindu undivided family which has at least one member whose net wealth`
  line `assessable for the assessment year exceeds Rs. 2,50,000, —`
  line `Rate of tax`
  line `( a ) where the net wealth does not exceed Rs. 1,50,000 Nil;`
  line `( b ) where the net wealth exceeds Rs. 1,50,000 but does`
  line `not exceed Rs. 5,00,000`
  line `1 per cent. of the amount by which the net wealth`
  line `exceeds Rs. 1,50,000;`
  line `( c ) where the net wealth exceeds Rs. 5,00,000, but does`
  line `not exceed Rs. 10,00,000`
  line `Rs. 3,500 plus 2 per cent. of the amount by which`
  line `the net wealth exceeds Rs. 5,00,000;`
  line `( d ) where the net wealth exceeds Rs. 10,00,000 Rs. 13,500 plus 3 per cent. of the amount by which`
  line `the net wealth exceeds Rs. 10,00,000.]`
  line `4 [ Surcharge on wealth-tax`
  line `The amount of wealth-tax computed in accordance with the provisions of this Part shall, in relation to`
  line `the assessment year commencing on the 1st day of April, 1988 be increased by surcharge calculated at the`
  line `rate of ten per cent of such wealth-tax.]`
  line `5 * * * * *`
  line `6 * * * * *`
  line `7 * * * * *`
  line `8 * * * * *`
  line `9 * * * * *`
  line `1. The Schedule numbered as Schedule I thereof by Act 66 of 1976, s. 27 ( b ) (w.e.f. 1-4-1977).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 18 of 1992, s. 100, for “(See section 3)” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1993).`
  line `3. Subs. by Act 32 of 1985, s. 40, for Part I (w.e.f. 1-4-1986).`
  line `4. Added by Act 26 of 1988, s. 66 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line `5. Part II omitted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 100 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `6. Rule 1 omitted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 100 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `7. Rule 2 omitted by Act 19 of 1970, s. 26 (w.r.e.f. 1-4-1969).`
  line `8. Rules 3, 4, 5 omitted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 100 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
  line `9. Schedule II omitted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 100 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993). Earlier it was inserted by Act 66 of 1976, s. 27 (w.e.f. 1-4-1977).`
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-102
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 102
  title `Page 102`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  sourcePage 102
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line 102
  line `1 [ SCHEDULE III`
  line `[ See section 7(1)]`
  line `RULES FOR DETERMINING THE VALUE OF ASSETS`
  line `PART A`
  line `G ENERAL`
  line `1. Value of assets how to be determined. — The value of any asset, other than cash, for the purposes`
  line `of this Act, shall be determined in the manner laid down in these rules.`
  line `2. Definitions. — In this Schedule, unless the context otherwise requires, —`
  line `( 1 ) “accounting year” in relation to a company means a period in respect of which any profit and`
  line `loss account of the company laid before it in the annual general meeting is made up;`
  line `( 2 ) “debenture” in cludes debenture stock, bonds and any other securities of a company, whether`
  line `constituting a charge on the assets of the company or not;`
  line `( 3 ) “equity share” means any share in the share capital of a company other than a preference`
  line share;
  line `( 4 ) “gold” means gol d, including its alloy, whether virgin, melted, remelted, wrought or`
  line `unwrought, in any shape or form of a purity of not less than nine carats and includes any gold coin`
  line `(whether legal tender or not), any gold ornament and other article of gold;`
  line `( 5 ) “gold ornament” means any article in a finished form, meant for personal adornment or for the`
  line `adornment of any idol, deity or any other object of religious worship made of, or manufactured from,`
  line `gold, whether or not set with stones or gems, real or artificial, or with pearls, real, cultured or`
  line `imitation, or with all or any of them and includes parts, pendants or broken pieces of gold ornaments;`
  line `( 6 ) “investment company” means a company whose gross total income consists mainly of income`
  line `which is chargeable to income- tax under the heads “Income from house property”, “Capital gains”`
  line `and “Income from other sources”.`
  line `Explanation. —In this clause, the expression “gross total income” shall have the meaning`
  line `assigned to it in section 80B of the Income-tax Act;`
  line `( 7 ) “ jewellery ” includes—`
  line `( a ) ornaments made of gold, silver, platinum or any other precious metal or any alloy`
  line `containing one or more of such precious metals, whether or not containing any precious or semi-`
  line `precious stones, and whether or not worked or sewn into any wearing apparel;`
  line `( b ) precious or semi-precious stones, whether or not set in any furniture, utensils or other`
  line `article or worked or sewn into any apparel;`
  line `( 8 ) “preference share” has the meaning assigned to it in section 85 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1`
  line `of 1956);`
  line `( 9 ) “quoted share” or “quoted debenture”, in relation to an equity share or a preference share or,`
  line `as the case may be, a debenture, means a share or debenture quoted on any recognised stock exchange`
  line `with regularity from time to time, where the quotations of such shares or debentures are based on`
  line `current transactions made in the ordinary course of business.`
  line `Explanation. — Where any question arises whether a share or debenture is a “ quoted share ” or a`
  line `“ quoted debenture ” within the meaning of this clause, a certificate to that effect furnished by the`
  line `concerned stock exchange in the prescribed form shall be accepted as conclusive;`
  line `1. Ins. by Act 3 of 1989, s. 78 (w.e.f. 1-4-1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-103
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 103
  title `Page 103`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  sourcePage 103
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line 103
  line `( 10 ) “ recognised stock exchange ” has the meaning assigned to it in clause ( f ) of section 2 of the`
  line `Securities Contracts (Regulation) Act, 1956 (42 of 1956);`
  line `( 11 ) “ unquoted share ” or “ unquoted debenture ”, in relation to an equity share or a preference`
  line `share or, as the case may be, a debenture, means a share or debenture which is not a quoted share or a`
  line `quoted debenture.`
  line `PART B`
  line `I MMOVABLE PROPERTY`
  line `3. Valuation of immovable property. — Subject to the provisions of rules 4, 5, 6, 7 and 8, for the`
  line `purposes of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 7, the value of any immovable property, being a building or land`
  line `appurtenant thereto, or part thereof, shall be the amount arrived at by multiplying the net maintainable`
  line `rent by the figure 12.5:`
  line `Provided that in relation to any such property which is constructed on leasehold land, this rule shall`
  line `have effect as if for the figure 12.5, —`
  line `( a ) where the unexpired period of the lease of such land is fifty years or more, the figure 10.0 had`
  line `been substituted; and`
  line `( b ) where the unexpired period of the lease of such land is less than fifty years, the figure 8.0 had`
  line `been substituted:`
  line `Provided further that where such property is acquired or construction of which is completed after`
  line `the 31st day of March, 1974, if the value so arrived at is lower than the cost of acquisition or the cost`
  line `of construction, as increased, in either case, by the cost of any improvement to the property, the cost`
  line `of acquisition or, as the case may be, the cost of construction, as so increased, shall be taken to be the`
  line `value of the property under this rule:`
  line `Provided also that the provisions of the second proviso shall not apply for determining the value`
  line `of one house belonging to the assessee, where such house is acquired or the construction whereof is`
  line `completed after the 31st day of March, 1974, and the house is exclusively used by the assessee for his`
  line `own residential purposes throughout the period of twelve months immediately preceding the`
  line `valuation date and the cost of acquisition or, as the case may be, the cost of construction, as increased,`
  line `in either case, by the cost of any improvement to the house, does not exceed, —`
  line `( a ) if the house is situate at Bombay, Calcutta, Delhi or Madras, fifty lakh rupees;`
  line `( b ) if the house is situate at any other place, twenty-five lakh rupees:`
  line `Provided also that where more than one house belonging to the assessee is exclusively used`
  line `by him for residential purposes, the provisions of the third proviso shall apply only in respect of`
  line `one of such houses which the assessee may, at his option, specify in this behalf.`
  line `4. Net maintainable rent how to be computed. — For the purposes of rule 3, "net maintainable rent"`
  line `in relation to an immovable property referred to in that rule, shall be the amount of gross maintainable`
  line `rent as reduced by —`
  line `( i ) the amount of taxes levied by any local authority in respect of the property; and`
  line `( ii ) a sum equal to fifteen per cent of the gross maintainable rent.`
  line `5. Gross maintainable rent how to be computed. — For the purposes of rule 4, “ gross maintainable`
  line `rent ”, in relation to any immovable property referred to in rule 3, means —`
  line `( i ) where the property is let, the amount received or receivable by the owner as annual rent or the`
  line `annual value assessed by the local authority in whose area the property is situated for the purposes of`
  line `levy of property tax or any other tax on the basis of such assessment, whichever is higher;`
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-104
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 104
  title `Page 104`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  sourcePage 104
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line 104
  line `( ii ) where the property is not let, the amount of annual rent assessed by the local authority in`
  line `whose area the property is situated for the purpose of levy of property tax or any other tax on the`
  line `basis of such assessment, or, if there is no such assessment or the property is situated outside the area`
  line `of any local authority the amount which the owner can reasonably be expected to receive as annual`
  line `rent had such property been let.`
  line `Explanation. — In this rule, —`
  line `( 1 ) “ annual rent ” means, —`
  line `( a ) where the property is let throughout the year ending on the valuation date (hereinafter`
  line `referred to as “ previous year ” ), the actual rent received or receivable by the owner in respect of`
  line `such year;`
  line `( b ) where the property is let for only a part of the previous year, the amount which bears the`
  line `same proportion to the amount of actual rent received or receivable by the owner for the period`
  line `for which the property is let as the period of twelve months bears to the number of months`
  line `(including part of a month) during which the property is let during the previous year:`
  line `Provided that in the following cases, such actual rent under sub-clauses ( a ) and ( b ) shall be`
  line `increased in the manner specified below: —`
  line `( i ) where the property is in the occupation of a tenant and taxes levied by any local`
  line `authority in respect of the property are borne wholly or partly by the tenant, by the amount of`
  line `the taxes so borne by the tenant;`
  line `( ii ) where the property is in the occupation of a tenant and expenditure on repairs in`
  line `respect of the property is borne by the tenant, by one-ninth of the actual rent;`
  line `( iii ) where the owner has accepted any amount as deposit (not being advance payment`
  line `towards rent for a period of three months or less), by the amount calculated at the rate of 15`
  line `per cent per annum on the amount of deposit outstanding from month to month, for the`
  line `number of months (excluding part of a month) during which such deposit was held by the`
  line `owner in the previous year, and if the owner is liable to pay interest on such deposit, the`
  line `increase to be made under this clause shall be limited to the sum by which the amount`
  line `calculated as aforesaid exceeds the interest actually paid;`
  line `( iv ) where the owner has received any amount by way of premium or otherwise as`
  line `consideration for leasing of the property or any modification of the terms of the lease, by the`
  line `amount obtained by dividing the premium or other amount by the number of years of the`
  line `period of the lease;`
  line `( v ) where the owner derives any benefit or perquisite, whether convertible into money or`
  line `not, as consideration for leasing of the property or any modification of the terms of the lease`
  line `by the value of such benefit or perquisite;`
  line `( 2 ) “ rent received or receivable ” shall include all payments for the use of the property, by`
  line `whatever name called, the value of all benefits or perquisites whether convertible into money or not,`
  line `obtained from a tenant or occupier of the property and any sum paid by a tenant or occupier of the`
  line `property in respect of any obligation which, but for such payment, would have been payable by the`
  line owner.
  line `6. Adjustments to value arrived at under rule 3, for unbuilt area of plot of land. — Where the`
  line `unbuilt area of the plot of land on which the property referred to in rule 3 is constructed exceeds the`
  line `specified area, the value arrived at in accordance with the provisions of rule 3 shall be increased by an`
  line `amount calculated in the following manner, namely: —`
  line `( a ) where the difference between the unbuilt area and the specified area exceeds five per cent. but`
  line `does not exceed ten per cent. of the aggregate area, by an amount equal to twenty per cent of such`
  line value;
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-105
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 105
  title `Page 105`
  content obj_root_law_sections_105_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes
  sourcePage 105
obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line 105
  line `( b ) where the difference between the unbuilt area and the specified area exceeds ten per cent but`
  line `does not exceed fifteen per cent of the aggre-gate area, by an amount equal to thirty per cent of such`
  line value;
  line `( c ) where the difference between the unbuilt area and the specified area exceeds fifteen per cent`
  line `but does not exceed twenty per cent of the aggregate area, by an amount equal to forty per cent of`
  line `such value.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this rule and rule 6, —`
  line `( a ) “ aggregate area ”, in relation to the plot of land on which the property is constructed, means`
  line `the aggregate of the area on which the property is constructed and the unbuilt area;`
  line `( b ) “ specified area ”, in relation to the plot of land on which the property is constructed, means —`
  line `( i ) where the property is situate at Bombay, Calcutta, Delhi or Madras, sixty per cent of the`
  line `aggregate area;`
  line `( ii ) where the property is situate at Agra, Ahmedabad, Allahabad, Amritsar, Bangalore,`
  line `Bhopal, Cochin, Hyderabad, Indore, Jabalpur, Jamshedpur, Kanpur, Lucknow, Ludhiana,`
  line `Madurai, Nagpur, Patna, Pune, Salem, Sholapur, Srinagar, Surat, Tiruchirapalli, Trivandrum,`
  line `Vadodara (Baroda) or Varanasi (Benaras), sixty-five per cent. of the aggregate area; and`
  line `( iii ) where the property is situate at any other place, seventy per cent. of the aggregate area:`
  line `Provided that where, under any law for the time being in force, the minimum area of the plot`
  line `of land required to be kept as open space for the enjoyment of the property exceeds the specified`
  line `area, such minimum area shall be deemed to be the specified area;`
  line `( c ) “ unbuilt area ”, in relation to the aggregate area of the plot of land on which the property is`
  line `constructed, means that part of such aggregate area on which no building has been erected.`
  line `7. Adjustment for unearned increase in the value of the land. — Where the property is constructed`
  line `on land obtained on lease from the Government, a local authority or any authority referred to in clause`
  line `( 20A ) of section 10 of the Income-tax Act, and the Government or any such authority is, under the terms`
  line `of the lease, entitled to claim and recover a specified part of the unearned increase in the value of the land`
  line `at the time of the transfer of the property, the value of such property as determined under rule 3 shall be`
  line `reduced by the amount so liable to be claimed and recovered or by an amount equal to fifty per cent. of`
  line `the value of the property as so determined, whichever is less, as if the property had been transferred on`
  line `the valuation date.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purpose of this rule, "unearned increase" means the difference between the`
  line `value of such land on the valuation date as determined by the Government or such authority for the`
  line `purpose of calculating such increase and the amount of the premium paid or payable to the Government`
  line `or such authority for the lease of the land.`
  line `8. Rule 3 not to apply in certain cases. — Nothing contained in rule 3 shall apply, —`
  line `( a ) where, having regard to the facts and circumstances of the case, the Assessing Officer, with`
  line `the previous approval of the Deputy Commissioner, is of opinion that it is not practicable to apply the`
  line `provisions of the said rule to such a case; or`
  line `( b ) where the difference between the unbuilt area and the specified area exceeds twenty per cent`
  line `of the aggregate area; or`
  line `( c ) where the property is constructed on leasehold land and the lease expires within a period not`
  line `exceeding fifteen years from the relevant valuation date and the deed of lease does not give an option`
  line `to the lessee for the renewal of the lease,`
  line `and in any case referred to in clause ( a ) or clause ( b ) or clause ( c ), the value of the property shall be`
  line `determined in the manner laid down in rule 20.`
obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_106:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-106
  sectionNo (106)
  orderNo 106
  title `Page 106`
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes
  sourcePage 106
obj_root_law_sections_106_content:
  string
  line 106
  line `1 * * * * *`
  line `PART D`
  line `A SSETS OF BUSINESS`
  line `14. Global valuation of assets of business. — ( 1 ) Where the assessee is carrying on a business for`
  line `which accounts are maintained by him regularly, the net value of the assets of the business as a whole,`
  line `having regard to the balance-sheet of such business on the valuation date after adjustments specified in`
  line `sub-rule (2) shall be taken as the value of such assets for the purposes of this Act.`
  line `( 2 ) For the purposes of sub-rule (1) —`
  line `( a ) the value of any asset as disclosed in the balance-sheet shall be taken to be, —`
  line `( i ) in the case of an asset on which depreciation is admissible, its written-down value;`
  line `( ii ) in the case of an asset on which no depreciation is admissible, its book value;`
  line `( iii ) in the case of closing stock its value adopted for the purposes of assessment under the`
  line `Income-tax Act for the previous year relevant to the corresponding assessment year;`
  line `( b ) where the value of any of the assets referred to in clause ( a ), deter-mined in accordance with`
  line `the provisions of this Schedule as applicable to that particular asset or if there are no such provisions,`
  line `determined in accordance with rule 20, exceeds the value arrived at in accordance with clause ( a ) by`
  line `more than 20 per cent, then the higher value shall be taken to be the value of that asset;`
  line `( c ) the value of an asset not disclosed in the balance-sheet, shall be taken to be the value`
  line `determined in accordance with the provisions of this Schedule as applicable to that asset;`
  line `( d ) the value of the following assets which are disclosed in the balance sheet shall not be taken`
  line `into account, namely: —`
  line `( i ) any amount paid as advance tax under the Income-tax Act;`
  line `( ii ) the debt due to the assessee according to the balance-sheet or part thereof which has been`
  line `allowed as a deduction under clause ( vii ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 36 of the Income-tax Act,`
  line `for the purposes of assessment for the previous year relevant to the corresponding assessment`
  line `year under that Act;`
  line `( iii ) the value of any asset in respect of which wealth-tax is not payable under this Act;`
  line `( iv ) any amount shown in the balance-sheet including the debit balance in the profit and loss`
  line `account or profit and loss appropriation account which does not represent the value of any asset;`
  line `( v ) any asset shown in the balance-sheet not really pertaining to the business;`
  line `( e ) the following amounts shown as liabilities in the balance-sheet shall not be taken into account,`
  line `namely: —`
  line `( i ) capital employed in the business other than that attributable to borrowed money;`
  line `( ii ) reserves by whatever name called;`
  line `( iii ) any provision made for meeting any future or contingent liability;`
  line `( iv ) any liability shown in the balance-sheet not really pertaining to the business;`
  line `1. Part C omitted by Act 18 of 1992, s. 100 (w.e.f. 1-4-1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_107:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-107
  sectionNo (107)
  orderNo 107
  title `Page 107`
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes
  sourcePage 107
obj_root_law_sections_107_content:
  string
  line 107
  line `( v ) any debt owed by the assessee to the extent to which it has been specifically utilised for`
  line `acquiring an asset in respect of which wealth-tax is not payable under this Act:`
  line `Provided that where it is not possible to calculate the amount of debt so utilised, it shall be`
  line `taken as the amount which bears the same proportion to the total of the debts owed by the`
  line `assessee as the value of that asset bears to the total value of the assets of the business.`
  line `Explanation. — Provision for any purpose other than taxation shall be treated as a reserve.`
  line `PART E`
  line `I NTEREST IN FIRM OR ASSOCIATION OF PERSONS`
  line `15. Valuation of interest in firm or association of persons. — The value of the interest of a person`
  line `in a firm of which he is a partner or in an association of persons of which he is a member shall be`
  line `determined in the manner provided in rule 16.`
  line `16. Computation of net wealth of the firm or association and its allocation amongst the partners`
  line `or members. — The net wealth of the firm or association of persons on the valuation date shall first be`
  line `determined as if it were the assessee and, thereafter, —`
  line `( i ) that portion of the net wealth of the firm or association as is equal to the amount of its capital`
  line `shall be allocated among the partners or members in the proportion in which capital has been`
  line `contributed by them;`
  line `( ii ) the residue of the net wealth of the firm or association shall be allocated amongst the partners`
  line `or members in accordance with the agreement of partnership or association for the distribution of`
  line `assets in the event of dissolution of the firm or association or, in the absence of such agreement, in the`
  line `proportion in which the partners or members are entitled to share the profits,`
  line `and the sum total of amounts so allocated to a partner or member under clause ( i ) and clause ( ii ) shall be`
  line `treated as the value of the interest of that partner or member in the firm or association:`
  line `Provided that in determining the net wealth of the firm or association for the purposes of this rule, no`
  line `account shall be taken of the exemptions in sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 1A ) of section 5.`
  line `Explanation. — For the purposes of this rule, —`
  line `( a ) where the net wealth of the firm or association computed in accordance with this rule includes`
  line `the value of any assets located outside India, the value of the interest of any partner or member in the`
  line `assets located in India shall be determined having regard to the proportion which the value of assets`
  line `located in India diminished by the debts relating to those assets bears to the net wealth of the firm or`
  line association;
  line `( b ) where the net wealth of the firm or association computed in accordance with this rule includes`
  line `the value of any assets which are exempt from inclusion in the net wealth under sub-sections ( 1 ) and`
  line `( 1A ) of section 5, the value of the interest of a partner or member shall be deemed to include the value`
  line `of his proportionate share in the said assets and, the provisions of sub-sections ( 1 ) and ( 1A ) of section`
  line `5 shall apply to him accordingly;`
  line `( c ) where the net wealth of the firm or association computed in accordance with this rule includes`
  line `the value of any assets referred to in sub-section ( 2 ) of section 5, the value of the interest of a partner`
  line `or member shall be deemed to include the value of his proportionate share in the said assets, and the`
  line `provisions of sub-section ( 2 ) of section 5 shall apply to him accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_108:
  kind page
  sectionId pdf-page-108
  sectionNo (108)
  orderNo 108
  title `Page 108`
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes
  sourcePage 108
obj_root_law_sections_108_content:
  string
  line 108
  line `PART F`
  line `L IFE INTEREST`
  line `17. Valuation of life interest. — ( 1 ) For the purposes of sub-section (1) of section 7, the value of the`
  line `life interest of an assessee shall be arrived at by multiplying the average annual income that accrued to the`
  line `assessee from the life interest by the fraction 1 minus 1, where ‘P’ represents the annual premium`
  line `p + d`
  line `for a whole life insurance without profits on the life of the life tenant for unit sum assured as specified in`
  line `the Appendix to these rules, and ‘d’ is equal to i “i” being the rate of interest.`
  line 1+i
  line `Explanation. — In this rule, —`
  line `( a ) “ life tenant ” means a person for the duration of whose life the life interest is to subsist;`
  line `( b ) “ average annual income ” means the average of the gross income derived by the assessee from`
  line `the life interest during each year of the period ending on the valuation date, reduced by the average of`
  line `the expenses incurred on the collection of such income in each of those years:`
  line `Provided that the amount of the reduction for such expenses shall, in no case, exceed five per cent`
  line `of the average of the annual gross income:`
  line `Provided further that in case the income so derived is for a period exceeding three years, only that`
  line `income derived during the three years ending on the valuation date shall be taken into account;`
  line `( c ) the rate of interest shall be 6½ per cent. per annum.`
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-rule (1), —`
  line `( a ) the Assessing Officer may, if he is of the opinion that in the case of the life tenant, a life`
  line `insurance company would not take the risk of insuring his life at the normal premium rates in force`
  line `but would demand a higher premium, vary the valuation suitably;`
  line `( b ) the value of the life interest so determined shall, in no case, exceed the value as on the`
  line `valuation date as determined under this Schedule, of the corpus of the trust from which the life`
  line `interest is derived.`
  line `PART G`
  line `J EWELLERY`
  line `1 [ 18. Valuation of jewellery. — ( 1 ) The value of the jewellery shall be estimated to be the price which`
  line `it would fetch if sold in the open market on the valuation date (hereafter in this rule referred to as fair`
  line `market value).`
  line `( 2 ) The return of net wealth furnished by the assessee shall be supported by, —`
  line `( i ) a statement in the prescribed form, where the value of the jewellery on the valuation date does`
  line `not exceed rupees five lakhs;`
  line `( ii ) a report of a registered valuer in the prescribed form, where the value of the jewellery on the`
  line `valuation date exceeds rupees five lakhs.`
  line `( 3 ) Notwithstanding anything mentioned in sub-rule (2), the Assessing Officer may, if he is of`
  line `opinion, that the value of the jewellery declared in the return, —`
  line `( a ) is less than its fair market value by such percentage or such amount as is prescribed under`
  line `sub-clause ( i ) of clause ( b ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 16A;`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 58, for rule 18 (w.e.f. 1-4-1990).`
obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes:
  string
  line
