  string
  line 109
  line `( b ) is less than its fair market value as referred to in clause ( a ) of sub-section ( 1 ) of section 16A,`
  line `he may refer the valuation of such jewellery to a Valuation Officer under sub-section ( 1 ) of the said`
  line `section and the value of such jewellery shall be the fair market value as estimated by the Valuation`
  line Officer.]
  line `19. Adjustment in value of jewellery for subsequent assessment years. — The value of any`
  line `jewellery determined in accordance with 1 [sub-rule (3) of] rule 18 for any assessment year (hereinafter`
  line `referred to as the first assessment year), shall be taken to be the value of such jewellery for the subsequent`
  line `four assessment years, subject to the following adjustments, namely: —`
  line `( a ) where the jewellery includes gold or silver or any alloy containing gold or silver, the value of`
  line `such gold or silver or such alloy as on the valuation date relevant to the concerned subsequent`
  line `assessment year shall be substituted for the value of such gold or silver or alloy on the valuation date`
  line `relevant to the first assessment year;`
  line `( b ) where any jewellery or part of jewellery is sold or otherwise disposed of by the assessee, or`
  line `any jewellery or part of jewellery is acquired by him, on or before the valuation date relevant to the`
  line `concerned subsequent year, the value of the jewellery determined for the first assessment year shall`
  line `be reduced or increased, as the case may be, and the value as so reduced or increased shall be the`
  line `value of the jewellery for such subsequent assessment year.`
  line `PART H`
  line RESIDUARY
  line `20. Valuation of assets in other cases. — ( 1 ) The value of any asset, other than cash, being an asset`
  line `which is not covered by rules 3 to 19, for the purposes of this Act, shall be estimated to be the price`
  line `which, in the opinion of the Assessing Officer, it would fetch if sold in the open market on the valuation`
  line date.
  line `( 2 ) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-rule (1), where the valuation of any asset referred to in`
  line `that sub-rule is referred by the Assessing Officer to the Valuation Officer under section 16A, the value of`
  line `such asset shall be estimated to be the price which, in the opinion of the Valuation Officer, it would fetch`
  line `if sold in the open market on the valuation date.`
  line `( 3 ) Where the value of any asset cannot be estimated under this rule because it is not saleable in the`
  line `open market, the value shall be determined in accordance with such guidelines or principles as may be`
  line `specified by the Board from time to time by general or special order.`
  line `21. Restrictive covenants to be ignored in determining market value. — For the removal of doubts,`
  line `it is hereby declared that the price or other consideration for which any property may be acquired by or`
  line `transferred to any person under the terms of a deed of trust or through or under any restrictive covenant in`
  line `any instrument of transfer shall be ignored for the purposes of determining under any provision of this`
  line `Schedule, the price such property would fetch if sold in the open market on the valuation date.`
  line `1. Subs. by Act 12 of 1990, s. 58, for “clause ( b ) of” (w.e.f. 1 -4-1990).`
